{"mode":"editor","version":1,"windowDimensions":{"x":0,"y":23,"width":1024,"height":752,"maximized":false},"grammars":{"deserializer":"GrammarRegistry","grammarOverridesByPath":{}},"project":{"paths":["/Users/joegesualdo/code/node/modules/subtitle-hero/videos-srt"],"buffers":[{"load":true,"text":"1\n00:00:02,335 --> 00:00:04,637\nMr. Earnest: Good\nafternoon, everybody.\n\n2\n00:00:04,637 --> 00:00:05,672\nNice to see you.\n\n3\n00:00:07,307 --> 00:00:08,475\nLet me do a quick\nannouncement at the top\n\n4\n00:00:08,475 --> 00:00:10,410\nand then we'll go\nto your questions.\n\n5\n00:00:10,410 --> 00:00:14,080\nI just want to begin by\nnoting that seven years ago\n\n6\n00:00:14,080 --> 00:00:18,017\ntoday, Lehman Brothers filed\nfor bankruptcy, setting off\n\n7\n00:00:18,017 --> 00:00:21,221\nthe worst financial crisis\nof our lifetimes.\n\n8\n00:00:21,221 --> 00:00:24,124\nWhen President Obama took\noffice in 2009, financial\n\n9\n00:00:24,124 --> 00:00:27,327\nmarkets were spiraling\ndangerously downward and\n\n10\n00:00:27,327 --> 00:00:29,629\nmore than 750,000\nAmericans were losing\n\n11\n00:00:29,629 --> 00:00:32,265\ntheir jobs each month.\n\n12\n00:00:32,265 --> 00:00:34,267\nBut thanks to the hard work\nand dedication of American\n\n13\n00:00:34,267 --> 00:00:37,237\nworkers and businesses and\nentrepreneurs, and of\n\n14\n00:00:37,237 --> 00:00:39,506\ncourse, to the policies that\nthe President enacted, some\n\n15\n00:00:39,506 --> 00:00:41,508\nof which were politically\ncontroversial and\n\n16\n00:00:41,508 --> 00:00:44,611\nhard-fought, we've come\na long way back.\n\n17\n00:00:44,611 --> 00:00:46,613\nAnd there are a number of\nways to illustrate the\n\n18\n00:00:46,613 --> 00:00:48,615\nprogress that we've made so\nfar, and I've got a couple\n\n19\n00:00:48,615 --> 00:00:50,884\nof slides here to help\nillustrate what a couple of\n\n20\n00:00:50,884 --> 00:00:51,885\nthose are.\n\n21\n00:00:51,885 --> 00:00:54,421\nSo, cue the slides.\n\n22\n00:00:54,421 --> 00:00:56,423\nLook at this, we're going\nmultimedia here.\n\n23\n00:00:58,625 --> 00:01:02,395\nAs the slide indicates, Wall\nStreet has made some\n\n24\n00:01:02,395 --> 00:01:03,430\nimportant progress.\n\n25\n00:01:03,430 --> 00:01:06,232\nThere are a lot of ways to\nmeasure that -- everything\n\n26\n00:01:06,232 --> 00:01:11,204\nfrom the S&P 500 -- the year\nbefore the President took\n\n27\n00:01:11,204 --> 00:01:16,676\noffice, the S&P was down 39\npercent.\n\n28\n00:01:16,676 --> 00:01:19,379\nSince then, the value of the\nstock market has nearly\n\n29\n00:01:19,379 --> 00:01:21,448\ntripled.\n\n30\n00:01:21,448 --> 00:01:24,551\nYou can also measure this\nvia economic growth.\n\n31\n00:01:24,551 --> 00:01:27,253\nEconomic output declined at\nan annual rate of 8.2\n\n32\n00:01:27,253 --> 00:01:29,789\npercent during the\nPresident's -- or during the\n\n33\n00:01:29,789 --> 00:01:33,126\nlast quarter of 2008, so the\nquarter before the President\n\n34\n00:01:33,126 --> 00:01:34,127\ntook office.\n\n35\n00:01:34,127 --> 00:01:36,129\nAnd over the last year,\nwe've seen our economy grow\n\n36\n00:01:36,129 --> 00:01:38,932\nat a healthy 2.7 percent\nover the last year.\n\n37\n00:01:38,932 --> 00:01:43,036\nThat obviously is an 11\npercentage point turnaround,\n\n38\n00:01:43,036 --> 00:01:46,773\nand stands in stark contrast\nto the GDP that's being\n\n39\n00:01:46,773 --> 00:01:50,109\nposted by other countries\naround the world these days.\n\n40\n00:01:50,109 --> 00:01:51,544\nLet's go to the second\nslide.\n\n41\n00:01:51,544 --> 00:01:56,349\nThe second slide illustrates\nthe significant improvement\n\n42\n00:01:56,349 --> 00:02:00,186\nin the housing market since\nthe President took office.\n\n43\n00:02:03,990 --> 00:02:06,125\nThe year before the\nPresident entered office,\n\n44\n00:02:06,125 --> 00:02:09,062\nhome prices had declined 8\npercent.\n\n45\n00:02:11,498 --> 00:02:14,634\nIn that time, we've seen the\nhousing market continue to\n\n46\n00:02:14,634 --> 00:02:18,404\nrecover and home prices are\nnow back to pre-crisis\n\n47\n00:02:18,404 --> 00:02:23,042\nlevels and just last year\nrose another 5 percent.\n\n48\n00:02:23,042 --> 00:02:27,680\nSo many middle-class\nfamilies rely on the value\n\n49\n00:02:27,680 --> 00:02:30,216\nof their home as an\nimportant part of their\n\n50\n00:02:30,216 --> 00:02:32,986\nhousehold wealth, so the\nimprovement in the housing\n\n51\n00:02:32,986 --> 00:02:33,987\nmarket is significant.\n\n52\n00:02:33,987 --> 00:02:36,990\nLet's go to the third and\nlast slide, which talks\n\n53\n00:02:36,990 --> 00:02:38,057\nabout job growth.\n\n54\n00:02:38,057 --> 00:02:40,260\nAnd this is our most\ncommonly cited set of\n\n55\n00:02:40,260 --> 00:02:41,761\nstatistics.\n\n56\n00:02:41,761 --> 00:02:44,097\nBut again, before the\nPresident took office, the\n\n57\n00:02:44,097 --> 00:02:46,399\nyear before the President\ntook office, our economy\n\n58\n00:02:46,399 --> 00:02:50,970\nlost 4.6 million private\nsector jobs, but since then\n\n59\n00:02:50,970 --> 00:02:56,242\nwe've been on the longest\nsustained streak of private\n\n60\n00:02:56,242 --> 00:03:01,447\nsector job creation, for a\ntotal of 13.1 million\n\n61\n00:03:01,447 --> 00:03:05,318\nprivate sector jobs created\nsince February of 2010.\n\n62\n00:03:05,318 --> 00:03:07,587\nAnd the overall employment\nrate has been cut nearly in\n\n63\n00:03:07,587 --> 00:03:12,492\nhalf, from the high of 10\npercent down to 5.1 percent\n\n64\n00:03:12,492 --> 00:03:13,493\ntoday.\n\n65\n00:03:13,493 --> 00:03:17,964\nThat's the lowest level in\nmore than seven years.\n\n66\n00:03:17,964 --> 00:03:19,966\nWhen you look at this\nprogress, it seems in stark\n\n67\n00:03:19,966 --> 00:03:22,602\ncontrast to what we are\nseeing from Republicans on\n\n68\n00:03:22,602 --> 00:03:23,803\nCapitol Hill.\n\n69\n00:03:23,803 --> 00:03:25,972\nInstead of playing games\nwith our economic progress\n\n70\n00:03:25,972 --> 00:03:30,143\nand imposing another set of\nself-inflicted wounds,\n\n71\n00:03:30,143 --> 00:03:33,379\nRepublicans need to do the\njob that voters have asked\n\n72\n00:03:33,379 --> 00:03:36,816\nthem to do, and that is to\npass a budget that reverses\n\n73\n00:03:36,816 --> 00:03:39,519\nthe harmful cuts known as\nthe sequester, and of\n\n74\n00:03:39,519 --> 00:03:42,722\ncourse, avoids another\ngovernment shutdown.\n\n75\n00:03:42,722 --> 00:03:45,358\nThe President will make this\ncase tomorrow when he speaks\n\n76\n00:03:45,358 --> 00:03:48,127\nwith and takes questions at\nthe quarterly meeting of the\n\n77\n00:03:48,127 --> 00:03:51,331\nBusiness Roundtable right\nhere in Washington, D.C. The\n\n78\n00:03:51,331 --> 00:03:53,466\nPresident will make the case\nto Congress that we cannot\n\n79\n00:03:53,466 --> 00:03:56,536\nafford to reverse course in\nthe progress that we've seen\n\n80\n00:03:56,536 --> 00:03:58,538\nby playing games with the\nbudget.\n\n81\n00:03:58,538 --> 00:04:00,540\nAnd it's critical that we\nincrease investments in\n\n82\n00:04:00,540 --> 00:04:03,009\ninfrastructure, that we\nsupport American jobs\n\n83\n00:04:03,009 --> 00:04:05,445\nthrough Made in America\nexports, that we strengthen\n\n84\n00:04:05,445 --> 00:04:09,816\neducation and innovation,\nand fight to undermine -- or\n\n85\n00:04:09,816 --> 00:04:13,019\nfight efforts to undermine\nWall Street reform.\n\n86\n00:04:13,019 --> 00:04:15,021\nSo that's something to look\nforward to tomorrow.\n\n87\n00:04:15,021 --> 00:04:17,023\nThe President will speak and\ntake questions at the\n\n88\n00:04:17,023 --> 00:04:19,292\nBusiness Roundtable, and\nthat will be open to\n\n89\n00:04:19,292 --> 00:04:21,294\ntraveling press pool, so all\nof you will have the\n\n90\n00:04:21,294 --> 00:04:22,729\nopportunity to see it.\n\n91\n00:04:22,729 --> 00:04:24,831\nSo with that long windup,\nNancy, thanks for your\n\n92\n00:04:24,831 --> 00:04:25,832\npatience.\n\n93\n00:04:25,832 --> 00:04:26,799\nLet's go to questions.\n\n94\n00:04:27,900 --> 00:04:30,837\nThe Press: A couple things\non the migrant situation.\n\n95\n00:04:30,837 --> 00:04:34,240\nWith the situation on the\nborder in Hungary and\n\n96\n00:04:34,240 --> 00:04:37,610\nelsewhere getting\nincreasingly desperate, what\n\n97\n00:04:37,610 --> 00:04:38,678\nis the U.S.\n\n98\n00:04:38,678 --> 00:04:40,913\nposition on mandatory\nquotas?\n\n99\n00:04:40,913 --> 00:04:42,749\nAnd is the U.S.\n\n100\n00:04:42,749 --> 00:04:44,417\ninvolved in trying to\nresolve the differences\n\n101\n00:04:44,417 --> 00:04:47,120\nbetween different countries\nthere about how to deal with\n\n102\n00:04:47,120 --> 00:04:48,955\nthe crisis?\n\n103\n00:04:48,955 --> 00:04:52,225\nMr. Earnest: Nancy, it is\nclear that our friends and\n\n104\n00:04:52,225 --> 00:04:56,963\nallies in Europe are dealing\nwith a significant\n\n105\n00:04:56,963 --> 00:05:01,567\nhumanitarian crisis, and\nthere's no downplaying the\n\n106\n00:05:01,567 --> 00:05:05,672\nhuman cost of the\ninstability in Syria that\n\n107\n00:05:05,672 --> 00:05:09,075\nhas led to millions of\npeople fleeing their homes\n\n108\n00:05:09,075 --> 00:05:11,077\nand their communities,\ntrying to escape the\n\n109\n00:05:11,077 --> 00:05:12,311\nterrible violence.\n\n110\n00:05:12,311 --> 00:05:15,982\nIt's led to an urgent\nhumanitarian situation in\n\n111\n00:05:15,982 --> 00:05:16,983\nEurope now.\n\n112\n00:05:18,985 --> 00:05:22,755\nYou have heard me offer\ncompliments to countries\n\n113\n00:05:22,755 --> 00:05:26,959\nlike Germany that have, both\non the part of their\n\n114\n00:05:26,959 --> 00:05:29,729\ngovernment and their\ncitizens, recognized the\n\n115\n00:05:29,729 --> 00:05:33,533\nhumanity of those in their\nmidst who are suffering and\n\n116\n00:05:33,533 --> 00:05:36,636\ntried to provide for their\nbasic humanitarian needs.\n\n117\n00:05:36,636 --> 00:05:40,807\nAnd ultimately it will be\nthe responsibility of the\n\n118\n00:05:40,807 --> 00:05:43,810\nnations of Europe and\nmembers of the EU to work\n\n119\n00:05:43,810 --> 00:05:45,878\ntogether to confront this\nproblem.\n\n120\n00:05:45,878 --> 00:05:50,349\nThere is tremendous capacity\nin the EU, both economically\n\n121\n00:05:50,349 --> 00:05:54,687\nand otherwise, to address\nthis problem, but they will\n\n122\n00:05:54,687 --> 00:05:56,689\nbe more effective in\nconfronting this problem if\n\n123\n00:05:56,689 --> 00:05:57,690\nthey act together.\n\n124\n00:05:57,690 --> 00:06:00,393\nI don't have specific\nconversations to tell you\n\n125\n00:06:00,393 --> 00:06:02,462\nabout at this point, but\nthere certainly are\n\n126\n00:06:02,462 --> 00:06:04,964\nadministration officials\nthat have been in touch with\n\n127\n00:06:04,964 --> 00:06:10,703\nthose in Europe and in the\nregion who are dealing with\n\n128\n00:06:10,703 --> 00:06:12,739\nthis crisis firsthand.\n\n129\n00:06:12,739 --> 00:06:17,744\nAnd the United States is\ncommitted to our role in\n\n130\n00:06:20,680 --> 00:06:23,683\nthis, which is to provide\nsignificant financial\n\n131\n00:06:23,683 --> 00:06:26,252\nassistance to meeting the\nbasic humanitarian needs of\n\n132\n00:06:26,252 --> 00:06:28,588\nthose who are in this\nvulnerable position, these\n\n133\n00:06:28,588 --> 00:06:29,589\nmigrants.\n\n134\n00:06:29,589 --> 00:06:32,191\nThe United States continues\nto be the largest bilateral\n\n135\n00:06:32,191 --> 00:06:35,661\ndonor of humanitarian\nassistance to this crisis.\n\n136\n00:06:35,661 --> 00:06:37,830\nThe President has indicated\nthat next year he would like\n\n137\n00:06:37,830 --> 00:06:41,968\nto see us scale up the\nnumber of Syrian refugees\n\n138\n00:06:41,968 --> 00:06:45,972\nthat are admitted to this\ncountry, a minimum of 10,000\n\n139\n00:06:45,972 --> 00:06:47,240\nnext year.\n\n140\n00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:49,542\nAnd the President's national\nsecurity team is continuing\n\n141\n00:06:49,542 --> 00:06:53,446\nto work on other ways that\nthe United States can\n\n142\n00:06:53,446 --> 00:06:56,382\ncontinue to play a leading\nrole in confronting this\n\n143\n00:06:56,382 --> 00:06:58,384\nsignificant\ninternational crisis.\n\n144\n00:06:59,552 --> 00:07:01,754\nThe Press: Does he have a\nposition on the mandatory\n\n145\n00:07:01,754 --> 00:07:02,822\nquotas, though?\n\n146\n00:07:02,822 --> 00:07:03,990\nMr. Earnest: Ultimately, it\nwill be the responsibility\n\n147\n00:07:03,990 --> 00:07:07,527\nof the nations in Europe to\ndetermine that best way to\n\n148\n00:07:07,527 --> 00:07:10,263\nwork together to confront\nthis crisis.\n\n149\n00:07:10,263 --> 00:07:13,232\nAnd we've seen some\ncountries -- Germany is the\n\n150\n00:07:13,232 --> 00:07:15,234\none that's gotten the most\nattention, and I think\n\n151\n00:07:15,234 --> 00:07:17,904\ndeservedly so, for the kind\nof generosity that they have\n\n152\n00:07:17,904 --> 00:07:21,641\nalready demonstrated in\ntaking in so many migrants.\n\n153\n00:07:21,641 --> 00:07:25,311\nAnd it will be important for\nother countries to stand\n\n154\n00:07:25,311 --> 00:07:28,781\nwith Germany as they deal\nwith the situation.\n\n155\n00:07:29,849 --> 00:07:32,485\nThe Press: And then,\non Russia.\n\n156\n00:07:32,485 --> 00:07:34,921\nPresident Putin said today\nthat it's impossible to\n\n157\n00:07:34,921 --> 00:07:37,523\ndefeat the Islamic State\nwithout cooperating with the\n\n158\n00:07:37,523 --> 00:07:42,528\nregime in Damascus -- with\nsigns that Moscow is\n\n159\n00:07:42,528 --> 00:07:46,199\nplanning to set up an\nairbase in Syria.\n\n160\n00:07:46,199 --> 00:07:51,103\nYou mentioned yesterday that\nat the appropriate time\n\n161\n00:07:51,103 --> 00:07:54,240\nthere could be a\nPresidential conversation.\n\n162\n00:07:54,240 --> 00:07:56,776\nDo you have a sense of how\nimminent or not the\n\n163\n00:07:56,776 --> 00:08:01,080\nappropriate time might be\nfor a conversation?\n\n164\n00:08:01,080 --> 00:08:03,950\nMr. Earnest: When our team\nand, most importantly, when\n\n165\n00:08:03,950 --> 00:08:07,920\nthe President has determined\nthat it would advance our\n\n166\n00:08:07,920 --> 00:08:09,922\ninterests to have a\nconversation with President\n\n167\n00:08:09,922 --> 00:08:12,091\nPutin, he'll pick up the\nphone and try to set up\n\n168\n00:08:12,091 --> 00:08:13,092\nthat call.\n\n169\n00:08:13,092 --> 00:08:17,730\nThe President has made quite\nclear that the decision of\n\n170\n00:08:17,730 --> 00:08:21,133\nthe Russians to double down\non the leadership of Bashar\n\n171\n00:08:21,133 --> 00:08:23,336\nal-Assad is a losing bet.\n\n172\n00:08:23,336 --> 00:08:26,606\nAnd the reason for that is\nthat we have seen over the\n\n173\n00:08:26,606 --> 00:08:31,310\nyears that because of his\nfailed leadership and\n\n174\n00:08:31,310 --> 00:08:35,448\nbecause of his willingness\nto slaughter innocent people\n\n175\n00:08:35,448 --> 00:08:39,886\nusing the mechanics of that\ncountry's military, he's\n\n176\n00:08:39,886 --> 00:08:41,888\nlost the legitimacy to lead\nthat country.\n\n177\n00:08:41,888 --> 00:08:48,261\nAnd we have made clear that\nthe solution -- despite the\n\n178\n00:08:48,261 --> 00:08:52,131\ndecision of the Russians to\nbuild up their military --\n\n179\n00:08:52,131 --> 00:08:56,769\nthe solution in Syria\nrequires a diplomatic\n\n180\n00:08:56,769 --> 00:08:59,472\nstrategy.\n\n181\n00:09:00,172 --> 00:09:03,376\nAnd the United States has\nworked hard to support the\n\n182\n00:09:03,376 --> 00:09:07,380\nU.N.-led efforts to\nfacilitate a democratic\n\n183\n00:09:07,380 --> 00:09:09,782\npolitical transition inside\nof Syria.\n\n184\n00:09:09,782 --> 00:09:11,784\nAnd we've been pretty\nforthright, and I think it's\n\n185\n00:09:11,784 --> 00:09:13,786\npretty obvious to anybody\nwho's been paying attention,\n\n186\n00:09:13,786 --> 00:09:15,788\nthat those efforts haven't\ngained nearly as much\n\n187\n00:09:15,788 --> 00:09:17,390\ntraction as we would like.\n\n188\n00:09:17,390 --> 00:09:20,159\nSo there's significant work\nto be done in this area.\n\n189\n00:09:20,726 --> 00:09:22,828\nWhat we would prefer to see\nfrom the Russians is a more\n\n190\n00:09:22,828 --> 00:09:26,799\nconstructive engagement with\nthe 60-member coalition\n\n191\n00:09:26,799 --> 00:09:29,435\nthat's led by the United\nStates, that's focused on\n\n192\n00:09:29,435 --> 00:09:31,437\ndegrading and ultimately\ndestroying ISIL.\n\n193\n00:09:31,437 --> 00:09:34,774\nWe would welcome Russia's\nparticipation in that\n\n194\n00:09:34,774 --> 00:09:35,775\neffort.\n\n195\n00:09:35,775 --> 00:09:38,844\nAnd as we've said before, we\ncontinue to believe that\n\n196\n00:09:38,844 --> 00:09:43,182\ntheir efforts to support\nAssad and continue to offer\n\n197\n00:09:43,182 --> 00:09:46,585\nhim support are\ndestabilizing and\n\n198\n00:09:46,585 --> 00:09:47,586\ncounterproductive.\n\n199\n00:09:47,586 --> 00:09:50,189\nThe Press: Just finally,\non politics.\n\n200\n00:09:50,189 --> 00:09:54,727\nHow interested is the\nPresident in kind of the\n\n201\n00:09:54,727 --> 00:09:57,263\nnitty-gritty of the\nGOP race?\n\n202\n00:09:57,263 --> 00:10:02,301\nAnd is he planning to watch\nthe debate tomorrow night?\n\n203\n00:10:02,301 --> 00:10:05,972\nMr. Earnest: Well, I think\neven hearing some of the\n\n204\n00:10:05,972 --> 00:10:08,240\nPresident's comments at the\ntown hall meeting yesterday,\n\n205\n00:10:08,240 --> 00:10:12,011\nit's apparent that he is\nfollowing the race.\n\n206\n00:10:12,011 --> 00:10:18,317\nHe is at least a keenly\ninterested observer to that\n\n207\n00:10:18,317 --> 00:10:20,219\nprocess.\n\n208\n00:10:20,219 --> 00:10:22,455\nBut I would not anticipate\nthat the President will\n\n209\n00:10:22,455 --> 00:10:25,391\nwatch the debate tomorrow\nnight.\n\n210\n00:10:25,391 --> 00:10:28,127\nThe first one was held back\nin August, and to the\n\n211\n00:10:28,127 --> 00:10:31,263\ndisbelief of some, the\nPresident did not watch that\n\n212\n00:10:31,263 --> 00:10:32,264\ndebate.\n\n213\n00:10:32,264 --> 00:10:34,266\nI do not anticipate that\nhe'll watch tomorrow's\n\n214\n00:10:34,266 --> 00:10:35,267\neither.\n\n215\n00:10:35,267 --> 00:10:37,269\nBut I'm confident that he\nwill read the news coverage\n\n216\n00:10:37,269 --> 00:10:40,539\nand be aware of the\narguments that are made in\n\n217\n00:10:40,539 --> 00:10:41,540\nthat setting.\n\n218\n00:10:42,541 --> 00:10:43,542\nJeff.\n\n219\n00:10:43,542 --> 00:10:46,379\nThe Press: Josh, North Korea\nsaid today that its nuclear\n\n220\n00:10:46,379 --> 00:10:49,949\ncomplex was operating and it\nwas working to improve the\n\n221\n00:10:49,949 --> 00:10:53,519\nquality and quantity of its\nweapons so that they could\n\n222\n00:10:53,519 --> 00:10:55,654\nuse them against\nthe United States.\n\n223\n00:10:55,654 --> 00:10:58,524\nWhat is the White House's\nresponse to that?\n\n224\n00:10:58,524 --> 00:11:01,460\nMr. Earnest: Jeff, we're\naware of the reporting that\n\n225\n00:11:01,460 --> 00:11:04,697\nindicates the readjustment\nin operation of the nuclear\n\n226\n00:11:04,697 --> 00:11:08,167\nfacilities at Yongbyon,\nincluding the 5-megawatt\n\n227\n00:11:08,167 --> 00:11:11,070\nplutonium reactor and the\nuranium enrichment facility\n\n228\n00:11:11,070 --> 00:11:16,509\nat Yongbyon.\n\n229\n00:11:16,509 --> 00:11:20,780\nWe will repeat our call that\nNorth Korea should refrain\n\n230\n00:11:20,780 --> 00:11:23,149\nfrom irresponsible\nprovocations that aggravate\n\n231\n00:11:23,149 --> 00:11:26,352\nregional tensions, and\nshould focus instead on\n\n232\n00:11:26,352 --> 00:11:31,323\nfulfilling its international\nobligations and commitments.\n\n233\n00:11:31,357 --> 00:11:33,359\nThe position of the United\nStates -- and this is a\n\n234\n00:11:33,359 --> 00:11:35,828\nposition that is shared by\ncountries around the world,\n\n235\n00:11:35,828 --> 00:11:39,298\nincluding significant\nplayers in the region -- is\n\n236\n00:11:39,298 --> 00:11:42,835\nthat we will not accept\nNorth Korea as a nuclear\n\n237\n00:11:42,835 --> 00:11:45,237\nstate.\n\n238\n00:11:45,237 --> 00:11:47,540\nAnd that's why we urge North\nKorea to refrain from\n\n239\n00:11:47,540 --> 00:11:50,242\nactions and rhetoric that\nthreaten regional peace and\n\n240\n00:11:50,242 --> 00:11:53,112\nsecurity, and focus instead\non fulfilling its\n\n241\n00:11:53,112 --> 00:11:55,581\ninternational obligations\nand commitments.\n\n242\n00:11:55,581 --> 00:11:58,684\nAnd we will work with our\npartners in the context of\n\n243\n00:11:58,684 --> 00:12:04,123\nthe Six-Party talks to try\nto return North Korea to a\n\n244\n00:12:04,123 --> 00:12:09,995\nposture of fulfilling those\ncommitments that they've\n\n245\n00:12:09,995 --> 00:12:12,231\nmade in the context of those\nconversations.\n\n246\n00:12:12,231 --> 00:12:14,767\nThe Press: How seriously do\nyou take their threats?\n\n247\n00:12:14,767 --> 00:12:19,572\nMr. Earnest: Well, again, I\nthink that we're certainly\n\n248\n00:12:19,572 --> 00:12:24,577\naware of the actions that\nNorth Korea has taken, and I\n\n249\n00:12:26,579 --> 00:12:30,216\ndon't think I have a\nspecific reaction to those\n\n250\n00:12:30,216 --> 00:12:35,754\nactions, other than saying\nthat North Korea should\n\n251\n00:12:35,754 --> 00:12:38,791\nrefrain from irresponsible\nprovocations that serve only\n\n252\n00:12:38,791 --> 00:12:40,126\nto aggravate regional\ntensions.\n\n253\n00:12:40,126 --> 00:12:43,395\nThe Press: On a separate\ntopic, GE said today that\n\n254\n00:12:43,395 --> 00:12:44,930\nit's moving 500 U.S.\n\n255\n00:12:44,930 --> 00:12:48,934\npower turbine manufacturing\njobs to Europe because of an\n\n256\n00:12:48,934 --> 00:12:51,137\ninability to get\nEx-Im funding.\n\n257\n00:12:51,137 --> 00:12:56,041\nNow, I know that you'll see\nthis is a reason Republicans\n\n258\n00:12:56,041 --> 00:12:58,711\nshould allow the\nBank to continue.\n\n259\n00:12:58,711 --> 00:13:03,582\nI'm also curious to know if\nyou are disappointed in GE\n\n260\n00:13:03,582 --> 00:13:08,020\nfor doing this instead of\nwaiting to see how the\n\n261\n00:13:08,020 --> 00:13:09,822\npolitical process\nplays out.\n\n262\n00:13:09,822 --> 00:13:13,359\nMr. Earnest: Jeff, I won't\nhandicap individual business\n\n263\n00:13:13,359 --> 00:13:14,360\ndecisions.\n\n264\n00:13:14,360 --> 00:13:17,796\nObviously there are a range\nof factors that influence\n\n265\n00:13:17,796 --> 00:13:20,032\nhow those decisions\nare reached.\n\n266\n00:13:20,032 --> 00:13:24,904\nBut I do think it serves as\nan illustration that there\n\n267\n00:13:24,904 --> 00:13:27,573\nare real-world consequences\nfor congressional inaction.\n\n268\n00:13:27,573 --> 00:13:31,777\nAnd we have seen Republicans\ncounter decades of\n\n269\n00:13:31,777 --> 00:13:36,115\nbipartisan agreement and\nbipartisan support for the\n\n270\n00:13:36,115 --> 00:13:37,816\nExport-Import Bank.\n\n271\n00:13:37,816 --> 00:13:42,488\nAnd their failure to\nconfront this situation in a\n\n272\n00:13:42,488 --> 00:13:45,291\ntimely fashion and to allow\nsome of the funding for the\n\n273\n00:13:45,291 --> 00:13:51,830\nExport-Import Bank to lapse\nhas affected business\n\n274\n00:13:51,830 --> 00:13:54,500\ndecisions that are going to\nimpact jobs.\n\n275\n00:13:55,267 --> 00:13:59,171\nAnd we hear a lot about\nRepublicans complaining\n\n276\n00:13:59,171 --> 00:14:02,441\nabout supposedly job-killing\nregulations.\n\n277\n00:14:02,441 --> 00:14:05,511\nThe fact is it seems like,\nbased on what GE has\n\n278\n00:14:05,511 --> 00:14:09,148\nreported today, that\nRepublicans are killing\n\n279\n00:14:09,148 --> 00:14:10,149\nquite a few jobs\non their own.\n\n280\n00:14:10,149 --> 00:14:11,517\nJim.\n\n281\n00:14:11,517 --> 00:14:16,188\nThe Press: Josh, getting\nback to Syria, there are\n\n282\n00:14:16,188 --> 00:14:21,794\nreports that Russia is\nsending battle tanks to a\n\n283\n00:14:21,794 --> 00:14:25,764\nnew airbase in Syria.\n\n284\n00:14:25,764 --> 00:14:30,736\nI know you've said that the\nPresident will talk to\n\n285\n00:14:35,641 --> 00:14:40,646\nPresident Putin at the\nappropriate time, but does\n\n286\n00:14:43,549 --> 00:14:48,554\nthe United States view this\nas a provocation in that\n\n287\n00:14:53,425 --> 00:14:54,426\nregion?\n\n288\n00:14:54,426 --> 00:14:59,431\nAnd what do you make of\nwhat Putin is up to?\n\n289\n00:15:05,304 --> 00:15:10,309\nIs he banking on Assad to\ndefeat ISIS rather than the\n\n290\n00:15:16,181 --> 00:15:22,121\nSyrian opposition that\nyou've invested in?\n\n291\n00:15:22,121 --> 00:15:27,092\nMr. Earnest: Well, Jim, the\ndeployment of military\n\n292\n00:15:30,729 --> 00:15:33,032\nassets that you've cited is\nthe assessment of the\n\n293\n00:15:33,032 --> 00:15:36,268\nDepartment of Defense, so\nfor specific questions about\n\n294\n00:15:36,268 --> 00:15:37,303\nthat I'd refer you to them.\n\n295\n00:15:37,303 --> 00:15:39,305\nThe Press: Is that a\nprovocation, though?\n\n296\n00:15:39,305 --> 00:15:41,307\nMr. Earnest: Well, what it\nis, is it's -- we've made\n\n297\n00:15:41,307 --> 00:15:43,309\nclear that further support,\nmilitary or otherwise, for\n\n298\n00:15:43,309 --> 00:15:45,311\nthe Assad regime is\ndestabilizing and\n\n299\n00:15:45,311 --> 00:15:47,313\ncounterproductive,\nprincipally because Assad\n\n300\n00:15:47,313 --> 00:15:49,315\nhas lost the legitimacy to\nlead that country.\n\n301\n00:15:49,315 --> 00:15:51,317\nIt's also clear that Assad\nis actually losing\n\n302\n00:15:51,317 --> 00:15:53,319\nterritory, that the latest\nanalysis indicates that he\n\n303\n00:15:53,319 --> 00:15:55,321\ncontinues to govern at,\nleast nominally, territory\n\n304\n00:15:55,321 --> 00:15:56,322\nthat's shrinking in size.\n\n305\n00:15:56,322 --> 00:15:58,290\nAnd again, that is why the\nPresident indicated that\n\n306\n00:15:58,290 --> 00:16:00,526\ndoubling down on Assad -- or\nRussia's decision to double\n\n307\n00:16:00,526 --> 00:16:02,061\ndown on Assad is\na losing bet.\n\n308\n00:16:02,061 --> 00:16:04,496\nAnd what we would rather see\nis the Russians offer up\n\n309\n00:16:04,496 --> 00:16:06,498\nsome kind of constructive\ncooperation with the\n\n310\n00:16:06,498 --> 00:16:08,500\n60-member anti-ISIL\ncoalition that's built by\n\n311\n00:16:08,500 --> 00:16:10,502\nthe United States and\nfocused on degrading and\n\n312\n00:16:10,502 --> 00:16:11,503\nultimately destroying ISIL.\n\n313\n00:16:11,503 --> 00:16:13,505\nThe Russians indicate that\nthey share that goal, and\n\n314\n00:16:13,505 --> 00:16:15,541\nwe'd like to see them work\ncooperatively with the rest\n\n315\n00:16:15,541 --> 00:16:17,543\nof the international\ncommunity to advance it.\n\n316\n00:16:17,543 --> 00:16:19,545\nThe Press: And even though\nAssad has perpetrated some\n\n317\n00:16:19,545 --> 00:16:21,547\nungodly acts in Syria, in\nterms of a more effective\n\n318\n00:16:21,547 --> 00:16:23,549\nfighting force in terms of\ntaking on ISIS, is Putin\n\n319\n00:16:23,549 --> 00:16:25,551\ngoing with perhaps the more\neffective fighting force?\n\n320\n00:16:25,551 --> 00:16:27,553\nIs that a decision that you\nthink that he's making here?\n\n321\n00:16:27,553 --> 00:16:29,521\nMr. Earnest: A close look at\nthe facts on the ground does\n\n322\n00:16:29,521 --> 00:16:31,523\nnot substantiate the claim\nthat the Assad fighting\n\n323\n00:16:31,523 --> 00:16:33,525\nforce is effectively\nadvancing the interests of\n\n324\n00:16:33,525 --> 00:16:34,526\nPresident Assad.\n\n325\n00:16:34,526 --> 00:16:36,528\nAgain, the amount of\nterritory that they're\n\n326\n00:16:36,528 --> 00:16:37,529\ndefending is shrinking.\n\n327\n00:16:37,529 --> 00:16:40,933\nAnd there are a variety of\nreasons for that, including\n\n328\n00:16:40,933 --> 00:16:44,403\nthe willingness of the Assad\nregime to engage in\n\n329\n00:16:44,403 --> 00:16:47,106\nindiscriminate acts of\nviolence against the Syrian\n\n330\n00:16:47,106 --> 00:16:48,107\npeople.\n\n331\n00:16:48,240 --> 00:16:54,046\nSo there are a lot of -- I'm\nconfident there are a lot of\n\n332\n00:16:54,046 --> 00:16:56,982\nfactors that go into\nPresident Putin's assessment\n\n333\n00:16:56,982 --> 00:16:58,617\nof the situation.\n\n334\n00:16:58,617 --> 00:17:01,820\nBut I think what most\nobservers have acknowledged\n\n335\n00:17:01,820 --> 00:17:08,394\nis that President Assad's\ngrip on power is weakening,\n\n336\n00:17:08,394 --> 00:17:10,629\nand for many of the reasons\nthat we're --\n\n337\n00:17:10,629 --> 00:17:12,631\nThe Press: So you're saying\n-- that's the tactical\n\n338\n00:17:12,631 --> 00:17:14,633\ndecision that President\nPutin is making you're\n\n339\n00:17:14,633 --> 00:17:15,634\nsaying it's the wrong one?\n\n340\n00:17:15,634 --> 00:17:17,636\nMr. Earnest: Well, I think\nhe's making a strategic\n\n341\n00:17:17,636 --> 00:17:19,638\ndecision to double down on\nhis support for the Assad\n\n342\n00:17:19,638 --> 00:17:21,640\nregime, and I think that's a\nlosing bet.\n\n343\n00:17:21,640 --> 00:17:22,641\nThe Press: Okay.\n\n344\n00:17:22,641 --> 00:17:24,610\nAnd on China, The Washington\nPost is reporting that the\n\n345\n00:17:24,610 --> 00:17:26,612\nadministration is holding\noff on sanctions against\n\n346\n00:17:26,612 --> 00:17:30,482\nChinese entities prior to\nPresident Xi's visit here.\n\n347\n00:17:30,482 --> 00:17:32,050\nIs that accurate?\n\n348\n00:17:32,050 --> 00:17:37,289\nAnd I guess it's a difficult\nquestion to answer because\n\n349\n00:17:37,289 --> 00:17:41,994\nthe administration has still\nnot said publicly that China\n\n350\n00:17:41,994 --> 00:17:47,733\nwas behind the OPM hack, and\nI guess I'm just curious,\n\n351\n00:17:47,733 --> 00:17:51,403\nwhat's the holdup with\nholding the Chinese\n\n352\n00:17:51,403 --> 00:17:54,173\naccountable for their\nactions in cyber security?\n\n353\n00:17:54,173 --> 00:17:58,177\nMr. Earnest: Jim, as I've\nindicated before, we are not\n\n354\n00:17:58,177 --> 00:18:01,680\nlikely to spend time talking\nabout our plan to implement\n\n355\n00:18:01,680 --> 00:18:04,450\nsanctions prior to their\nimplementation.\n\n356\n00:18:04,450 --> 00:18:07,753\nAnd the reason for that is\nwe do not want to give those\n\n357\n00:18:07,753 --> 00:18:11,223\nwho may be the target of\nthose sanctions the\n\n358\n00:18:11,223 --> 00:18:14,560\nopportunity to plan -- or\ncarry out a strategy to\n\n359\n00:18:14,560 --> 00:18:17,029\nevade those sanctions before\nthey're even implemented.\n\n360\n00:18:17,029 --> 00:18:19,031\nSo that's why we have\nwithheld comment on specific\n\n361\n00:18:19,031 --> 00:18:21,033\nreports about our plans to\nimplement sanctions.\n\n362\n00:18:21,033 --> 00:18:23,035\nWhat I will say is that the\nonly reason we're having\n\n363\n00:18:23,035 --> 00:18:28,040\nthis discussion is because\nearlier this year the\n\n364\n00:18:30,375 --> 00:18:35,314\nPresident initiated a policy\nchange that delegated\n\n365\n00:18:35,314 --> 00:18:40,052\nauthority to the Secretary\nof the Treasury to impose\n\n366\n00:18:40,052 --> 00:18:45,057\neconomic sanctions against\nentities that engage in bad\n\n367\n00:18:49,428 --> 00:18:54,066\nbehavior in cyberspace or\nbenefit from that behavior.\n\n368\n00:18:54,066 --> 00:19:00,072\nAnd I think what we know\nabout the tool of economic\n\n369\n00:19:00,072 --> 00:19:03,575\nsanctions is that it can\nserve as a pretty effective\n\n370\n00:19:03,575 --> 00:19:06,879\ndeterrent, even if it hasn't\nalready been implemented;\n\n371\n00:19:06,879 --> 00:19:13,118\nthat merely having this\nresponse tool in our arsenal\n\n372\n00:19:13,118 --> 00:19:15,120\ncan advance the interests of\nthe United States.\n\n373\n00:19:16,054 --> 00:19:20,259\nSo we'll obviously continue\nto monitor this situation,\n\n374\n00:19:20,259 --> 00:19:23,862\nand I think there are a\nnumber of steps that the\n\n375\n00:19:23,862 --> 00:19:30,202\nUnited States has taken,\nincluding engaging directly\n\n376\n00:19:30,202 --> 00:19:33,205\nbetween the two Presidents,\nfrom President Obama to his\n\n377\n00:19:33,205 --> 00:19:35,908\ncounterpart, raising\nsignificant concerns about\n\n378\n00:19:35,908 --> 00:19:38,110\nChina's activity in\ncyberspace.\n\n379\n00:19:39,344 --> 00:19:42,281\nYou'll recall last year that\nfive Chinese military\n\n380\n00:19:42,281 --> 00:19:44,349\nofficials were indicted by\nthe United States Department\n\n381\n00:19:44,349 --> 00:19:48,921\nof Justice for their actions\nin cyberspace.\n\n382\n00:19:48,921 --> 00:19:50,923\nSo I think it's quite clear\nto the public that this is\n\n383\n00:19:50,923 --> 00:19:52,891\nan issue that the United\nStates and the Obama\n\n384\n00:19:52,891 --> 00:19:54,893\nadministration take\nseriously, and it's quite\n\n385\n00:19:54,893 --> 00:19:56,895\nclear to the Chinese\ngovernment that this is an\n\n386\n00:19:56,895 --> 00:19:58,897\nissue that we take\nseriously, as evidenced by\n\n387\n00:19:58,897 --> 00:20:01,033\nthe decision of the Chinese\nPresident to send Secretary\n\n388\n00:20:01,033 --> 00:20:07,339\nMeng to the United States to\nmeet with a range of U.S.\n\n389\n00:20:07,339 --> 00:20:09,341\nofficials in advance of his\nvisit.\n\n390\n00:20:09,341 --> 00:20:11,310\nThe Press: But just this\nmorning your administration\n\n391\n00:20:11,310 --> 00:20:13,312\nannounced China's\ncooperation and some\n\n392\n00:20:13,312 --> 00:20:16,448\nadvancements that they've\nmade with respect to climate\n\n393\n00:20:16,448 --> 00:20:20,018\nchange and acting on the\nclimate pact that the\n\n394\n00:20:20,018 --> 00:20:21,620\nPresident reached\nlast year.\n\n395\n00:20:21,620 --> 00:20:24,890\nIs it difficult to issue\nsanctions or prosecute\n\n396\n00:20:24,890 --> 00:20:29,227\nChinese entities for these\nacts when you've got these\n\n397\n00:20:29,227 --> 00:20:31,196\nother big-ticket\nitems at stake?\n\n398\n00:20:31,196 --> 00:20:33,465\nMr. Earnest: Well, again, I\ndon't want to get --\n\n399\n00:20:33,465 --> 00:20:34,466\nThe Press: It's complicated.\n\n400\n00:20:34,466 --> 00:20:36,468\nMr. Earnest: Yes, well, I\nthink we've acknowledged\n\n401\n00:20:36,468 --> 00:20:37,469\nthat complication.\n\n402\n00:20:37,469 --> 00:20:39,471\nBut the fact is, I think\nit's pretty easily described\n\n403\n00:20:39,471 --> 00:20:41,473\nthat there are some areas\nwhere we're able to\n\n404\n00:20:41,473 --> 00:20:43,642\ncooperate effectively with\nthe Chinese to advance the\n\n405\n00:20:43,642 --> 00:20:46,044\ninterests of the citizens of\nboth of our countries.\n\n406\n00:20:46,044 --> 00:20:48,280\nAnd whether it's the climate\nannouncement that you've\n\n407\n00:20:48,280 --> 00:20:53,852\njust cited or trying to\nbuild international\n\n408\n00:20:53,852 --> 00:20:55,821\nconsensus around confronting\nIran of their nuclear\n\n409\n00:20:55,821 --> 00:20:57,823\nprogram -- you'll recall\nthat China was a\n\n410\n00:20:57,823 --> 00:21:01,793\nconstructive partner in the\nP5+1 efforts; we even have\n\n411\n00:21:01,793 --> 00:21:05,063\nsome effective cooperation\nwith China when it comes to\n\n412\n00:21:05,063 --> 00:21:07,566\ncontaining the threat that\nis posed by North Korea and\n\n413\n00:21:07,566 --> 00:21:10,369\ntrying to de-nuclearize the\nKorean Peninsula.\n\n414\n00:21:10,936 --> 00:21:12,938\nSo there are a variety of\nareas where we can work\n\n415\n00:21:12,938 --> 00:21:14,940\neffectively with the Chinese\nto advance the interests of\n\n416\n00:21:14,940 --> 00:21:16,942\nthe American people but also\nthe Chinese people.\n\n417\n00:21:16,942 --> 00:21:20,012\nBut that certainly in no way\ndiminishes the significance\n\n418\n00:21:20,012 --> 00:21:22,614\nof the concerns that we do\nhave with some of China's\n\n419\n00:21:22,614 --> 00:21:23,615\npolicy decisions.\n\n420\n00:21:23,615 --> 00:21:28,120\nAnd whether that is their\nactivity in cyberspace or\n\n421\n00:21:28,120 --> 00:21:31,523\nthe concerns that we have\nabout their lack of respect\n\n422\n00:21:31,523 --> 00:21:32,524\nfor basic human rights.\n\n423\n00:21:32,524 --> 00:21:34,526\nThe Press: And last thing --\nI've gone on too long, but\n\n424\n00:21:34,526 --> 00:21:36,528\nis it the President's view\nthat Hillary --\n\n425\n00:21:36,528 --> 00:21:38,530\nMr. Earnest: It's possible\nthat I've gone on too long.\n\n426\n00:21:38,530 --> 00:21:39,531\n(laughter)\n\n427\n00:21:39,531 --> 00:21:41,533\nThe Press: Is it the\nPresident's view that\n\n428\n00:21:41,533 --> 00:21:43,535\nHillary Clinton is\nstruggling right now?\n\n429\n00:21:43,535 --> 00:21:45,537\nMr. Earnest: No, that's not\nthe President's view.\n\n430\n00:21:45,537 --> 00:21:51,610\nAs I've conveyed to you,\nit's unwise to draw\n\n431\n00:21:51,610 --> 00:21:53,612\nsignificant conclusions\nabout the outcome of an\n\n432\n00:21:53,612 --> 00:21:57,849\nelection 15 months before\nit's scheduled to be held.\n\n433\n00:21:57,849 --> 00:21:58,850\nCheryl.\n\n434\n00:21:58,850 --> 00:22:01,987\nThe Press: Thanks, Josh, and\nI know you've said that the\n\n435\n00:22:01,987 --> 00:22:04,856\nPresident is going to be\ntalking about budget and\n\n436\n00:22:04,856 --> 00:22:07,759\nspending bills tomorrow, but\nthere are some Democrats on\n\n437\n00:22:07,759 --> 00:22:11,930\nCapitol Hill who say that\nthe President should not\n\n438\n00:22:11,930 --> 00:22:15,634\nsign even a short-term CR\nunless budget negotiations\n\n439\n00:22:15,634 --> 00:22:16,635\nactually start.\n\n440\n00:22:16,635 --> 00:22:20,739\nWhat is the President's view\non when negotiations really\n\n441\n00:22:20,739 --> 00:22:22,107\nneed to start?\n\n442\n00:22:22,107 --> 00:22:24,910\nMr. Earnest: Well, Cheryl,\nthe President's view is\n\n443\n00:22:24,910 --> 00:22:30,115\nthat, as I described at some\nlength before this briefing\n\n444\n00:22:30,115 --> 00:22:32,517\nstarted, our economy has\nmade a lot of important\n\n445\n00:22:32,517 --> 00:22:35,487\nprogress over the last seven\nyears, and that's because\n\n446\n00:22:35,487 --> 00:22:37,856\nprimarily of the grit and\ndetermination of the\n\n447\n00:22:37,856 --> 00:22:40,225\nAmerican work force and\nAmerican business leaders\n\n448\n00:22:40,225 --> 00:22:41,226\nand entrepreneurs.\n\n449\n00:22:41,226 --> 00:22:46,932\nIt's our private sector that\nhas led this recovery, and\n\n450\n00:22:46,932 --> 00:22:49,334\nthe American people can feel\ngood about the momentum that\n\n451\n00:22:49,334 --> 00:22:50,335\nwe have built up.\n\n452\n00:22:51,269 --> 00:22:53,605\nAt the same time, the last\nthing that this momentum\n\n453\n00:22:53,605 --> 00:22:58,610\nneeds is to be undermined by\ndysfunction in the United\n\n454\n00:23:00,846 --> 00:23:02,714\nStates Congress.\n\n455\n00:23:02,714 --> 00:23:06,685\nAnd we've seen that once\nbefore, as recently as two\n\n456\n00:23:06,685 --> 00:23:08,854\nyears ago, when Republicans\nled the effort to shut down\n\n457\n00:23:08,854 --> 00:23:12,257\nthe government in protest\nover the Affordable Care\n\n458\n00:23:12,257 --> 00:23:13,258\nAct.\n\n459\n00:23:13,258 --> 00:23:15,260\nIt would be a shame for\nRepublicans to marshal a\n\n460\n00:23:15,260 --> 00:23:17,462\nsimilar effort for any\nreason.\n\n461\n00:23:17,462 --> 00:23:20,699\nThe fact is the Congress has\na basic responsibility to\n\n462\n00:23:20,699 --> 00:23:23,068\npass a budget on an annual\nbasis to fund the government\n\n463\n00:23:23,068 --> 00:23:24,503\nat appropriate levels.\n\n464\n00:23:24,503 --> 00:23:28,740\nAnd that's why the\nadministration has\n\n465\n00:23:28,740 --> 00:23:34,479\nregularly, even daily in the\ncontext of these briefings,\n\n466\n00:23:34,479 --> 00:23:37,482\nsuggested that Republican\nleaders in Congress should\n\n467\n00:23:37,482 --> 00:23:39,885\naccept the offer from\nDemocrats in Congress to\n\n468\n00:23:39,885 --> 00:23:43,722\nnegotiate a bipartisan\nbudget agreement that would\n\n469\n00:23:43,722 --> 00:23:46,625\nboth avoid a government\nshutdown but also make sure\n\n470\n00:23:46,625 --> 00:23:49,094\nthat our nation's priorities\nwhen it comes to both our\n\n471\n00:23:49,094 --> 00:23:51,429\neconomy and our national\nsecurity are adequately\n\n472\n00:23:51,429 --> 00:23:52,430\nfunded.\n\n473\n00:23:52,430 --> 00:23:55,934\nThe Press: Okay, but we're\nbarely two weeks till the\n\n474\n00:23:55,934 --> 00:23:58,069\nend of the fiscal year.\n\n475\n00:23:58,069 --> 00:24:02,841\nWhat day would you say we\nneed to start before it's\n\n476\n00:24:02,841 --> 00:24:05,010\njust dragged on too long?\n\n477\n00:24:05,010 --> 00:24:07,846\nMr. Earnest: Well, I think\nit already has dragged on\n\n478\n00:24:07,846 --> 00:24:08,847\ntoo long.\n\n479\n00:24:08,847 --> 00:24:11,583\nWe have been suggesting that\nthese negotiations take\n\n480\n00:24:11,583 --> 00:24:14,019\nplace for months now.\n\n481\n00:24:14,019 --> 00:24:17,589\nLast time, back in 2013, the\nlast time Republicans shut\n\n482\n00:24:17,589 --> 00:24:20,458\ndown the government, we\nactually had to go through\n\n483\n00:24:20,458 --> 00:24:23,662\ntwo or two and a half weeks\nof a shutdown before\n\n484\n00:24:23,662 --> 00:24:26,164\nRepublicans engaged in\nserious negotiations with\n\n485\n00:24:26,164 --> 00:24:27,566\nDemocrats.\n\n486\n00:24:27,566 --> 00:24:29,668\nWe had hoped that\nRepublicans would be able to\n\n487\n00:24:29,668 --> 00:24:32,237\nbe willing to negotiate with\nDemocrats prior to a\n\n488\n00:24:32,237 --> 00:24:34,472\ngovernment shutdown, as\nopposed to after a\n\n489\n00:24:34,472 --> 00:24:35,941\ngovernment shutdown.\n\n490\n00:24:35,941 --> 00:24:36,942\nBut we'll have to see.\n\n491\n00:24:36,942 --> 00:24:38,944\nThat will ultimately be the\nresponsibility of Republican\n\n492\n00:24:38,944 --> 00:24:42,280\nleaders in Congress to\ndecide whether or not they\n\n493\n00:24:42,280 --> 00:24:44,282\ncan demonstrate to the\nAmerican people that they're\n\n494\n00:24:44,282 --> 00:24:48,887\ncapable of leading the\nCongress.\n\n495\n00:24:48,887 --> 00:24:51,289\nAnd prompting a second\ngovernment shutdown in two\n\n496\n00:24:51,289 --> 00:24:54,526\nyears I think is going to\nraise some significant\n\n497\n00:24:54,526 --> 00:24:57,062\ndoubts about their ability\nto do exactly that.\n\n498\n00:24:57,062 --> 00:24:58,029\nJustin.\n\n499\n00:24:58,029 --> 00:25:01,132\nThe Press: First I wanted to\nlook back on the answer that\n\n500\n00:25:01,132 --> 00:25:02,500\nyou gave to Jim.\n\n501\n00:25:02,500 --> 00:25:06,271\nIt sounded like you snuck a\nnew line about deterrence\n\n502\n00:25:06,271 --> 00:25:07,305\nand sanctions in there.\n\n503\n00:25:07,305 --> 00:25:11,142\nAnd what I'm curious about\nis in the context of the\n\n504\n00:25:11,142 --> 00:25:14,045\ntalks that happened with\nAmbassador Rice and other\n\n505\n00:25:14,045 --> 00:25:16,948\nofficials over the weekend\n-- if the U.S.\n\n506\n00:25:16,948 --> 00:25:20,218\ngot any assurances from\nChina either on the activity\n\n507\n00:25:20,218 --> 00:25:23,488\nin cyberspace that has\nraised some concern here, or\n\n508\n00:25:23,488 --> 00:25:26,358\nthe viability of an\nagreement between the U.S.\n\n509\n00:25:26,358 --> 00:25:29,261\nand China on cyber\nactivities, on data theft,\n\n510\n00:25:29,261 --> 00:25:32,898\non kind of these -- was\nthere some sort of\n\n511\n00:25:32,898 --> 00:25:35,800\nbreakthrough or significant\nprogress made that might be\n\n512\n00:25:35,800 --> 00:25:37,235\nsolidified in the talks?\n\n513\n00:25:37,235 --> 00:25:40,205\nMr. Earnest: Well, I don't\nhave a more detailed readout\n\n514\n00:25:40,205 --> 00:25:42,207\nof those conversations to\nshare with you.\n\n515\n00:25:42,207 --> 00:25:46,444\nI think we made clear that\nthe concerns that we have\n\n516\n00:25:46,444 --> 00:25:50,181\nabout China's behavior in\ncyberspace were discussed\n\n517\n00:25:50,181 --> 00:25:52,851\nbluntly by those American\nofficials who participated\n\n518\n00:25:52,851 --> 00:25:54,586\nin those conversations.\n\n519\n00:25:54,586 --> 00:25:57,722\nAnd I would anticipate that\nwhen President Obama next\n\n520\n00:25:57,722 --> 00:26:01,326\nhas the opportunity to have\na conversation with his\n\n521\n00:26:01,326 --> 00:26:04,195\ncounterpart that the\nPresident will be just as\n\n522\n00:26:04,195 --> 00:26:09,267\ndirect in conveying his\nconcerns about the way that\n\n523\n00:26:09,267 --> 00:26:12,570\nChina has pursued some of\nthat activity in cyberspace.\n\n524\n00:26:12,570 --> 00:26:14,572\nIt will not be the first\ntime the President has\n\n525\n00:26:14,572 --> 00:26:15,540\nraised those concerns.\n\n526\n00:26:15,540 --> 00:26:17,542\nIn fact, the President has\nraised those concerns in\n\n527\n00:26:17,542 --> 00:26:19,544\neach of the previous\nmeetings that he's had with\n\n528\n00:26:19,544 --> 00:26:22,380\nPresident Xi.\n\n529\n00:26:22,380 --> 00:26:25,984\nThe reference that I made to\nthe value of deterrence is\n\n530\n00:26:25,984 --> 00:26:27,986\nsomething that I am\ndiscussing for the first\n\n531\n00:26:27,986 --> 00:26:31,089\ntime in this context, but as\nsomeone pointed out to me\n\n532\n00:26:31,089 --> 00:26:35,093\nearlier today, we've used\neconomic sanctions\n\n533\n00:26:35,093 --> 00:26:38,930\neffectively in a variety of\nother areas, as recently in\n\n534\n00:26:38,930 --> 00:26:42,667\nconfronting Iran over their\nnuclear program.\n\n535\n00:26:42,667 --> 00:26:47,105\nAnd we did discuss how the\nthreat of additional\n\n536\n00:26:47,105 --> 00:26:53,411\nsanctions did serve as a\nuseful way to apply pressure\n\n537\n00:26:53,411 --> 00:26:57,315\nto Iran to further isolate\nthem and to advance our\n\n538\n00:26:57,315 --> 00:26:58,350\ninterests.\n\n539\n00:26:58,350 --> 00:27:04,189\nSo I don't mean to introduce\na new factor here, but\n\n540\n00:27:04,189 --> 00:27:06,458\nrather to sort of draw a\nconnection about the\n\n541\n00:27:06,458 --> 00:27:09,961\nphilosophy that we'd pursue\nwhen considering the\n\n542\n00:27:09,961 --> 00:27:12,063\nimplementation of additional\nsanctions to advance the\n\n543\n00:27:12,063 --> 00:27:13,098\ninterests of the United\nStates.\n\n544\n00:27:13,098 --> 00:27:15,400\nThe Press: I wanted to ask\nyou about a pair of phone\n\n545\n00:27:15,400 --> 00:27:17,936\ncalls the Vice President had\nwith some foreign leaders.\n\n546\n00:27:17,936 --> 00:27:21,840\nThe first one is, yesterday,\nhe said in a conversation\n\n547\n00:27:21,840 --> 00:27:24,542\nwith his counterpart in\nMontenegro that the U.S.\n\n548\n00:27:24,542 --> 00:27:27,612\nwas ready to back their\ninvitation to NATO.\n\n549\n00:27:27,612 --> 00:27:30,749\nI'm wondering, obviously,\nthis is probably going to\n\n550\n00:27:30,749 --> 00:27:35,020\ndraw some concern in Moscow,\nand if you could talk about\n\n551\n00:27:35,020 --> 00:27:38,156\nthe intentionality of making\nthis announcement in the\n\n552\n00:27:38,156 --> 00:27:41,659\ncontext of what Russia has\nbeen doing in Syria?\n\n553\n00:27:41,659 --> 00:27:43,661\nMr. Earnest: my\nunderstanding is that there\n\n554\n00:27:43,661 --> 00:27:47,665\nhas been a policy process\nbehind that decision that's\n\n555\n00:27:47,665 --> 00:27:50,201\nbeen ongoing for quite some\ntime.\n\n556\n00:27:50,201 --> 00:27:54,773\nAnd the United States has\ntalked -- the President has\n\n557\n00:27:54,773 --> 00:27:57,742\ntalked on a number of\noccasions about how central\n\n558\n00:27:57,742 --> 00:28:01,112\nthe NATO alliance is to not\njust the national security\n\n559\n00:28:01,112 --> 00:28:04,249\nof the United States but to\nbroader stability in the\n\n560\n00:28:04,249 --> 00:28:05,250\nNorth Atlantic region.\n\n561\n00:28:05,250 --> 00:28:11,489\nAnd the United States has\nenjoyed a lot of security\n\n562\n00:28:11,489 --> 00:28:13,491\ncooperation from Montenegro\nin the past, and that sort\n\n563\n00:28:13,491 --> 00:28:15,493\nof explains the lead-up to\nthis policy decision that\n\n564\n00:28:15,493 --> 00:28:17,495\nthe Montenegrin leader was\ninformed of yesterday by the\n\n565\n00:28:17,495 --> 00:28:18,496\nVice President.\n\n566\n00:28:18,496 --> 00:28:23,501\nThe Press: On a separate\ncall today the King of\n\n567\n00:28:30,442 --> 00:28:34,779\nJordan's office said that he\nurged the Vice President to\n\n568\n00:28:34,779 --> 00:28:36,981\nhave the administration\nspeak more bluntly about\n\n569\n00:28:36,981 --> 00:28:39,150\nyour stance on Israeli\npolice action against\n\n570\n00:28:39,150 --> 00:28:41,953\nPalestinian protestors at\nthe Temple Mount, and so I'm\n\n571\n00:28:41,953 --> 00:28:45,090\nwondering if you could talk\nabout where you guys are\n\n572\n00:28:45,090 --> 00:28:47,892\nkind of on that situation as\nit's been developing.\n\n573\n00:28:47,892 --> 00:28:50,095\nMr. Earnest: Well, Justin,\nthe United States remains\n\n574\n00:28:50,095 --> 00:28:52,864\ndeeply concerned by the\nrecent violence and\n\n575\n00:28:52,864 --> 00:28:54,866\nescalating tensions\nsurrounding Haram al-Sharif,\n\n576\n00:28:54,866 --> 00:28:57,969\nor the Temple Mount, as\nit's also known.\n\n577\n00:28:57,969 --> 00:29:00,972\nThe United States, as we\nroutinely do, strongly\n\n578\n00:29:00,972 --> 00:29:04,275\ncondemn all acts of\nviolence, particularly in\n\n579\n00:29:04,275 --> 00:29:08,913\nthat location that's so\nsacred to many, many people.\n\n580\n00:29:08,913 --> 00:29:11,483\nIt is absolutely critical\nthat all sides exercise\n\n581\n00:29:11,483 --> 00:29:15,420\nrestraint, refrain from\nprovocative actions and\n\n582\n00:29:15,420 --> 00:29:19,023\nrhetoric, and preserve\nunchanged the historic\n\n583\n00:29:19,023 --> 00:29:22,927\nstatus quo on the Haram\nal-Sharif Temple Mount, both\n\n584\n00:29:22,927 --> 00:29:24,996\nin word and in practice.\n\n585\n00:29:24,996 --> 00:29:26,998\nAnd that has been the\nlong-held position of the\n\n586\n00:29:26,998 --> 00:29:27,999\nUnited States.\n\n587\n00:29:27,999 --> 00:29:30,001\nIt's a position that has\nbeen conveyed to all parties\n\n588\n00:29:30,001 --> 00:29:31,002\nin this ongoing disturbance.\n\n589\n00:29:31,002 --> 00:29:33,004\nAnd that is the message that\nthe Vice President conveyed\n\n590\n00:29:33,004 --> 00:29:38,009\nto King Abdullah, as well.\n\n591\n00:29:43,648 --> 00:29:46,518\nThe Press: And one last\npotential fool's errand, but\n\n592\n00:29:46,518 --> 00:29:50,155\nSenator Hoevan, having\nstruck out on his summertime\n\n593\n00:29:50,155 --> 00:29:52,357\nprediction on the Keystone\npipeline, has said now that\n\n594\n00:29:52,357 --> 00:29:53,358\nthe administration is --\n\n595\n00:29:53,358 --> 00:29:55,360\nMr. Earnest: He's not the\nonly one.\n\n596\n00:29:55,360 --> 00:29:57,362\nHe can take some solace in\nthat.\n\n597\n00:29:57,362 --> 00:29:59,364\nThe Press: -- that the\nadministration is waiting\n\n598\n00:29:59,364 --> 00:30:01,332\nuntil after the\nCanadian elections.\n\n599\n00:30:01,332 --> 00:30:03,334\nI know this has come up\nbefore, but I'm wondering if\n\n600\n00:30:03,334 --> 00:30:04,335\nyou had anything\nfresh on that.\n\n601\n00:30:04,335 --> 00:30:06,337\nMr. Earnest: I don't have\nanything new in terms of\n\n602\n00:30:06,337 --> 00:30:08,339\ntiming, but the State\nDepartment may so you can\n\n603\n00:30:08,339 --> 00:30:09,340\ncheck with them.\n\n604\n00:30:09,340 --> 00:30:10,341\nJon.\n\n605\n00:30:10,341 --> 00:30:12,343\nThe Press: Just a couple of\nfollow-ups, one, on the\n\n606\n00:30:12,343 --> 00:30:15,847\nquestion of the\nshort-term CR.\n\n607\n00:30:15,847 --> 00:30:20,285\nIs the President willing to\nsign a short-term funding to\n\n608\n00:30:20,285 --> 00:30:24,389\nallow negotiations to go\nforward that would extend\n\n609\n00:30:24,389 --> 00:30:26,457\ncurrent government\nfunding levels?\n\n610\n00:30:26,457 --> 00:30:29,627\nMr. Earnest: Well, Jon, I\ndon't want to speculate\n\n611\n00:30:29,627 --> 00:30:33,064\nright now on what Congress\nmay eventually do.\n\n612\n00:30:33,064 --> 00:30:36,701\nWe have made clear what our\npriorities are, which are to\n\n613\n00:30:36,701 --> 00:30:39,504\nprevent a government\nshutdown, to make sure that\n\n614\n00:30:39,504 --> 00:30:41,606\nour national security and\neconomic priorities are\n\n615\n00:30:41,606 --> 00:30:46,144\nadequately funded, and to\nmake sure that we don't lock\n\n616\n00:30:46,144 --> 00:30:51,482\nin over the long term the\nsequester budget levels that\n\n617\n00:30:51,482 --> 00:30:55,587\nright now inadequately fund\nour national security and\n\n618\n00:30:55,587 --> 00:30:56,588\neconomic priorities.\n\n619\n00:30:56,588 --> 00:30:59,123\nThe Press: But you don't\nrule out locking that in for\n\n620\n00:30:59,123 --> 00:31:00,124\na short term?\n\n621\n00:31:00,124 --> 00:31:02,327\nMr. Earnest: I don't have\nanything to -- well, I guess\n\n622\n00:31:02,327 --> 00:31:06,831\nthe -- I think we would\nperceive an internal\n\n623\n00:31:06,831 --> 00:31:10,168\ncontradiction between the\nwords \"short term\" and \"lock\n\n624\n00:31:10,168 --> 00:31:11,169\nin.\"\n\n625\n00:31:11,169 --> 00:31:12,170\nThe Press: Okay.\n\n626\n00:31:12,170 --> 00:31:16,140\nAnd then a follow-up on\nRussia's actions in Syria.\n\n627\n00:31:16,140 --> 00:31:18,743\nU.S.\n\n628\n00:31:18,743 --> 00:31:20,878\npolicy is still that Assad\nneeds to go, right?\n\n629\n00:31:20,878 --> 00:31:22,880\nMr. Earnest: That is the\npolicy of the United States,\n\n630\n00:31:22,880 --> 00:31:23,881\nyes.\n\n631\n00:31:23,881 --> 00:31:25,883\nThe Press: Also to degrade\nand destroy ISIL.\n\n632\n00:31:25,883 --> 00:31:26,884\nMr. Earnest: That's correct.\n\n633\n00:31:26,884 --> 00:31:28,886\nThe Press: What is the\nhigher priority?\n\n634\n00:31:28,886 --> 00:31:34,292\nMr. Earnest: Well, I think\nboth of these are\n\n635\n00:31:34,292 --> 00:31:37,195\npriorities, principally\nbecause the reason that ISIL\n\n636\n00:31:37,195 --> 00:31:40,531\nhas been able to grow both\nin terms of the area they\n\n637\n00:31:40,531 --> 00:31:46,838\ncontrol and in their stature\nin the region is a direct\n\n638\n00:31:46,838 --> 00:31:48,840\nresult of the failed\nleadership of Bashar\n\n639\n00:31:48,840 --> 00:31:49,841\nal-Assad.\n\n640\n00:31:49,841 --> 00:31:54,812\nSo you have identified two\npolicies of the United\n\n641\n00:31:54,812 --> 00:31:59,817\nStates government, but they\nare not disconnected; that\n\n642\n00:32:02,487 --> 00:32:04,489\none is -- the failed\nleadership of President\n\n643\n00:32:04,489 --> 00:32:06,491\nAssad has had an impact and\nhas contributed\n\n644\n00:32:06,491 --> 00:32:08,493\nsignificantly to the growth\nof ISIL.\n\n645\n00:32:08,493 --> 00:32:10,495\nSo those two things are\nrelated.\n\n646\n00:32:10,495 --> 00:32:15,500\nThe Press: So I guess the\nsame answer if I ask you\n\n647\n00:32:17,568 --> 00:32:22,140\nwhat's the greater threat to\nthe United States, Assad\n\n648\n00:32:22,140 --> 00:32:27,145\ncontinuing to be in power in\nparts of Syria he controls,\n\n649\n00:32:29,914 --> 00:32:31,316\nor ISIL?\n\n650\n00:32:31,316 --> 00:32:36,254\nMr. Earnest: Obviously, the\nrisk to U.S.\n\n651\n00:32:36,254 --> 00:32:41,125\ninterests is different, but\nthe fact is resolving both\n\n652\n00:32:41,125 --> 00:32:45,263\nof these concerns would\nadvance our interests.\n\n653\n00:32:45,263 --> 00:32:49,200\nThe Press: And what do you\nassess, what does the\n\n654\n00:32:49,200 --> 00:32:53,771\nadministration assess is\nRussia's goal here?\n\n655\n00:32:53,771 --> 00:32:59,310\nAre they -- publicly they\nsay this is about fighting\n\n656\n00:32:59,310 --> 00:33:00,912\nterrorism and battling ISIL.\n\n657\n00:33:00,912 --> 00:33:05,383\nAre they trying to prop up\nAssad for another reason, or\n\n658\n00:33:05,383 --> 00:33:07,418\nis that truly their reason?\n\n659\n00:33:07,418 --> 00:33:11,856\nOr do you think that Russia\nhas a longer game here\n\n660\n00:33:11,856 --> 00:33:15,493\nthey're playing to expand\ntheir influence and power in\n\n661\n00:33:15,493 --> 00:33:16,728\nthe Middle East?\n\n662\n00:33:16,728 --> 00:33:18,930\nMr. Earnest: Well, this\nwould not be the first\n\n663\n00:33:18,930 --> 00:33:22,734\nsituation in which President\nPutin's true motivations are\n\n664\n00:33:22,734 --> 00:33:23,735\nrather hard to discern.\n\n665\n00:33:25,837 --> 00:33:27,972\nThe decision-making process\nin that country is rather\n\n666\n00:33:27,972 --> 00:33:33,544\nopaque, but there are a\ncouple of thing that we do\n\n667\n00:33:33,544 --> 00:33:34,512\nknow.\n\n668\n00:33:34,512 --> 00:33:38,483\nRussia does have\nlongstanding concerns about\n\n669\n00:33:38,483 --> 00:33:41,619\nthe spread of violent\nextremism and there's no\n\n670\n00:33:41,619 --> 00:33:43,888\ndoubt that the failed\nleadership of Assad has\n\n671\n00:33:43,888 --> 00:33:47,525\ncontributed to the spread of\nviolent extremism in Syria\n\n672\n00:33:47,525 --> 00:33:52,630\nand Iraq and even increased\nthe risk in other countries,\n\n673\n00:33:52,630 --> 00:33:53,631\ntoo.\n\n674\n00:33:54,899 --> 00:34:00,738\nWe know also that Russia has\nviewed Syria as essentially\n\n675\n00:34:00,738 --> 00:34:04,308\ntheir client state in the\nMiddle East.\n\n676\n00:34:04,308 --> 00:34:07,979\nThat is a relationship that\nRussia has enjoyed at least\n\n677\n00:34:07,979 --> 00:34:11,816\nfor quite some time and it's\none of the reasons that we\n\n678\n00:34:11,816 --> 00:34:15,853\nknow that Russia already has\nsome significant military\n\n679\n00:34:15,853 --> 00:34:17,922\nassets in Syria already.\n\n680\n00:34:17,922 --> 00:34:21,225\nAnd so this latest military\nbuildup is only to build on\n\n681\n00:34:21,225 --> 00:34:26,931\nthose assets and presumably\nto complement those assets\n\n682\n00:34:26,931 --> 00:34:30,301\nthat are already in place\ninside Syria.\n\n683\n00:34:30,334 --> 00:34:32,837\nSo that longstanding\nclient-state relationship\n\n684\n00:34:32,837 --> 00:34:36,507\nmight lead one to conclude\nthat President Putin is\n\n685\n00:34:36,507 --> 00:34:39,310\nfactoring into this equation\nsome long-term\n\n686\n00:34:39,310 --> 00:34:41,979\nconsiderations.\n\n687\n00:34:41,979 --> 00:34:44,949\nBut it's not clear exactly\nwhat he believes is the best\n\n688\n00:34:44,949 --> 00:34:47,351\nway for him to advance those\nlonger-term interests that\n\n689\n00:34:47,351 --> 00:34:50,354\nRussia may have inside of\nSyria.\n\n690\n00:34:50,354 --> 00:34:54,425\nThe case that we have made\n-- both publicly and\n\n691\n00:34:54,425 --> 00:34:56,461\nprivately in the context of\nat least a couple of phone\n\n692\n00:34:56,461 --> 00:34:58,896\ncalls between Secretary\nKerry and Foreign Minister\n\n693\n00:34:58,896 --> 00:35:02,467\nLavrov -- is that it would\nadvance the interests of the\n\n694\n00:35:02,467 --> 00:35:08,206\nworld for Russia to be a\npart of this anti-ISIL\n\n695\n00:35:08,206 --> 00:35:11,609\ncoalition to degrade and\nultimately destroy ISIL --\n\n696\n00:35:11,609 --> 00:35:15,213\nto contribute,\nconstructively to that\n\n697\n00:35:15,213 --> 00:35:18,483\neffort, but also to support\nthe kind of political\n\n698\n00:35:18,483 --> 00:35:21,819\ntransition in Syria that we\nbelieve is necessary to\n\n699\n00:35:21,819 --> 00:35:25,656\nsolve the underlying problem\nthat has led to both the\n\n700\n00:35:25,656 --> 00:35:30,595\ngrowth of ISIL, the\nexpansion of violence, and a\n\n701\n00:35:30,595 --> 00:35:33,030\nterrible humanitarian crisis\nthat's caused millions of\n\n702\n00:35:33,030 --> 00:35:35,032\npeople to flee their homes\ninside Syria.\n\n703\n00:35:35,032 --> 00:35:36,901\nThe Press: Last question.\n\n704\n00:35:36,901 --> 00:35:39,470\nIn terms of the possibility\nof a phone call between the\n\n705\n00:35:39,470 --> 00:35:42,840\nPresident and Putin, Putin\nis obviously going to be in\n\n706\n00:35:42,840 --> 00:35:44,542\nNew York for the U.N.\n\n707\n00:35:44,542 --> 00:35:45,543\nGeneral Assembly.\n\n708\n00:35:45,543 --> 00:35:48,246\nThis President has, on the\ninternational stage, been a\n\n709\n00:35:48,246 --> 00:35:50,248\nlongtime advocate\nof engagement.\n\n710\n00:35:50,248 --> 00:35:53,618\nWhy would he not meet with\nPutin while he is going to\n\n711\n00:35:53,618 --> 00:35:56,988\nbe right here in New York\nin the same city?\n\n712\n00:35:56,988 --> 00:35:58,689\nWhy would they not meet?\n\n713\n00:35:58,689 --> 00:36:01,392\nMr. Earnest: Well, the\nPresident's schedule for his\n\n714\n00:36:01,392 --> 00:36:05,763\ntrip to New York is still in\nflux and so we'll have more\n\n715\n00:36:05,763 --> 00:36:08,466\nto say once that schedule\nhas been arranged.\n\n716\n00:36:08,466 --> 00:36:11,502\nAnd certainly there is the\npossibility that the two\n\n717\n00:36:11,502 --> 00:36:14,171\nleaders could meet while\nthey're there because they\n\n718\n00:36:14,171 --> 00:36:17,208\nare likely to be there at\nthe same time.\n\n719\n00:36:17,208 --> 00:36:20,578\nAt the same time, the\nPresident has a number of\n\n720\n00:36:20,578 --> 00:36:23,281\nother commitments in New\nYork while he's there.\n\n721\n00:36:23,281 --> 00:36:26,984\nThe Press: Putin has already\nsaid that he would like to\n\n722\n00:36:26,984 --> 00:36:31,022\nmeet -- he's open to meeting\nwith the President in New York\n\n723\n00:36:31,022 --> 00:36:34,058\nMr. Earnest: Well, and\nagain, I think the President\n\n724\n00:36:34,058 --> 00:36:36,761\nhas indicated that he has\nbenefitted from regular\n\n725\n00:36:36,761 --> 00:36:38,763\nconversations with President\nPutin.\n\n726\n00:36:38,763 --> 00:36:40,831\nThey obviously disagree on\nmost of the issues that they\n\n727\n00:36:40,831 --> 00:36:43,467\ndiscuss, but at least they\ncan discuss them in a\n\n728\n00:36:43,467 --> 00:36:48,339\ncandid, pretty businesslike\nformat or environment.\n\n729\n00:36:48,339 --> 00:36:51,842\nAnd so, again, that's why I\nthink I would expressly not\n\n730\n00:36:51,842 --> 00:36:54,312\nrule out necessarily a\nPresidential conversation\n\n731\n00:36:54,312 --> 00:36:55,313\nsometime soon.\n\n732\n00:36:55,313 --> 00:36:57,915\nBut at this point, I don't\nhave updates on the\n\n733\n00:36:57,915 --> 00:36:59,083\nPresident's schedule for\nyou.\n\n734\n00:36:59,083 --> 00:37:00,084\nApril.\n\n735\n00:37:00,084 --> 00:37:02,086\nThe Press: Josh, I don't\nwant to assume -- this is\n\n736\n00:37:02,086 --> 00:37:05,289\nwhy I'm asking you -- why is\nthe President not going to\n\n737\n00:37:05,289 --> 00:37:07,291\nwatch the debate tomorrow\nnight?\n\n738\n00:37:07,291 --> 00:37:10,261\nMr. Earnest: I guess because\nhe feels like he's got\n\n739\n00:37:10,261 --> 00:37:11,596\nbetter things to do.\n\n740\n00:37:11,596 --> 00:37:12,597\n(laughter)\n\n741\n00:37:12,597 --> 00:37:14,599\nWith all due respect to CNN,\nJim.\n\n742\n00:37:14,599 --> 00:37:15,866\nThe Press: That's fine.\n\n743\n00:37:15,866 --> 00:37:16,867\n(laughter)\n\n744\n00:37:16,867 --> 00:37:19,003\nI think the viewership will\nbe okay.\n\n745\n00:37:19,003 --> 00:37:21,005\nMr. Earnest: I suspect\nthat's correct.\n\n746\n00:37:21,005 --> 00:37:23,007\nThe Press: I ask that\nbecause you use the word\n\n747\n00:37:23,007 --> 00:37:25,009\n\"human\" -- watching this\nPresidential dynamic, the\n\n748\n00:37:25,009 --> 00:37:28,613\nwannabes who want to be in\nhis office right now human\n\n749\n00:37:28,613 --> 00:37:31,916\nand I find it interesting\nthat he won't watch since\n\n750\n00:37:31,916 --> 00:37:35,553\nhe's keenly aware of what's\ngoing on, on the GOP side\n\n751\n00:37:35,553 --> 00:37:37,555\nand I guess the Democratic\nside.\n\n752\n00:37:37,555 --> 00:37:39,857\nCan you elaborate a little\nbit more?\n\n753\n00:37:39,857 --> 00:37:41,859\nMr. Earnest: Well, the\nPresident understands\n\n754\n00:37:41,859 --> 00:37:44,462\nprobably better than any\nother American that\n\n755\n00:37:44,462 --> 00:37:48,265\nelections have consequences,\nand that the kinds of\n\n756\n00:37:48,265 --> 00:37:54,138\ndiscussions about the future\nof the country that will\n\n757\n00:37:54,138 --> 00:37:57,875\ntake place over the next 15\nmonths or so are critically\n\n758\n00:37:57,875 --> 00:38:01,612\nimportant as Americans\ndecide the next person that\n\n759\n00:38:01,612 --> 00:38:03,581\nshould sit in the Oval\nOffice just down the hall\n\n760\n00:38:03,581 --> 00:38:04,582\nhere.\n\n761\n00:38:04,582 --> 00:38:07,251\nAnd there are big\nconsequences for that,\n\n762\n00:38:07,251 --> 00:38:10,788\nparticularly as it relates\nto the vision that this\n\n763\n00:38:10,788 --> 00:38:12,790\nPresident has for the future\nof the country.\n\n764\n00:38:12,790 --> 00:38:16,994\nThe President is very\ninvested in seeing the kinds\n\n765\n00:38:16,994 --> 00:38:20,264\nof values and priorities\nthat he's championed be\n\n766\n00:38:20,264 --> 00:38:25,770\nsupported by the next\nPresident.\n\n767\n00:38:25,770 --> 00:38:27,772\nAnd obviously there will be\na pretty robust debate about\n\n768\n00:38:27,772 --> 00:38:28,773\nthe best way to do that.\n\n769\n00:38:28,773 --> 00:38:34,011\nThere are some -- there are\na variety of points of view\n\n770\n00:38:34,011 --> 00:38:35,980\nthat will be offered up both\nin the Democratic and\n\n771\n00:38:35,980 --> 00:38:38,849\nRepublican primaries, and\nthen we'll also have a\n\n772\n00:38:38,849 --> 00:38:41,252\npretty vigorous national\ndebate in the context of the\n\n773\n00:38:41,252 --> 00:38:42,586\ngeneral election.\n\n774\n00:38:42,586 --> 00:38:44,789\nAll of that is evidence of a\nvery healthy democracy in\n\n775\n00:38:44,789 --> 00:38:46,791\nthis country, and the\nPresident is pleased that we\n\n776\n00:38:46,791 --> 00:38:48,793\ncan have a robust political\ndebate.\n\n777\n00:38:48,793 --> 00:38:50,795\nAnd again, the President\nunderstands the stakes of\n\n778\n00:38:50,795 --> 00:38:52,797\nthose debates better than\nmost because he's been\n\n779\n00:38:52,797 --> 00:38:54,799\nthrough this process himself\ntwice now.\n\n780\n00:38:54,799 --> 00:38:56,801\nSo he certainly understands\nwhy this is important, and\n\n781\n00:38:56,801 --> 00:38:58,769\nthat's why he's paying\nattention.\n\n782\n00:38:58,769 --> 00:39:00,771\nThe Press: Thinking back to\nthen-Presidential candidate\n\n783\n00:39:00,771 --> 00:39:02,940\nthe first time, Barack\nObama, do you think that he\n\n784\n00:39:02,940 --> 00:39:07,945\nlived up to his pledge of\nhope and change since he's\n\n785\n00:39:12,216 --> 00:39:15,586\nbeen in office twice?\n\n786\n00:39:15,586 --> 00:39:18,322\nMr. Earnest: Absolutely.\n\n787\n00:39:18,322 --> 00:39:20,324\nThere probably is a really\nlong answer to that question\n\n788\n00:39:20,324 --> 00:39:24,829\n-- I'll try to keep it short\n-- which is I think the\n\n789\n00:39:24,829 --> 00:39:29,066\nopening of the briefing\ntoday is one powerful\n\n790\n00:39:29,066 --> 00:39:31,836\nillustration of the\ntremendously important\n\n791\n00:39:31,836 --> 00:39:34,705\neconomic progress that this\ncountry has made under the\n\n792\n00:39:34,705 --> 00:39:36,774\nleadership of President\nObama.\n\n793\n00:39:36,774 --> 00:39:38,776\nAgain, I would be the first\nperson -- actually, the\n\n794\n00:39:38,776 --> 00:39:41,112\nPresident would be the first\nperson to give the bulk of\n\n795\n00:39:41,112 --> 00:39:43,114\nthat credit to the American\npeople and to American\n\n796\n00:39:43,114 --> 00:39:45,116\nworkers and to American\nentrepreneurs.\n\n797\n00:39:45,116 --> 00:39:50,287\nBut there is no denying that\nthis President made some\n\n798\n00:39:50,287 --> 00:39:54,558\nrisky, politically unpopular\nbets, but the President had\n\n799\n00:39:54,558 --> 00:39:56,560\nconfidence in those bets\nbecause he was betting on\n\n800\n00:39:56,560 --> 00:39:57,561\nthe American people.\n\n801\n00:39:57,561 --> 00:39:59,930\nAnd whether that was a\ndecision to invest in the\n\n802\n00:39:59,930 --> 00:40:02,800\nRecovery Act, or to invest\nand rescue the auto\n\n803\n00:40:02,800 --> 00:40:07,037\nindustry, the American\neconomy has benefitted\n\n804\n00:40:07,037 --> 00:40:11,976\ntremendously from those\ndifficult and, in some\n\n805\n00:40:11,976 --> 00:40:14,311\ncases, very politically\nunpopular decisions that the\n\n806\n00:40:14,311 --> 00:40:15,312\nPresident made.\n\n807\n00:40:15,312 --> 00:40:20,184\nBut they paid off for the\nU.S.\n\n808\n00:40:20,184 --> 00:40:22,186\neconomy and for the American\npeople.\n\n809\n00:40:22,186 --> 00:40:27,024\nAnd the President is proud\nof it.\n\n810\n00:40:27,024 --> 00:40:32,029\nThe Press: And one last\nquestion -- going back to\n\n811\n00:40:39,203 --> 00:40:44,175\none of your answers to one\nof my questions, you had a\n\n812\n00:40:53,784 --> 00:40:58,789\nstatement basically saying\nthe President is concerned\n\n813\n00:40:58,789 --> 00:41:04,595\nwith some of the rhetoric\nthat's out there that's kind\n\n814\n00:41:04,595 --> 00:41:10,768\nof walked away or moving\naway from his policies.\n\n815\n00:41:10,768 --> 00:41:15,973\nWhat are -- can you\narticulate specifically some\n\n816\n00:41:15,973 --> 00:41:17,975\nof his concerns in listening\nto this rhetoric that he's\n\n817\n00:41:17,975 --> 00:41:19,977\nhearing on Democratic and\nRepublican side?\n\n818\n00:41:19,977 --> 00:41:21,979\nMr. Earnest: Well, I don't\nthink there is anything that\n\n819\n00:41:21,979 --> 00:41:23,981\nI'd single out at this\npoint, but I do -- in the\n\n820\n00:41:23,981 --> 00:41:25,983\ncontext of the town hall\nmeeting that the President\n\n821\n00:41:25,983 --> 00:41:27,985\nconvened in Des Moines just\nyesterday, somebody asked\n\n822\n00:41:27,985 --> 00:41:29,987\nthe question about -- asked\nthe President a question\n\n823\n00:41:29,987 --> 00:41:31,989\nabout immigration reform and\nimmigration policy.\n\n824\n00:41:31,989 --> 00:41:33,991\nAnd the President made clear\nhis concerns about some of\n\n825\n00:41:33,991 --> 00:41:35,993\nthe rhetoric that's thrown\nabout on the Republican side\n\n826\n00:41:35,993 --> 00:41:37,995\nwhen describing the\ncontribution of immigrants\n\n827\n00:41:37,995 --> 00:41:38,996\nto our country.\n\n828\n00:41:38,996 --> 00:41:40,998\nThe President has been quite\ndisappointed in that\n\n829\n00:41:40,998 --> 00:41:43,000\nrhetoric and he made that\nclear yesterday.\n\n830\n00:41:43,000 --> 00:41:44,001\nThat's only one example.\n\n831\n00:41:44,001 --> 00:41:45,970\nThe Press: Perhaps speaking\nabout Donald Trump,\n\n832\n00:41:45,970 --> 00:41:47,972\nspecifically or --\nMr. Earnest: That is\n\n833\n00:41:47,972 --> 00:41:49,974\nspeaking to the rhetoric\nthat is used by an alarming\n\n834\n00:41:49,974 --> 00:41:51,976\nnumber of Republican\ncandidates.\n\n835\n00:41:51,976 --> 00:41:52,977\nKevin.\n\n836\n00:41:52,977 --> 00:41:53,978\nThe Press: Josh, thanks.\n\n837\n00:41:53,978 --> 00:41:55,980\nI want to follow up on your\ncomments about cyber\n\n838\n00:41:55,980 --> 00:41:57,982\nterrorism and cyber spying\nas it relates to China.\n\n839\n00:41:57,982 --> 00:41:59,984\nAnd I know that you don't\nwant to get into specifics\n\n840\n00:41:59,984 --> 00:42:01,986\nabout individuals or even\ncompanies that may\n\n841\n00:42:01,986 --> 00:42:03,988\nultimately be sanctioned,\nbut I'm curious about,\n\n842\n00:42:03,988 --> 00:42:05,990\nbroadly speaking, what might\nsanctions look like, what\n\n843\n00:42:05,990 --> 00:42:07,992\ntype of sanctions are we\ntalking about, and how they\n\n844\n00:42:07,992 --> 00:42:08,993\nmight have teeth, if you\nwill.\n\n845\n00:42:08,993 --> 00:42:10,995\nMr. Earnest: Well, Kevin, I\nthink for a detailed\n\n846\n00:42:10,995 --> 00:42:12,997\nanalysis of this, I'd refer\nyou to the Treasury\n\n847\n00:42:12,997 --> 00:42:13,998\nDepartment.\n\n848\n00:42:13,998 --> 00:42:16,000\nBut traditionally, what\neconomic sanctions refers to\n\n849\n00:42:16,000 --> 00:42:18,002\nis targeting a set of\nindividuals for a variety of\n\n850\n00:42:18,002 --> 00:42:19,970\nreasons -- in this case it\nwould be because they either\n\n851\n00:42:19,970 --> 00:42:21,972\nengaged in inappropriate or\ndeeply concerning cyber\n\n852\n00:42:21,972 --> 00:42:23,974\nactivity, or they benefited\nfrom it.\n\n853\n00:42:23,974 --> 00:42:25,976\nAnd essentially, these\nindividuals would have their\n\n854\n00:42:25,976 --> 00:42:26,977\naccess to the U.S.\n\n855\n00:42:26,977 --> 00:42:28,979\nfinancial system either\nseverely limited or entirely\n\n856\n00:42:28,979 --> 00:42:29,980\nshut off.\n\n857\n00:42:29,980 --> 00:42:33,217\nAnd because of the\npreeminent role that the\n\n858\n00:42:33,217 --> 00:42:34,351\nU.S.\n\n859\n00:42:34,351 --> 00:42:36,587\nfinancial and banking system\nplays in the international\n\n860\n00:42:36,587 --> 00:42:39,490\neconomy, that can have some\npretty serious consequences\n\n861\n00:42:39,490 --> 00:42:43,360\nfor those individuals or for\nthose entities.\n\n862\n00:42:43,360 --> 00:42:49,099\nAnd again, that is one way\nthat the strength of the\n\n863\n00:42:49,099 --> 00:42:50,100\nU.S.\n\n864\n00:42:50,100 --> 00:42:52,703\neconomy and our influence\naround the world can be\n\n865\n00:42:52,703 --> 00:42:55,339\nleveraged to advance our\ninterests around the world,\n\n866\n00:42:55,339 --> 00:42:57,608\neven in a setting that, in\nsome cases, isn't directly\n\n867\n00:42:57,608 --> 00:42:58,609\nrelated to the economy.\n\n868\n00:42:58,609 --> 00:43:01,578\nThe Press: So is it a\nthreat, is it a warning when\n\n869\n00:43:01,578 --> 00:43:03,180\nPresident Xi comes?\n\n870\n00:43:03,180 --> 00:43:06,684\nIs the President essentially\nsaying, knock it off or\n\n871\n00:43:06,684 --> 00:43:07,685\nelse?\n\n872\n00:43:07,685 --> 00:43:09,687\nHow does that conversation\nplay out in your mind?\n\n873\n00:43:09,687 --> 00:43:12,289\nMr. Earnest: Well, I think\nthe conversation plays out I\n\n874\n00:43:12,289 --> 00:43:14,325\nthink in the same way that\nit has the two previous\n\n875\n00:43:14,325 --> 00:43:16,327\ntimes -- or at least the two\nprevious times that I can\n\n876\n00:43:16,327 --> 00:43:19,396\nrecall that the President\nmet with President Xi and\n\n877\n00:43:19,396 --> 00:43:24,201\ndirectly raised these\nissues, and that is the\n\n878\n00:43:24,201 --> 00:43:26,370\nPresident will speak\ndirectly with President Xi\n\n879\n00:43:26,370 --> 00:43:29,873\nabout the specific concerns\nthat we have with the kind\n\n880\n00:43:29,873 --> 00:43:34,378\nof activity that we see\nemanating from China.\n\n881\n00:43:34,378 --> 00:43:37,481\nAnd I don't think the\nPresident has found it\n\n882\n00:43:37,481 --> 00:43:42,453\nparticularly constructive to\nbe offering or posing or\n\n883\n00:43:42,453 --> 00:43:45,856\nmaking specific threats in\nthe Oval Office.\n\n884\n00:43:45,856 --> 00:43:48,659\nBut everyone is aware of the\nrange of options that the\n\n885\n00:43:48,659 --> 00:43:51,261\nPresident has for\nconfronting this particular\n\n886\n00:43:51,261 --> 00:43:52,930\nproblem.\n\n887\n00:43:52,930 --> 00:43:57,301\nThere is no doubt in the\nmind of leaders of the\n\n888\n00:43:57,301 --> 00:44:00,537\nChinese government that\nPresident Obama takes this\n\n889\n00:44:00,537 --> 00:44:05,576\nissue very seriously and is\nwilling to speak directly\n\n890\n00:44:05,576 --> 00:44:10,447\nand act decisively to\nconfront it.\n\n891\n00:44:10,447 --> 00:44:13,050\nAnd that's what the\nPresident will do in the\n\n892\n00:44:13,050 --> 00:44:15,052\ncontext of this meeting as\nwell.\n\n893\n00:44:15,052 --> 00:44:17,287\nThe Press: You don't think\nthere's any chance it will\n\n894\n00:44:17,287 --> 00:44:20,224\nultimately scuttle the\nPresident's visit to\n\n895\n00:44:20,224 --> 00:44:21,225\nWashington?\n\n896\n00:44:21,225 --> 00:44:23,227\nMr. Earnest: Well, I\ncertainly -- I mean, at this\n\n897\n00:44:23,227 --> 00:44:24,762\npoint I would hope not.\n\n898\n00:44:24,762 --> 00:44:27,898\nThere's a lot to discuss.\n\n899\n00:44:27,898 --> 00:44:29,900\nAnd again, there are a range\nof issues.\n\n900\n00:44:29,900 --> 00:44:32,436\nThis is certainly an\nimportant one and a genuine\n\n901\n00:44:32,436 --> 00:44:35,472\npriority, and one that we\ncontinue to be quite\n\n902\n00:44:35,472 --> 00:44:37,174\nconcerned about.\n\n903\n00:44:37,174 --> 00:44:40,878\nBut the announcement that\nwas made today, the\n\n904\n00:44:40,878 --> 00:44:44,481\ncommitment on the part of a\nnumber of Chinese cities and\n\n905\n00:44:44,481 --> 00:44:50,387\nprovinces to cap their\ncarbon pollution, is a\n\n906\n00:44:50,387 --> 00:44:53,290\nsignificant announcement and\nhas significant consequences\n\n907\n00:44:53,290 --> 00:44:55,692\nand benefits for American\ninterests and the American\n\n908\n00:44:55,692 --> 00:44:56,693\npeople.\n\n909\n00:44:56,693 --> 00:44:58,862\nThere were corresponding\ncommitments that were made\n\n910\n00:44:58,862 --> 00:45:00,697\nby American cities as well.\n\n911\n00:45:00,697 --> 00:45:02,699\nAnd this is an example of\nhow the United States and\n\n912\n00:45:02,699 --> 00:45:05,335\nChina can work together to\nadvance our interests.\n\n913\n00:45:05,335 --> 00:45:09,740\nThe same thing was true when\nit came to the Iran\n\n914\n00:45:09,740 --> 00:45:12,142\nnegotiations, and that was\n-- China played a very\n\n915\n00:45:12,142 --> 00:45:13,143\nconstructive role there.\n\n916\n00:45:13,143 --> 00:45:16,480\nSo there is an opportunity\nfor us -- and I think that\n\n917\n00:45:16,480 --> 00:45:19,616\nthe Chinese leaders would\nsay that the diplomatic\n\n918\n00:45:19,616 --> 00:45:23,554\nresolution to that situation\nis in the interest of the\n\n919\n00:45:23,554 --> 00:45:25,122\nChinese people as well.\n\n920\n00:45:25,122 --> 00:45:28,659\nThat's a case that the\nPresident has obviously made\n\n921\n00:45:28,659 --> 00:45:32,729\nto the American people and\neven to our Israeli allies.\n\n922\n00:45:32,729 --> 00:45:35,265\nI'm confident that Chinese\nofficials feel the same way.\n\n923\n00:45:35,265 --> 00:45:38,068\nThe Press: Are they lying\nwhen they say the U.S.\n\n924\n00:45:38,068 --> 00:45:40,070\nis cyber-spying on them as\nwell?\n\n925\n00:45:40,070 --> 00:45:42,639\nMr. Earnest: Well, I\ncertainly would not -- I\n\n926\n00:45:42,639 --> 00:45:46,276\ndon't think it would be\nappropriate, at least in\n\n927\n00:45:46,276 --> 00:45:50,180\nthis context, for me to use\nthat kind of label against\n\n928\n00:45:50,180 --> 00:45:53,117\nthe leaders of China.\n\n929\n00:45:53,117 --> 00:45:57,187\nBut what I think I would\nalso say is I don't have a\n\n930\n00:45:57,187 --> 00:46:01,992\nlot to say about any\nactivity that may or may not\n\n931\n00:46:01,992 --> 00:46:05,062\nbe engaged in by the United\nStates in that regard.\n\n932\n00:46:05,062 --> 00:46:09,666\nBut we have been quite clear\nthat the United States does\n\n933\n00:46:09,666 --> 00:46:13,904\nnot engage in the kind of\ncyber activity that yields a\n\n934\n00:46:13,904 --> 00:46:16,140\nsignificant financial\nbenefit for American\n\n935\n00:46:16,140 --> 00:46:17,307\ncompanies.\n\n936\n00:46:17,307 --> 00:46:19,843\nAnd that's precisely the\nkind of behavior and\n\n937\n00:46:19,843 --> 00:46:22,679\nactivity that we've raised\nconcerns about with regard\n\n938\n00:46:22,679 --> 00:46:23,680\nto China.\n\n939\n00:46:23,680 --> 00:46:25,682\nThe Press: Last one --\nCalifornia fires.\n\n940\n00:46:25,682 --> 00:46:26,683\nAny update on that?\n\n941\n00:46:26,683 --> 00:46:27,684\nHas the President been\nbriefed?\n\n942\n00:46:27,684 --> 00:46:28,685\nIt's a massive problem\nthere.\n\n943\n00:46:28,685 --> 00:46:34,258\nMr. Earnest: Well, Kevin,\nthis is a significant\n\n944\n00:46:34,258 --> 00:46:36,260\nproblem, and this is one\nthat the President has been\n\n945\n00:46:36,260 --> 00:46:37,261\nfocused on.\n\n946\n00:46:37,261 --> 00:46:40,797\nAnd we may have a little bit\nmore news on this later\n\n947\n00:46:40,797 --> 00:46:47,638\ntoday, but you have seen\nthat the Obama\n\n948\n00:46:47,638 --> 00:46:50,340\nadministration had made a\nspecific request of Congress\n\n949\n00:46:50,340 --> 00:46:54,745\nto change the funding\nmechanism for wildfires and\n\n950\n00:46:54,745 --> 00:46:56,747\nthe response to wildfires.\n\n951\n00:46:56,747 --> 00:46:58,916\nRight now, you essentially\nhave a situation where both\n\n952\n00:46:58,916 --> 00:47:02,085\nthe Forest Service and some\nelements of the Department\n\n953\n00:47:02,085 --> 00:47:08,559\nof Interior are using\nfunding that was originally\n\n954\n00:47:08,559 --> 00:47:11,862\ndedicated to preventing\nforest fires to actually\n\n955\n00:47:12,029 --> 00:47:13,297\nfight the forest fires.\n\n956\n00:47:13,297 --> 00:47:18,302\nAnd that ends up being a\nflawed strategy, because the\n\n957\n00:47:19,570 --> 00:47:23,307\nless that we can devote to\nwildfire prevention, the\n\n958\n00:47:23,307 --> 00:47:25,309\nmore that we're going to\nhave to dedicate to\n\n959\n00:47:25,309 --> 00:47:26,310\nfirefighting.\n\n960\n00:47:26,310 --> 00:47:28,779\nAnd so we made a specific\nrequest of Congress to\n\n961\n00:47:28,779 --> 00:47:31,014\nchange that funding\nmechanism so that we can\n\n962\n00:47:31,014 --> 00:47:34,618\nprotect the important\nprograms that go toward\n\n963\n00:47:35,052 --> 00:47:37,888\npreventing wildfires while\nalso making sure we have all\n\n964\n00:47:37,888 --> 00:47:42,459\nthe resources that we need\nto assist state and local\n\n965\n00:47:42,459 --> 00:47:45,896\nfirefighters who are trying\nto protect lives and\n\n966\n00:47:45,896 --> 00:47:46,897\nproperty out West.\n\n967\n00:47:46,897 --> 00:47:47,898\nPam.\n\n968\n00:47:47,898 --> 00:47:50,968\nThe Press: Josh, following\nup on the Montenegro issue,\n\n969\n00:47:50,968 --> 00:47:55,239\nRussia has made it pretty\nclear that it doesn't want\n\n970\n00:47:55,239 --> 00:47:59,042\nto see any NATO expansion,\nespecially in the East.\n\n971\n00:47:59,042 --> 00:48:02,312\nCould they view that as a\nprovocation, maybe an\n\n972\n00:48:02,312 --> 00:48:06,650\nin-your-face kind of thing\n-- the fact that the U.S.\n\n973\n00:48:06,650 --> 00:48:09,686\nhas given conditional\nsupport to Montenegro to\n\n974\n00:48:09,686 --> 00:48:10,687\njoin NATO?\n\n975\n00:48:10,687 --> 00:48:14,458\nAnd wasn't the Western\nUkraine sort of interest in\n\n976\n00:48:14,458 --> 00:48:18,495\nthe West a reason why Russia\ngot involved -- intervened\n\n977\n00:48:18,495 --> 00:48:19,630\nin Ukraine?\n\n978\n00:48:19,630 --> 00:48:22,899\nMr. Earnest: Well, to be\ndirect about answering your\n\n979\n00:48:22,899 --> 00:48:25,402\nquestion, I don't know how\nthe Russians will perceive\n\n980\n00:48:25,402 --> 00:48:26,403\nit.\n\n981\n00:48:26,403 --> 00:48:29,973\nWhat I would say to anybody\nwho's interested in\n\n982\n00:48:29,973 --> 00:48:32,142\nunderstanding exactly this\npolicy decision is I would\n\n983\n00:48:32,142 --> 00:48:35,712\nassure them that this is a\npolicy decision that went\n\n984\n00:48:35,712 --> 00:48:39,082\nthrough the regular process\nand took some time to arrive\n\n985\n00:48:39,082 --> 00:48:40,083\nat.\n\n986\n00:48:40,083 --> 00:48:43,720\nSo this is not an effort to\nrespond to any particular\n\n987\n00:48:43,720 --> 00:48:46,423\naction that's taken by any\nother country, but rather a\n\n988\n00:48:46,423 --> 00:48:48,592\npolicy decision that is\ngrounded in the long-term\n\n989\n00:48:48,592 --> 00:48:51,094\nbest interests of the United\nStates.\n\n990\n00:48:51,094 --> 00:48:53,096\nAnd again, that was a\ndecision that was conveyed\n\n991\n00:48:53,096 --> 00:48:56,466\nto the Montenegrin leader\njust yesterday by the Vice\n\n992\n00:48:56,466 --> 00:48:57,467\nPresident.\n\n993\n00:48:57,467 --> 00:48:59,603\nThe Press: Is there any\nconcern it could provoke a\n\n994\n00:48:59,603 --> 00:49:03,807\nnegative reaction from\nRussia if it does get into\n\n995\n00:49:03,807 --> 00:49:04,808\nNATO?\n\n996\n00:49:04,808 --> 00:49:07,377\nMr. Earnest: Well, I guess\nit's certainly possible, but\n\n997\n00:49:07,377 --> 00:49:09,913\nthat would be a decision\nthat is made by the\n\n998\n00:49:09,913 --> 00:49:10,914\nRussians.\n\n999\n00:49:10,914 --> 00:49:14,017\nWe've been quite clear about\nwhat our intentions are and\n\n1000\n00:49:14,017 --> 00:49:17,521\nhow the strength of NATO has\ncontributed to not just the\n\n1001\n00:49:17,521 --> 00:49:19,523\nnational security interests\nof the United States but has\n\n1002\n00:49:19,523 --> 00:49:24,227\nbeen a bedrock of a peaceful\nand unified Europe for a\n\n1003\n00:49:24,227 --> 00:49:25,228\ncouple generations now.\n\n1004\n00:49:25,228 --> 00:49:27,230\nThe Press: And just a quick\none.\n\n1005\n00:49:27,230 --> 00:49:28,699\nThere was recently a U.N.\n\n1006\n00:49:28,699 --> 00:49:32,736\nhuman rights report that\ncame out saying 8,000 people\n\n1007\n00:49:32,736 --> 00:49:36,206\nhave been killed in eastern\nUkraine since, I guess, a\n\n1008\n00:49:36,206 --> 00:49:39,343\nyear ago, April, and that\nthe situation really was\n\n1009\n00:49:39,343 --> 00:49:42,479\ngetting worse in terms of\ncivilians dying, and that\n\n1010\n00:49:42,479 --> 00:49:45,782\nmore needed to be done to\nstop the violence.\n\n1011\n00:49:45,782 --> 00:49:48,218\nIs there any thought to\nratcheting up the sanctions\n\n1012\n00:49:48,218 --> 00:49:49,753\non Russia for that?\n\n1013\n00:49:49,753 --> 00:49:52,022\nMr. Earnest: Well, the\nUnited States has\n\n1014\n00:49:52,022 --> 00:49:54,725\ncoordinated effectively with\nour European counterparts to\n\n1015\n00:49:54,725 --> 00:49:57,794\napply pressure to the\nRussians because of their\n\n1016\n00:49:57,794 --> 00:50:00,430\ndestabilizing activities in\nUkraine.\n\n1017\n00:50:00,430 --> 00:50:03,300\nAnd there are a raft of\neconomic figures that I\n\n1018\n00:50:03,300 --> 00:50:06,036\ncould point you to that are\nmoving in the opposite\n\n1019\n00:50:06,036 --> 00:50:08,405\ndirections from the\nstatistics that I cited at\n\n1020\n00:50:08,405 --> 00:50:09,406\nthe beginning of this\nbriefing.\n\n1021\n00:50:10,340 --> 00:50:12,743\nAnd part of the reason for\nthat is because of the\n\n1022\n00:50:12,743 --> 00:50:16,446\nincreasing international\neconomic isolation of the\n\n1023\n00:50:16,446 --> 00:50:21,451\nRussian leadership and the\nRussian economy.\n\n1024\n00:50:22,486 --> 00:50:24,488\nThat's had consequences for\nthem.\n\n1025\n00:50:24,488 --> 00:50:27,824\nIt's had consequences for\ntheir private investment\n\n1026\n00:50:27,824 --> 00:50:28,825\nenvironment.\n\n1027\n00:50:28,825 --> 00:50:30,827\nIt's had consequences for\nthe value of their currency.\n\n1028\n00:50:31,061 --> 00:50:34,064\nIt's had consequences for\nprojections about the future\n\n1029\n00:50:34,064 --> 00:50:35,065\ngrowth of their economy.\n\n1030\n00:50:35,532 --> 00:50:38,735\nSo there's no doubt that the\nUnited States and Russia --\n\n1031\n00:50:38,735 --> 00:50:41,138\nI'm sorry -- the United\nStates and Europe have been\n\n1032\n00:50:41,138 --> 00:50:44,374\nable to effectively\ncoordinate our actions to\n\n1033\n00:50:45,642 --> 00:50:48,412\nimpose costs on Russia for\ntheir destabilizing\n\n1034\n00:50:48,412 --> 00:50:49,880\nactivities in Ukraine.\n\n1035\n00:50:49,880 --> 00:50:52,282\nAt the same time, we've also\nbeen pretty candid about the\n\n1036\n00:50:52,282 --> 00:50:56,620\nfact that those costs have\nnot yet resulted in the\n\n1037\n00:50:56,620 --> 00:50:59,489\nkinds of strategic decisions\nthat we would like to see\n\n1038\n00:50:59,489 --> 00:51:01,525\nfrom President Putin.\n\n1039\n00:51:01,525 --> 00:51:04,961\nAnd that's why Russia faces\nincreasing international\n\n1040\n00:51:04,961 --> 00:51:05,962\nisolation.\n\n1041\n00:51:05,962 --> 00:51:11,535\nAnd I'm not aware of any new\nsanctions policy that will\n\n1042\n00:51:11,535 --> 00:51:15,005\nbe announced in the near\nterm, but what we have said\n\n1043\n00:51:15,005 --> 00:51:17,007\nis that the longer that\nthese sanctions remain in\n\n1044\n00:51:17,007 --> 00:51:23,413\nplace, the more isolated and\nthe more bite these\n\n1045\n00:51:23,413 --> 00:51:25,415\nsanctions end up having on\nthe Russian economy.\n\n1046\n00:51:25,415 --> 00:51:30,053\nAnd again, that is a direct\nresult of the strategic\n\n1047\n00:51:30,053 --> 00:51:33,290\ndecisions that are being\nmade by President Putin.\n\n1048\n00:51:33,290 --> 00:51:37,794\nAnd we've been just as clear\nthat if the Russians are\n\n1049\n00:51:37,794 --> 00:51:39,796\nprepared to start living up\nto the commitments that\n\n1050\n00:51:39,796 --> 00:51:42,399\nthey've made in the context\nof multilateral talks in\n\n1051\n00:51:42,399 --> 00:51:45,569\nMinsk that the United States\nand European community would\n\n1052\n00:51:45,569 --> 00:51:48,138\nbe prepared to start rolling\nback those sanctions.\n\n1053\n00:51:48,138 --> 00:51:51,875\nBut again, that will require\nRussia to make the kind of\n\n1054\n00:51:51,875 --> 00:51:56,813\ndecision to depart from the\ndestabilizing activities\n\n1055\n00:51:56,813 --> 00:51:58,815\nthat they've been pursuing\nin Ukraine for quite some\n\n1056\n00:51:58,815 --> 00:51:59,950\ntime now.\n\n1057\n00:51:59,950 --> 00:52:00,951\nMargaret.\n\n1058\n00:52:00,951 --> 00:52:02,953\nThe Press: Josh, you've said\nthe White House position is\n\n1059\n00:52:02,953 --> 00:52:04,554\nstill that Assad must go.\n\n1060\n00:52:04,554 --> 00:52:07,624\nI'm wondering if you could\ndrill down a little bit,\n\n1061\n00:52:07,624 --> 00:52:10,660\nbecause some of America's\nallies in this fight -- the\n\n1062\n00:52:10,660 --> 00:52:11,661\nU.K.\n\n1063\n00:52:11,661 --> 00:52:14,030\nand others -- have evolved\nin their view, saying that\n\n1064\n00:52:14,030 --> 00:52:18,001\nAssad doesn't have to go on\nday one, that he can be part\n\n1065\n00:52:18,001 --> 00:52:19,002\nof the transition.\n\n1066\n00:52:19,002 --> 00:52:21,371\nIs that also your\nunderstanding of where the\n\n1067\n00:52:21,371 --> 00:52:22,372\nU.S.\n\n1068\n00:52:22,372 --> 00:52:23,807\nis when it says Assad must\ngo?\n\n1069\n00:52:23,807 --> 00:52:26,309\nMr. Earnest: Well, the\nposition that we have made\n\n1070\n00:52:26,309 --> 00:52:29,079\nclear is that we do believe\nthat Assad has lost the\n\n1071\n00:52:29,079 --> 00:52:33,183\nlegitimacy to lead that\ncountry and we need to\n\n1072\n00:52:33,183 --> 00:52:36,786\nfacilitate a political\ntransition inside of Syria\n\n1073\n00:52:36,786 --> 00:52:39,222\nthat results in Assad's\ndeparture.\n\n1074\n00:52:39,222 --> 00:52:41,525\nHe's lost legitimacy to lead\nthat country.\n\n1075\n00:52:41,525 --> 00:52:44,961\nThere is a U.N.-led process\nto try to pursue this\n\n1076\n00:52:44,961 --> 00:52:48,031\ndiplomatic transition.\n\n1077\n00:52:48,031 --> 00:52:50,133\nAnd despite the strong\nsupport of the United\n\n1078\n00:52:50,133 --> 00:52:52,335\nStates, we haven't seen that\nprocess gain the kind of\n\n1079\n00:52:52,335 --> 00:52:53,336\ntraction that we would like.\n\n1080\n00:52:53,336 --> 00:52:56,940\nSo that continues to be our\n-- but that does continue to\n\n1081\n00:52:56,940 --> 00:52:59,609\nbe our goal, principally\nbecause it's just not\n\n1082\n00:52:59,609 --> 00:53:03,713\nfeasible for a leader like\nAssad to remain in power\n\n1083\n00:53:03,713 --> 00:53:06,683\nwhile he's also using the\nmilitary of that country to\n\n1084\n00:53:06,683 --> 00:53:08,852\ndrop bombs indiscriminately\non his own people.\n\n1085\n00:53:08,852 --> 00:53:11,187\nThe Press: So to clarify,\nyou're not ruling out that\n\n1086\n00:53:11,187 --> 00:53:13,890\nhe could be part of a\ntransition if the agreement\n\n1087\n00:53:13,890 --> 00:53:15,559\nis that he'll ultimately\nexit?\n\n1088\n00:53:15,559 --> 00:53:18,929\nMr. Earnest: What we have\nmade clear is that a\n\n1089\n00:53:18,929 --> 00:53:20,931\npolitical transition is\nnecessary, and Assad's\n\n1090\n00:53:20,931 --> 00:53:21,932\ndeparture is necessary.\n\n1091\n00:53:21,932 --> 00:53:25,268\nThe Press: But one doesn't\nhave to happen before the\n\n1092\n00:53:25,268 --> 00:53:26,269\nother.\n\n1093\n00:53:26,269 --> 00:53:28,271\nMr. Earnest: Well, again,\nthere's a U.N.-led process\n\n1094\n00:53:28,271 --> 00:53:31,741\nto try to determine -- to\ntry to effectuate that kind\n\n1095\n00:53:31,741 --> 00:53:32,876\nof political transition.\n\n1096\n00:53:32,876 --> 00:53:34,844\nAnd unfortunately, we\nhaven't seen a lot of\n\n1097\n00:53:34,844 --> 00:53:36,212\nprogress in that regard.\n\n1098\n00:53:36,212 --> 00:53:39,883\nBut it has not diminished\neither the United States'\n\n1099\n00:53:39,883 --> 00:53:44,421\nsupport for that process, or\nour belief that the only way\n\n1100\n00:53:44,421 --> 00:53:49,192\nthat we're going to resolve\nall of the terrible\n\n1101\n00:53:49,192 --> 00:53:52,829\nconsequences stemming from\nAssad's failed leadership\n\n1102\n00:53:52,829 --> 00:53:55,532\nwithout that kind of\nU.N.-facilitate political\n\n1103\n00:53:55,532 --> 00:53:56,533\ntransition.\n\n1104\n00:53:56,533 --> 00:54:00,136\nThe Press: To go then to the\nrefugee crisis, because, as\n\n1105\n00:54:00,136 --> 00:54:02,138\nyou're saying, there's a lot\nof frustration that you're\n\n1106\n00:54:02,138 --> 00:54:04,975\njust not in any kind of\nconversation diplomatically\n\n1107\n00:54:04,975 --> 00:54:06,776\nto make that transition\nhappen.\n\n1108\n00:54:06,776 --> 00:54:10,714\nSo if that's the path to\nending the war, that's not\n\n1109\n00:54:10,714 --> 00:54:11,781\nhaving much success.\n\n1110\n00:54:11,781 --> 00:54:15,385\nYou have this hemorrhage of\npeople into Europe and the\n\n1111\n00:54:15,385 --> 00:54:18,254\nneighboring countries, so is\nthere any thought of\n\n1112\n00:54:18,254 --> 00:54:21,091\nrevisiting the White House\ndecision and looking at\n\n1113\n00:54:21,091 --> 00:54:24,327\nestablishing some kind of\nsafe haven within the border\n\n1114\n00:54:24,327 --> 00:54:28,264\nof Syria so that people\ndon't have to flee it in\n\n1115\n00:54:28,264 --> 00:54:29,699\norder to find safety?\n\n1116\n00:54:29,699 --> 00:54:32,569\nAny kind of version of a\nsafe haven?\n\n1117\n00:54:32,569 --> 00:54:35,105\nMr. Earnest: Those who know\na whole lot more about Syria\n\n1118\n00:54:35,105 --> 00:54:38,141\nthan I do I'm sure would\nconfidently describe the\n\n1119\n00:54:38,141 --> 00:54:40,143\nsituation in Syria as\nchaotic.\n\n1120\n00:54:40,143 --> 00:54:42,145\nAnd that has had a\ncorresponding impact that\n\n1121\n00:54:42,145 --> 00:54:44,714\nyou would expect on the\nsecurity situation in that\n\n1122\n00:54:44,714 --> 00:54:45,715\ncountry.\n\n1123\n00:54:45,715 --> 00:54:47,717\nSo the focus of our efforts\nright now is to degrade and\n\n1124\n00:54:47,717 --> 00:54:48,718\nultimately destroy ISIL.\n\n1125\n00:54:48,718 --> 00:54:50,720\nAnd there has been important\nprogress that counter-ISIL\n\n1126\n00:54:50,720 --> 00:54:52,722\nfighters have made in\ndriving ISIL out of\n\n1127\n00:54:52,722 --> 00:54:54,724\nsignificant portions of\nSyria, particularly along\n\n1128\n00:54:54,724 --> 00:54:55,725\nthe border with Turkey.\n\n1129\n00:54:55,725 --> 00:54:57,727\nSo there's been important\nprogress that's been made\n\n1130\n00:54:57,727 --> 00:55:02,732\nand we're going to continue\nto consult closely and work\n\n1131\n00:55:12,842 --> 00:55:17,047\neffectively with the Turks,\nwho are rightly concerned\n\n1132\n00:55:17,047 --> 00:55:19,049\nabout the security situation\nalong their border.\n\n1133\n00:55:19,049 --> 00:55:22,118\nThe Press: But there is a\nperception among other\n\n1134\n00:55:22,118 --> 00:55:24,120\ndepartments in Washington\nthat when it comes to the\n\n1135\n00:55:24,120 --> 00:55:26,656\nconversation of a safe zone\nthat while there are those\n\n1136\n00:55:26,656 --> 00:55:28,992\nwho support it, that\nconversation ends when it\n\n1137\n00:55:28,992 --> 00:55:30,493\ngets to the White House.\n\n1138\n00:55:30,493 --> 00:55:34,064\nIs the White House in any\nway revisiting any of those\n\n1139\n00:55:34,064 --> 00:55:35,865\npolicy decisions on Syria?\n\n1140\n00:55:35,865 --> 00:55:38,601\nMr. Earnest: Well, I guess\nto take on that question\n\n1141\n00:55:38,601 --> 00:55:42,205\ndirectly, because of some of\nthe challenges that are\n\n1142\n00:55:42,205 --> 00:55:45,108\nposed by Syria, particularly\nwhen it comes to trying to\n\n1143\n00:55:45,108 --> 00:55:47,510\nsee the kind of political\noutcome that we would like\n\n1144\n00:55:47,510 --> 00:55:49,512\nto see there and to\nstabilize the security\n\n1145\n00:55:49,512 --> 00:55:52,082\nsituation, that's obviously\nbeen very challenging.\n\n1146\n00:55:52,082 --> 00:55:54,884\nAnd we haven't made as much\nprogress in pursuit of those\n\n1147\n00:55:54,884 --> 00:55:56,653\ngoals as we would like to\nsee.\n\n1148\n00:55:56,653 --> 00:55:59,089\nAnd that's why the President\nis always pushing his team\n\n1149\n00:55:59,089 --> 00:56:04,828\nto bring him new ideas and\nto get an updated assessment\n\n1150\n00:56:04,828 --> 00:56:07,530\nof what's exactly happening\non the ground so that if\n\n1151\n00:56:07,530 --> 00:56:10,400\nthere are policy changes\nthat need to be implemented,\n\n1152\n00:56:10,400 --> 00:56:12,869\nthat those changes can be\nimplemented as soon as\n\n1153\n00:56:12,869 --> 00:56:13,870\npossible.\n\n1154\n00:56:13,870 --> 00:56:17,807\nSo I certainly wouldn't rule\nout that there would be\n\n1155\n00:56:17,807 --> 00:56:20,577\nfurther refinements of our\nstrategy based on what we\n\n1156\n00:56:20,577 --> 00:56:22,479\nknow is working on the\nground.\n\n1157\n00:56:22,479 --> 00:56:25,048\nAnd, again, I think that\nwe've seen that already by\n\n1158\n00:56:25,048 --> 00:56:27,550\nenlisting a significantly\ngreater contribution from\n\n1159\n00:56:27,550 --> 00:56:29,385\nthe Turks to this effort.\n\n1160\n00:56:29,385 --> 00:56:34,124\nAnd I think that's just one\nexample of how the President\n\n1161\n00:56:34,124 --> 00:56:37,160\nand his team are constantly\nreviewing our strategy when\n\n1162\n00:56:37,160 --> 00:56:41,798\nit comes to Syria to look\nfor ways that we can advance\n\n1163\n00:56:41,798 --> 00:56:43,800\nour interests more\neffectively than we have\n\n1164\n00:56:43,800 --> 00:56:44,801\nthus far.\n\n1165\n00:56:44,801 --> 00:56:45,802\nByron.\n\n1166\n00:56:45,802 --> 00:56:47,070\nThe Press: Thanks, Josh.\n\n1167\n00:56:47,070 --> 00:56:49,572\nThe House looks likely to\nvote on a bill lifting the\n\n1168\n00:56:49,572 --> 00:56:51,040\nban on oil exports.\n\n1169\n00:56:51,040 --> 00:56:55,111\nDoes the White House have a\nposition on this bill and\n\n1170\n00:56:55,111 --> 00:56:56,579\nthe topic in general?\n\n1171\n00:56:56,579 --> 00:56:59,082\nMr. Earnest: Well, what I\ncan tell you, Byron, is that\n\n1172\n00:56:59,082 --> 00:57:04,087\nthe -- we've got a position\non this, which is that this\n\n1173\n00:57:07,157 --> 00:57:12,362\nis a policy decision that is\nmade over at the Commerce\n\n1174\n00:57:12,362 --> 00:57:14,230\nDepartment.\n\n1175\n00:57:14,230 --> 00:57:17,967\nAnd for that reason, we\nwouldn't support legislation\n\n1176\n00:57:17,967 --> 00:57:21,704\nlike the one that's been put\nforward by Republicans.\n\n1177\n00:57:23,706 --> 00:57:26,976\nAnd so this is -- so for an\nupdate on our position, if\n\n1178\n00:57:26,976 --> 00:57:28,978\none is necessary, you can\nconsult with the Commerce\n\n1179\n00:57:28,978 --> 00:57:29,979\nDepartment.\n\n1180\n00:57:29,979 --> 00:57:32,882\nThe one thing that I would\nnote is that this policy\n\n1181\n00:57:32,882 --> 00:57:36,753\nannouncement is being made\nby Leader McCarthy in front\n\n1182\n00:57:36,753 --> 00:57:40,023\nof an organization in\nHouston that is largely\n\n1183\n00:57:40,023 --> 00:57:42,392\nfunded by four or five of\nthe biggest oil companies in\n\n1184\n00:57:42,392 --> 00:57:43,960\nthe United States.\n\n1185\n00:57:43,960 --> 00:57:49,465\nSo it is pretty clear, once\nagain, where Republicans in\n\n1186\n00:57:49,465 --> 00:57:53,736\nCongress and their political\nbenefactors stand when it\n\n1187\n00:57:53,736 --> 00:57:56,573\ncomes to their energy policy\npriorities.\n\n1188\n00:57:58,808 --> 00:58:03,580\nThe fact is I think Leader\nMcCarthy has an opportunity\n\n1189\n00:58:03,580 --> 00:58:05,949\nto demonstrate some true\npolitical courage where he\n\n1190\n00:58:05,949 --> 00:58:08,651\ncould go and stand before\nthat organization and\n\n1191\n00:58:08,651 --> 00:58:12,589\nactually offer up something\nbold but also common-sense,\n\n1192\n00:58:12,589 --> 00:58:15,491\nwhich is to end the billions\nin subsidies that oil and\n\n1193\n00:58:15,491 --> 00:58:19,229\ngas companies in the United\nStates already enjoy, and\n\n1194\n00:58:19,229 --> 00:58:23,466\nactually use that money to\nensure the long-term success\n\n1195\n00:58:23,466 --> 00:58:27,036\nof our economy and the\nenergy sector in this\n\n1196\n00:58:27,036 --> 00:58:29,639\ncountry by making important\ninvestments in things like\n\n1197\n00:58:29,639 --> 00:58:33,109\nwind energy and solar energy\n-- investments that even\n\n1198\n00:58:33,109 --> 00:58:35,245\nsome of those oil companies\nthemselves have bragged\n\n1199\n00:58:35,245 --> 00:58:36,246\nabout making.\n\n1200\n00:58:36,246 --> 00:58:37,614\nThe Press: Thanks.\n\n1201\n00:58:37,614 --> 00:58:39,782\nAnd can I follow on\nMargaret's question?\n\n1202\n00:58:41,851 --> 00:58:44,821\nYou said you're constantly\nreviewing your strategy.\n\n1203\n00:58:44,821 --> 00:58:47,991\nIs there a moment -- should\nwe expect refinements in\n\n1204\n00:58:47,991 --> 00:58:49,259\nthat strategy going forward?\n\n1205\n00:58:49,259 --> 00:58:51,461\nMr. Earnest: Well, I think I\nacknowledged to Margaret\n\n1206\n00:58:51,461 --> 00:58:54,864\nthat that's something that\nhappens -- that there is a\n\n1207\n00:58:54,864 --> 00:58:59,869\nhigh-profile example of that\nexactly happening once our\n\n1208\n00:59:02,138 --> 00:59:06,509\ndiplomatic overtures to\nTurkey resulted in a greater\n\n1209\n00:59:06,509 --> 00:59:09,545\ncommitment on the part of\nthe Turks to this\n\n1210\n00:59:09,545 --> 00:59:11,514\ncounter-ISIL effort.\n\n1211\n00:59:11,514 --> 00:59:16,552\nThere was more intense focus\non that area along the\n\n1212\n00:59:16,552 --> 00:59:18,621\nSyria-Turkey border.\n\n1213\n00:59:18,621 --> 00:59:21,624\nAnd there is important\nprogress that we're trying\n\n1214\n00:59:21,624 --> 00:59:24,594\nto build on in that region\nof Syria where we've seen\n\n1215\n00:59:24,594 --> 00:59:31,601\nanti-ISIL forces push ISIL\nout of those areas.\n\n1216\n00:59:31,601 --> 00:59:33,670\nAnd we've been working with\nthe Turks to try to build on\n\n1217\n00:59:33,670 --> 00:59:35,471\nthat momentum.\n\n1218\n00:59:35,471 --> 00:59:39,042\nThat's an example of our\nstrategy being refined to\n\n1219\n00:59:39,042 --> 00:59:42,946\nreflect both the position of\nother members of our\n\n1220\n00:59:42,946 --> 00:59:46,115\ncounter-ISIL campaign, but\nalso to reflect the\n\n1221\n00:59:46,115 --> 00:59:48,117\nconditions on the ground\ninside of Syria.\n\n1222\n00:59:48,117 --> 00:59:50,119\nMike, you had a question\nearlier.\n\n1223\n00:59:50,119 --> 00:59:53,323\nThe Press: Yes, I wanted to\nfollow up on the wildfires\n\n1224\n00:59:53,323 --> 00:59:54,324\nissue.\n\n1225\n00:59:54,324 --> 00:59:56,359\nYou mentioned this change\nthat the administration is\n\n1226\n00:59:56,359 --> 00:59:58,695\nseeking that would\npotentially open up some\n\n1227\n00:59:58,695 --> 01:00:00,730\nadditional monies for fire\nsuppression efforts.\n\n1228\n01:00:00,730 --> 01:00:03,766\nThere was a letter from\nCabinet officials today to\n\n1229\n01:00:03,766 --> 01:00:04,767\nthe Hill.\n\n1230\n01:00:04,767 --> 01:00:06,769\nThere's legislation --\nbipartisan legislation that\n\n1231\n01:00:06,769 --> 01:00:09,806\nwould effect that change,\nand I know some of the\n\n1232\n01:00:09,806 --> 01:00:11,808\nco-sponsors are hoping to\nmaybe get it attached to\n\n1233\n01:00:11,808 --> 01:00:13,810\nwhatever spending vehicle\ncomes through here at the\n\n1234\n01:00:13,810 --> 01:00:14,811\nend of the month.\n\n1235\n01:00:14,811 --> 01:00:16,813\nIs that something the White\nHouse would insist upon as\n\n1236\n01:00:16,813 --> 01:00:18,815\nwell to ensure that the\nchange went through?\n\n1237\n01:00:18,815 --> 01:00:21,451\nMr. Earnest: Mike, I'm not\naware of all the details of\n\n1238\n01:00:21,451 --> 01:00:24,354\nthat specific legislation,\nso I'll withhold judgment on\n\n1239\n01:00:24,354 --> 01:00:25,355\nit.\n\n1240\n01:00:25,355 --> 01:00:28,992\nWe can look into some of\nthose details for you.\n\n1241\n01:00:28,992 --> 01:00:30,994\nThe case that we have made\n-- and I don't know if this\n\n1242\n01:00:30,994 --> 01:00:32,996\nis included in the\nlegislation -- but the case\n\n1243\n01:00:32,996 --> 01:00:36,966\nthat we have made is that\nfunding to fight wildfires\n\n1244\n01:00:36,966 --> 01:00:40,103\nshould be similar to the way\nthat funding for other\n\n1245\n01:00:40,103 --> 01:00:43,906\ndisaster responses are\nstructured.\n\n1246\n01:00:43,906 --> 01:00:47,210\nAnd this is essentially to\nallow there to be regular\n\n1247\n01:00:47,210 --> 01:00:53,716\naccess to resources to fight\nwildfires that don't draw\n\n1248\n01:00:53,716 --> 01:00:56,452\naway from those things that\n-- from those programs that\n\n1249\n01:00:56,452 --> 01:00:58,588\ncould effectively prevent\nthose wildfires from\n\n1250\n01:00:58,588 --> 01:01:02,558\nstarting in the first place;\nthat you get into a pretty\n\n1251\n01:01:02,558 --> 01:01:06,195\ndangerous downward cycle if\nyou end up cannibalizing all\n\n1252\n01:01:06,195 --> 01:01:12,735\nof your wildfire prevention\nfunding to pay for needed\n\n1253\n01:01:12,735 --> 01:01:15,171\nwildfire fighting efforts.\n\n1254\n01:01:15,171 --> 01:01:17,140\nBut as it relates to the\nlegislation, let me look\n\n1255\n01:01:17,140 --> 01:01:18,408\ninto that for you.\n\n1256\n01:01:18,408 --> 01:01:19,409\nChris.\n\n1257\n01:01:19,409 --> 01:01:21,944\nThe Press: Let me just\nfollow up on Byron's\n\n1258\n01:01:21,944 --> 01:01:23,713\nquestion about the oil\nexports.\n\n1259\n01:01:23,713 --> 01:01:26,182\nIn stating opposition, you\ntalked about Congressman\n\n1260\n01:01:26,182 --> 01:01:28,651\nMcCarthy and the oil\ncompanies who have\n\n1261\n01:01:28,651 --> 01:01:29,652\n(inaudible)\n\n1262\n01:01:29,652 --> 01:01:32,155\ncharge on this and lobbying\nvery strongly in Congress.\n\n1263\n01:01:32,155 --> 01:01:34,991\nHaving said that, your own\nEnergy Department, the\n\n1264\n01:01:34,991 --> 01:01:38,861\nstatistical arm of it at\nleast, just put out a report\n\n1265\n01:01:38,861 --> 01:01:42,265\nsuggesting that not only\nwould this not increase U.S.\n\n1266\n01:01:42,265 --> 01:01:44,901\ngas prices, there's a good\npossibility it would lower\n\n1267\n01:01:44,901 --> 01:01:45,902\ngas prices.\n\n1268\n01:01:45,902 --> 01:01:49,305\nAnd I wonder if that very\nrecent survey was part of\n\n1269\n01:01:49,305 --> 01:01:50,306\nthis calculation?\n\n1270\n01:01:50,306 --> 01:01:53,076\nAnd what would you say\nabout, then, the decision\n\n1271\n01:01:53,076 --> 01:01:56,345\nthat you made given that\nthere's a chance that this\n\n1272\n01:01:56,345 --> 01:01:58,381\nwould lower gas prices for\nAmericans?\n\n1273\n01:01:58,381 --> 01:02:00,783\nMr. Earnest: Well, Chris, I\nguess what I would say is\n\n1274\n01:02:00,783 --> 01:02:04,187\nany decision that's made on\nthis policy is made at the\n\n1275\n01:02:04,187 --> 01:02:05,188\nDepartment of Commerce.\n\n1276\n01:02:05,188 --> 01:02:12,095\nAnd so they may have a more\nspecific guidance to offer\n\n1277\n01:02:12,095 --> 01:02:15,465\nyou in terms of their policy\nor any planning that they\n\n1278\n01:02:15,465 --> 01:02:18,234\nmay be engaged in.\n\n1279\n01:02:18,234 --> 01:02:24,073\nMy observation is that it\nseems pretty clear that\n\n1280\n01:02:24,073 --> 01:02:26,309\nregardless of the merits of\nthis individual position,\n\n1281\n01:02:26,309 --> 01:02:31,080\nthat it is quite clear what\nLeader McCarthy's priorities\n\n1282\n01:02:31,080 --> 01:02:34,250\nare -- and they are the\npriorities of his party in\n\n1283\n01:02:34,250 --> 01:02:37,954\nCongress -- is to cozy up to\noil interests and to pursue\n\n1284\n01:02:37,954 --> 01:02:39,956\npolicies and to make policy\nannouncements that are\n\n1285\n01:02:39,956 --> 01:02:43,726\nclearly in their interests\nat venues where he can be\n\n1286\n01:02:43,726 --> 01:02:47,797\nsure that they see it.\n\n1287\n01:02:47,797 --> 01:02:51,834\nThe administration believes\nthat the American people are\n\n1288\n01:02:51,834 --> 01:02:57,373\nbetter served by making sure\nthat we pursue the kind of\n\n1289\n01:02:57,373 --> 01:03:03,579\napproach that also invests\nin renewable energy that\n\n1290\n01:03:03,579 --> 01:03:05,648\nwill be good for the\nlong-term benefits of our\n\n1291\n01:03:05,648 --> 01:03:10,319\neconomy, creating jobs --\nparticularly in the\n\n1292\n01:03:10,319 --> 01:03:12,889\nrenewable industry -- while\nat the same time making\n\n1293\n01:03:12,889 --> 01:03:15,458\ndecisions that are\nconsistent with the public\n\n1294\n01:03:15,458 --> 01:03:17,827\nhealth and well-being of our\ncommunities and children.\n\n1295\n01:03:17,827 --> 01:03:21,464\nThe Press: If I can also\nfollow up on the question of\n\n1296\n01:03:21,464 --> 01:03:24,767\nwhether or not it seems --\nyour indication is that the\n\n1297\n01:03:24,767 --> 01:03:27,470\nPresident is considering --\nor his staff is considering\n\n1298\n01:03:27,470 --> 01:03:30,473\ntrying to set up a meeting\nwith Vladimir Putin when\n\n1299\n01:03:30,473 --> 01:03:31,707\nhe's in New York.\n\n1300\n01:03:31,707 --> 01:03:35,311\nAnd I'm wondering if a main\nfactor in that is Syria, and\n\n1301\n01:03:35,311 --> 01:03:38,614\nif he meets with Putin, is\nthat a reflection of the\n\n1302\n01:03:38,614 --> 01:03:41,350\nlevel of urgency and concern\nabout the military movements\n\n1303\n01:03:41,350 --> 01:03:42,552\nin Syria by Russia.\n\n1304\n01:03:42,552 --> 01:03:45,521\nMr. Earnest: Well, I think\nthat we've been quite candid\n\n1305\n01:03:45,521 --> 01:03:49,892\nabout the fact that we are\nconcerned by any strategic\n\n1306\n01:03:49,892 --> 01:03:55,097\ndecision by Russia to double\ndown on its support for the\n\n1307\n01:03:55,097 --> 01:03:56,098\nAssad regime.\n\n1308\n01:03:56,098 --> 01:03:58,100\nThe Press: Is that the\nmotive -- would that be the\n\n1309\n01:03:58,100 --> 01:04:00,102\nmain motivating factor in\ndeciding to have this\n\n1310\n01:04:00,102 --> 01:04:01,070\nmeeting?\n\n1311\n01:04:01,070 --> 01:04:03,072\nMr. Earnest: Well, if a\nmeeting is scheduled, we'll\n\n1312\n01:04:03,072 --> 01:04:05,074\nbe able to describe to you\nwhy the meeting occurred and\n\n1313\n01:04:05,074 --> 01:04:07,076\neven maybe give you a sense\nof what the conversation was\n\n1314\n01:04:07,076 --> 01:04:08,077\nlike after it's occurred.\n\n1315\n01:04:08,077 --> 01:04:10,079\nThe Press: And just a quick\nfollow-up on the refugees,\n\n1316\n01:04:10,079 --> 01:04:11,914\nbecause last week the U.N.\n\n1317\n01:04:11,914 --> 01:04:14,450\nand the folks who were on\nthe background call talked\n\n1318\n01:04:14,450 --> 01:04:18,287\nabout the larger plan that\nshould be in place by\n\n1319\n01:04:18,287 --> 01:04:21,390\nOctober 1st coming --\npotentially in the coming\n\n1320\n01:04:21,390 --> 01:04:22,391\ndays.\n\n1321\n01:04:22,391 --> 01:04:24,093\nDo you expect that this\nweek?\n\n1322\n01:04:24,093 --> 01:04:27,563\nMr. Earnest: Tell me which\nplan you're talking about\n\n1323\n01:04:27,563 --> 01:04:28,564\nhere.\n\n1324\n01:04:28,564 --> 01:04:32,168\nThe Press: So you announced\nthat 10,000 that was the new\n\n1325\n01:04:32,168 --> 01:04:35,638\nnumber that the President\nsuggested, but there was a\n\n1326\n01:04:35,638 --> 01:04:39,508\nlarger plan about funding --\nfor example, versus the $4\n\n1327\n01:04:39,508 --> 01:04:41,744\nbillion that happened this\nyear.\n\n1328\n01:04:41,744 --> 01:04:44,180\nAny changes that there might\nbe in terms of process and\n\n1329\n01:04:44,180 --> 01:04:45,181\nthat kind of thing?\n\n1330\n01:04:45,181 --> 01:04:46,182\nMr. Earnest: I see.\n\n1331\n01:04:46,182 --> 01:04:48,284\nThe Press: And you\nsuggested, as did people on\n\n1332\n01:04:48,284 --> 01:04:50,519\nthe background call, that\nthat plan should be coming\n\n1333\n01:04:50,519 --> 01:04:51,520\nin the coming days.\n\n1334\n01:04:51,520 --> 01:04:54,457\nAnd I just wondered if you\nhad any update on when that\n\n1335\n01:04:54,457 --> 01:04:55,458\nmight happen.\n\n1336\n01:04:55,458 --> 01:04:57,493\nMr. Earnest: The national\nsecurity officials who are\n\n1337\n01:04:57,493 --> 01:04:59,495\nconsidering this policy and\nconsidering a range of\n\n1338\n01:04:59,495 --> 01:05:02,565\noptions for scaling up our\nresponse to the refugee\n\n1339\n01:05:02,565 --> 01:05:05,768\nsituation in Europe continue\nto work urgently on this\n\n1340\n01:05:05,768 --> 01:05:07,770\npolicy matter, and I don't\nhave an update for you in\n\n1341\n01:05:07,770 --> 01:05:08,804\nterms of the timing.\n\n1342\n01:05:08,804 --> 01:05:09,805\nAndrew.\n\n1343\n01:05:09,805 --> 01:05:10,840\nThe Press: Thanks, Josh.\n\n1344\n01:05:10,840 --> 01:05:14,877\nThe Guardian in the UK this\nmorning was quoting Martti\n\n1345\n01:05:14,877 --> 01:05:17,313\nAhtisaari, the former\nFinnish President and\n\n1346\n01:05:17,313 --> 01:05:18,314\ninternational\n\n1347\n01:05:18,314 --> 01:05:19,315\n(inaudible)\n\n1348\n01:05:19,315 --> 01:05:22,184\nas saying that the Russians,\nin February of 2012, put\n\n1349\n01:05:22,184 --> 01:05:25,821\nforward a proposal that\nwould have seen Assad step\n\n1350\n01:05:25,821 --> 01:05:29,458\ndown, and that that was\nrejected by the U.S.\n\n1351\n01:05:29,458 --> 01:05:30,459\nbecause U.S.\n\n1352\n01:05:30,459 --> 01:05:33,929\nintelligence believed that\nAssad was going to fall soon\n\n1353\n01:05:33,929 --> 01:05:34,930\nanyway.\n\n1354\n01:05:34,930 --> 01:05:38,000\nI wanted to know if that\nreport is accurate.\n\n1355\n01:05:38,000 --> 01:05:40,970\nMr. Earnest: Andrew, I'm\nhearing about that report\n\n1356\n01:05:40,970 --> 01:05:43,406\nfrom you for the first time\nso let me take your question\n\n1357\n01:05:43,406 --> 01:05:45,408\nand see if I can get you a\nresponse.\n\n1358\n01:05:45,408 --> 01:05:46,409\nThe Press: Okay.\n\n1359\n01:05:46,409 --> 01:05:48,411\nAnd on a different subject,\nis the timing of Xi\n\n1360\n01:05:48,411 --> 01:05:50,179\nJinping's visit in question?\n\n1361\n01:05:50,179 --> 01:05:52,248\nMr. Earnest: Not that I'm\naware of.\n\n1362\n01:05:52,248 --> 01:05:55,518\nI would acknowledge that we\nhaven't announced a specific\n\n1363\n01:05:55,518 --> 01:05:57,620\ndate, but I think you can\nlook for an announcement\n\n1364\n01:05:57,620 --> 01:05:58,888\nrelatively soon here.\n\n1365\n01:05:58,888 --> 01:06:00,423\nI'll give you the last one.\n\n1366\n01:06:00,423 --> 01:06:02,491\nThe Press: Thank you, Josh.\n\n1367\n01:06:02,491 --> 01:06:06,662\nDespite the cyber issue, you\njust mentioned that we see\n\n1368\n01:06:06,662 --> 01:06:09,231\nanother example today of\nU.S.-China cooperation.\n\n1369\n01:06:09,231 --> 01:06:12,835\nAnd recently, China's news\nwire reports that during\n\n1370\n01:06:12,835 --> 01:06:16,439\nPresident Xi Jinping's state\nvisit to the United States,\n\n1371\n01:06:16,439 --> 01:06:20,710\nhe and President Obama will\nlikely exhibit even stronger\n\n1372\n01:06:20,710 --> 01:06:24,947\naspiration and resolution to\ntake on the climate change\n\n1373\n01:06:24,947 --> 01:06:25,948\nissue.\n\n1374\n01:06:25,948 --> 01:06:30,152\nSo I know you probably won't\ntalk about any deliverables\n\n1375\n01:06:30,152 --> 01:06:34,390\nbefore the meeting, but can\nwe expect any new\n\n1376\n01:06:34,390 --> 01:06:37,693\nannouncement or stronger\naspiration this time during\n\n1377\n01:06:37,693 --> 01:06:40,996\nPresident's overseas visit\nto the United States?\n\n1378\n01:06:40,996 --> 01:06:45,234\nMr. Earnest: Well, we'll\nhave more details about the\n\n1379\n01:06:45,234 --> 01:06:49,038\nChinese President's visit to\nthe United States soon.\n\n1380\n01:06:49,038 --> 01:06:52,641\nAnd I would anticipate that\nduring that visit, the\n\n1381\n01:06:52,641 --> 01:06:54,744\nPresident would -- President\nObama would take the\n\n1382\n01:06:54,744 --> 01:06:57,980\nopportunity to discuss with\nPresident Xi additional\n\n1383\n01:06:57,980 --> 01:07:00,516\nopportunities for the United\nStates and China to\n\n1384\n01:07:00,516 --> 01:07:03,352\ncooperate when it comes to\ncutting carbon pollution.\n\n1385\n01:07:03,352 --> 01:07:05,588\nYou'll recall that during\nPresident Obama's historic\n\n1386\n01:07:05,588 --> 01:07:10,025\nvisit to China last fall,\nthere was a joint commitment\n\n1387\n01:07:10,025 --> 01:07:12,094\nthat was made by both\nleaders on the part of both\n\n1388\n01:07:12,094 --> 01:07:16,198\ntheir countries to take a\nserious step to cutting\n\n1389\n01:07:16,198 --> 01:07:17,199\ncarbon pollution.\n\n1390\n01:07:17,199 --> 01:07:20,336\nAnd ultimately that led to\nChina making the historic\n\n1391\n01:07:20,336 --> 01:07:24,974\ncommitment to peak or cap\ntheir carbon pollution on\n\n1392\n01:07:24,974 --> 01:07:26,342\naround 2030.\n\n1393\n01:07:26,342 --> 01:07:28,310\nAnd some of the\nannouncements that we've\n\n1394\n01:07:28,310 --> 01:07:33,315\nseen today from Chinese\ncities and provinces would\n\n1395\n01:07:35,384 --> 01:07:38,254\nactually indicate that that\npeaking may occur before\n\n1396\n01:07:38,254 --> 01:07:40,322\n2030 because of some of the\nserious commitments that\n\n1397\n01:07:40,322 --> 01:07:43,526\nwe've seen from those\ncities.\n\n1398\n01:07:43,526 --> 01:07:45,528\nI know that there are at\nleast two cities, Beijing\n\n1399\n01:07:45,528 --> 01:07:47,530\nand Guangzhou, that they\nwill peak their pollution --\n\n1400\n01:07:47,530 --> 01:07:49,598\nor their carbon pollution by\n2020.\n\n1401\n01:07:52,268 --> 01:07:54,270\nAnd that would obviously\nmake a significant\n\n1402\n01:07:54,270 --> 01:07:56,272\ncontribution to China\nmeeting the goal that\n\n1403\n01:07:56,272 --> 01:08:01,243\nPresident Xi laid out in\nChina last fall.\n\n1404\n01:08:04,847 --> 01:08:07,149\nAt this point, I don't have\nanything to tell you about\n\n1405\n01:08:07,149 --> 01:08:10,052\npossible announcements\nduring the next visit, but I\n\n1406\n01:08:10,052 --> 01:08:12,054\nam confident that this will\nbe an issue that is will be\n\n1407\n01:08:12,054 --> 01:08:14,056\nan issue that is high on the\nagenda because it is an\n\n1408\n01:08:14,056 --> 01:08:17,460\nissue where President Xi and\nPresident Obama have been\n\n1409\n01:08:17,460 --> 01:08:20,963\nable to work cooperatively\ntogether to advance the\n\n1410\n01:08:20,963 --> 01:08:22,965\ninterests of both of our\ncountries.\n\n1411\n01:08:22,965 --> 01:08:25,334\nIt's certainly in the best\ninterests of both our\n\n1412\n01:08:25,334 --> 01:08:27,102\ncountries' economies.\n\n1413\n01:08:27,102 --> 01:08:29,305\nI think, most importantly,\nthough, it's in the best\n\n1414\n01:08:29,305 --> 01:08:31,640\ninterest of our planet and\nthe public health and\n\n1415\n01:08:31,640 --> 01:08:33,742\nwell-being of the citizens\nof both of our countries.\n\n1416\n01:08:33,742 --> 01:08:37,213\nThe Press: With the\nimportant Paris conference\n\n1417\n01:08:37,213 --> 01:08:41,650\njust around the corner, how\nimportant is this bilateral\n\n1418\n01:08:41,650 --> 01:08:47,089\nmeeting to bring the world\ncloser to meet the goal in\n\n1419\n01:08:47,089 --> 01:08:48,090\nDecember?\n\n1420\n01:08:48,090 --> 01:08:51,160\nMr. Earnest: Well, China and\nthe United States are two of\n\n1421\n01:08:51,160 --> 01:08:53,429\nthe world's largest emitters\nof carbon pollution.\n\n1422\n01:08:53,429 --> 01:08:56,232\nAnd to see a serious\ncommitment from our two\n\n1423\n01:08:56,232 --> 01:09:03,205\ncountries should serve as a\nsignal to the rest of the\n\n1424\n01:09:03,205 --> 01:09:04,974\nworld that the U.S.\n\n1425\n01:09:04,974 --> 01:09:06,976\nand China are prepared to\nconfront this challenge head\n\n1426\n01:09:06,976 --> 01:09:08,344\non.\n\n1427\n01:09:08,344 --> 01:09:10,346\nAnd, again, we do that\nbecause it's in the best\n\n1428\n01:09:10,346 --> 01:09:12,648\ninterest of our planet, but\nalso because we know it's in\n\n1429\n01:09:12,648 --> 01:09:14,650\nthe best interest of the\ncitizens of our countries.\n\n1430\n01:09:14,650 --> 01:09:17,219\nAnd the leaders of other\ncountries that are willing\n\n1431\n01:09:17,219 --> 01:09:20,022\nto take a hard look at this\nI think will arrive at a\n\n1432\n01:09:20,022 --> 01:09:20,990\nsimilar conclusion.\n\n1433\n01:09:20,990 --> 01:09:22,992\nAnd that's why we've seen\nsignificant commitments from\n\n1434\n01:09:22,992 --> 01:09:26,795\nplaces like Mexico and South\nKorea.\n\n1435\n01:09:26,795 --> 01:09:29,431\nAnd we would welcome\nadditional commitments from\n\n1436\n01:09:29,431 --> 01:09:33,903\nother countries to ensure\nthe success of the\n\n1437\n01:09:33,903 --> 01:09:37,406\ninternational effort to cut\ncarbon pollution and to\n\n1438\n01:09:37,406 --> 01:09:40,643\nconfront the challenge of\nclimate change.\n\n1439\n01:09:40,643 --> 01:09:42,611\nThanks a lot, everybody.\n\n","markerStore":{"nextMarkerId":32,"markersById":{"0":{"range":{"start":{"row":195,"column":17},"end":{"row":195,"column":28}},"properties":{"type":"selection","editorId":10,"goalScreenRange":null,"autoscroll":false,"preserveFolds":true},"reversed":false,"tailed":true,"valid":true,"invalidate":"never","maintainHistory":true}},"version":2},"history":{"version":3,"nextCheckpointId":2,"undoStack":[],"redoStack":[]},"encoding":"utf8","filePath":"/Users/joegesualdo/code/node/modules/subtitle-hero/videos-srt/9_15_15-WhiteHousePressBriefing-fBNYPrlYXOM.en.srt","digestWhenLastPersisted":"29c2725b705cfe18a6567433f785a4982aef5b2d","preferredLineEnding":null,"deserializer":"TextBuffer","version":2},{"load":true,"text":"1\n00:00:01,534 --> 00:00:04,637\nMr. Earnest: Good\nafternoon, everybody.\n\n2\n00:00:04,637 --> 00:00:05,839\nNice to see you all.\n\n3\n00:00:05,839 --> 00:00:11,845\nLet me do a quick topper\nbefore I go to your questions.\n\n4\n00:00:11,845 --> 00:00:15,014\nWith two weeks left to pass\na spending bill and avoid a\n\n5\n00:00:15,014 --> 00:00:18,218\nsecond government shutdown\nin two years, Republicans in\n\n6\n00:00:18,218 --> 00:00:20,920\nCongress have shown no\ninterest in taking Democrats\n\n7\n00:00:20,920 --> 00:00:23,456\nup on their offer to join\nthem at the table to\n\n8\n00:00:23,456 --> 00:00:25,859\nnegotiate a budget that\nkeeps the government open\n\n9\n00:00:25,859 --> 00:00:28,895\nand prevents irrational\ncuts to our economy and our\n\n10\n00:00:28,895 --> 00:00:30,697\nnational security.\n\n11\n00:00:30,697 --> 00:00:33,032\nBut instead of working with\nDemocrats to find common\n\n12\n00:00:33,032 --> 00:00:35,034\nground on a budget that\ninvests in the priorities of\n\n13\n00:00:35,034 --> 00:00:38,638\nmiddle-class Americans,\nHouse Republicans are\n\n14\n00:00:38,638 --> 00:00:42,375\npromoting a plan to\neliminate access to health\n\n15\n00:00:42,375 --> 00:00:45,812\ncare for families across the\ncountry and shut down\n\n16\n00:00:45,812 --> 00:00:47,147\nthe government.\n\n17\n00:00:47,147 --> 00:00:51,017\nThis is a strategy, I would\nnote, that was supported by\n\n18\n00:00:51,017 --> 00:00:55,488\na preponderance of the\nRepublican presidential\n\n19\n00:00:55,488 --> 00:00:59,426\ncandidates at the Reagan\nLibrary last night.\n\n20\n00:00:59,426 --> 00:01:01,861\nUnfortunately, however,\nthe story gets even worse.\n\n21\n00:01:01,861 --> 00:01:03,897\nToday, House Republicans are\nproposing to make permanent\n\n22\n00:01:03,897 --> 00:01:08,802\ntax cuts for the wealthy\nand well-connected without\n\n23\n00:01:08,802 --> 00:01:11,204\noffering any relief\nto working families.\n\n24\n00:01:11,204 --> 00:01:14,240\nToday, House Republicans are\nconsidering a measure that\n\n25\n00:01:14,240 --> 00:01:19,312\nwould offer permanent tax\ncuts for corporations and\n\n26\n00:01:19,312 --> 00:01:22,348\nbusinesses to the\ntune of $400 billion.\n\n27\n00:01:22,348 --> 00:01:25,018\nNow, to put that in\nperspective, it's a\n\n28\n00:01:25,018 --> 00:01:26,753\nlot of money.\n\n29\n00:01:26,753 --> 00:01:29,656\nIn fact, it's so much money\nthat the tax cuts that\n\n30\n00:01:29,656 --> 00:01:33,827\nRepublicans are advancing\ncost five times what it\n\n31\n00:01:33,827 --> 00:01:35,995\nwould cost to replace the\nsequester for the coming\n\n32\n00:01:35,995 --> 00:01:39,265\nyear and would prevent\nautomatic budget cuts that\n\n33\n00:01:39,265 --> 00:01:42,569\nwould harm our economy\nand military readiness.\n\n34\n00:01:42,569 --> 00:01:45,405\nAlternatively, while\nCongress has failed to\n\n35\n00:01:45,405 --> 00:01:47,440\nadequately invest in\ninfrastructure, the tax cuts\n\n36\n00:01:47,440 --> 00:01:52,145\nthat Republicans are\nadvancing today are four\n\n37\n00:01:52,145 --> 00:01:56,349\ntimes larger -- four times\nlarger -- than the six-year\n\n38\n00:01:56,349 --> 00:01:59,152\nshortfall of the\nHighway Trust Fund.\n\n39\n00:01:59,152 --> 00:02:02,155\nSo this is money that\ncould be used to make a\n\n40\n00:02:02,155 --> 00:02:05,992\nsubstantial investment\nin our infrastructure.\n\n41\n00:02:05,992 --> 00:02:09,162\nOne way to quantify this\nfor you, the tax cuts that\n\n42\n00:02:09,162 --> 00:02:12,332\nRepublicans are advancing\ncost twice as much as making\n\n43\n00:02:12,332 --> 00:02:15,535\npermanent vital tax credits\nfor about 25 million working\n\n44\n00:02:15,535 --> 00:02:17,103\nfamilies and students.\n\n45\n00:02:17,103 --> 00:02:20,039\nAnd this is something that\nRepublicans have failed to\n\n46\n00:02:20,039 --> 00:02:22,976\nact to prevent\nfrom expiring.\n\n47\n00:02:22,976 --> 00:02:25,111\nSo the bottom line here is\nthat instead of giving away\n\n48\n00:02:25,111 --> 00:02:27,113\nhundreds of billions of\ndollars of corporate tax\n\n49\n00:02:27,113 --> 00:02:29,582\ncuts, Republicans should\nactually do the most basic\n\n50\n00:02:29,582 --> 00:02:33,753\njob, first and foremost, and\nthat's fund the government\n\n51\n00:02:33,753 --> 00:02:35,755\nat levels that are\nconsistent with our economic\n\n52\n00:02:35,755 --> 00:02:37,757\nand national\nsecurity priorities.\n\n53\n00:02:37,757 --> 00:02:39,125\nThey should do that on time.\n\n54\n00:02:39,125 --> 00:02:41,094\nAnd then if they want to\nhave a conversation about\n\n55\n00:02:41,094 --> 00:02:43,863\ntaxes, we need to make sure\nthat middle-class families\n\n56\n00:02:43,863 --> 00:02:47,901\naren't left out the way\nthey are right now in this\n\n57\n00:02:47,901 --> 00:02:50,970\ncurrent Republican\ndiscussion.\n\n58\n00:02:50,970 --> 00:02:54,107\nSo, with that, Darlene,\nlet's go to questions.\n\n59\n00:02:54,107 --> 00:02:55,174\nThe Press: Thanks.\n\n60\n00:02:55,174 --> 00:02:57,477\nWhat is the objective of the\nPresident's meeting with\n\n61\n00:02:57,477 --> 00:03:00,313\nReid and Pelosi\nthis afternoon?\n\n62\n00:03:00,313 --> 00:03:02,248\nMr. Earnest: Darlene, this\nis an opportunity for the\n\n63\n00:03:02,248 --> 00:03:05,351\nPresident to sit down with\nthe Democratic leader in the\n\n64\n00:03:05,351 --> 00:03:08,555\nHouse of Representatives and\nthe Democratic leader in the\n\n65\n00:03:08,555 --> 00:03:11,257\nUnited States Senate to talk\nabout a range of priorities\n\n66\n00:03:11,257 --> 00:03:12,258\nfor the fall.\n\n67\n00:03:12,258 --> 00:03:14,394\nIt won't surprise you to\nhear that at the top of\n\n68\n00:03:14,394 --> 00:03:19,866\ntheir agenda is a discussion\nabout what I was just\n\n69\n00:03:19,866 --> 00:03:23,036\nhighlighting, which is the\nneed for Congress in the\n\n70\n00:03:23,036 --> 00:03:25,805\nnext two weeks to pass\nlegislation that would\n\n71\n00:03:25,805 --> 00:03:27,941\nprevent the government from\nshutting down, but also\n\n72\n00:03:27,941 --> 00:03:30,944\nmaking sure that adequate\ninvestments in our economy\n\n73\n00:03:30,944 --> 00:03:33,780\nand national\nsecurity are made.\n\n74\n00:03:33,780 --> 00:03:36,950\nThere is a shared priority\namong Democrats about the\n\n75\n00:03:36,950 --> 00:03:39,452\nurgency of this issue.\n\n76\n00:03:39,452 --> 00:03:44,724\nWe have said for some time\nthat a solution will be\n\n77\n00:03:44,724 --> 00:03:48,361\nyielded from a process that\nstarts with Republicans in\n\n78\n00:03:48,361 --> 00:03:50,496\nCongress sitting down to\nnegotiate with Democrats\n\n79\n00:03:50,496 --> 00:03:51,931\nin Congress.\n\n80\n00:03:51,931 --> 00:03:53,933\nWe've been quite candid and\nI don't think anybody has\n\n81\n00:03:53,933 --> 00:03:56,069\nbeen surprised that the\nadministration would be\n\n82\n00:03:56,069 --> 00:04:00,607\nsupportive of those kinds of\nconversations, but at the\n\n83\n00:04:00,607 --> 00:04:02,609\nsame time, we're going to be\nsitting on the same side of\n\n84\n00:04:02,609 --> 00:04:05,378\nthe table as Democrats in\nCongress because they share\n\n85\n00:04:05,378 --> 00:04:08,014\nour values when it comes to\nmaking sure that our top\n\n86\n00:04:08,014 --> 00:04:10,283\npriority is the safety and\nsecurity of the American\n\n87\n00:04:10,283 --> 00:04:13,753\npeople and doing everything\nwe can to expand economic\n\n88\n00:04:13,753 --> 00:04:15,755\nopportunity for\nthe middle class.\n\n89\n00:04:15,755 --> 00:04:16,756\nThose are our priorities.\n\n90\n00:04:16,756 --> 00:04:18,758\nThey should be\nreflected in the budget.\n\n91\n00:04:18,758 --> 00:04:21,861\nAnd we certainly are\nsupportive of the invitation\n\n92\n00:04:21,861 --> 00:04:24,097\nthat Democrats in the House\nand Senate have extended to\n\n93\n00:04:24,097 --> 00:04:26,833\nRepublicans in the House and\nSenate to sit down and talk\n\n94\n00:04:26,833 --> 00:04:28,167\nthis through.\n\n95\n00:04:28,167 --> 00:04:30,169\nSo this will be an\nopportunity for the\n\n96\n00:04:30,169 --> 00:04:34,007\nPresident to discuss that\neffort with Leader Reid and\n\n97\n00:04:34,007 --> 00:04:35,308\nLeader Pelosi\nthis afternoon.\n\n98\n00:04:35,308 --> 00:04:37,310\nThe Press: Should he sit\ndown also with Speaker\n\n99\n00:04:37,310 --> 00:04:39,412\nBoehner and Leader\nMcConnell at some point?\n\n100\n00:04:39,412 --> 00:04:41,180\nDo you anticipate\nthat he'll do that?\n\n101\n00:04:41,180 --> 00:04:43,716\nAnd why is he having a\nmeeting with Reid and Pelosi\n\n102\n00:04:43,716 --> 00:04:44,984\ntoday, not the Republicans?\n\n103\n00:04:44,984 --> 00:04:47,920\nMr. Earnest: Well, I think\nto answer the question very\n\n104\n00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:51,024\ndirectly is Republicans\nin Congress should be\n\n105\n00:04:51,024 --> 00:04:53,626\nnegotiating with\nDemocrats in Congress.\n\n106\n00:04:53,626 --> 00:04:58,364\nThat has been the principle\nthat we have supported for\n\n107\n00:04:58,364 --> 00:05:01,868\nquite some time, principally\nbecause it is the path\n\n108\n00:05:01,868 --> 00:05:03,269\nto success.\n\n109\n00:05:03,269 --> 00:05:06,973\nIn 2013, the last time that\nwe faced a budget showdown\n\n110\n00:05:06,973 --> 00:05:10,476\nlike this, Republicans\ndid engineer a successful\n\n111\n00:05:10,476 --> 00:05:12,478\nshutdown of the federal\ngovernment for two and a\n\n112\n00:05:12,478 --> 00:05:13,479\nhalf weeks.\n\n113\n00:05:13,479 --> 00:05:16,716\nWhen that shutdown was\nresolved, the long-term\n\n114\n00:05:16,716 --> 00:05:20,987\nbudget agreement was\ngenerated through\n\n115\n00:05:20,987 --> 00:05:23,089\nconversations between\nleading Democrats and\n\n116\n00:05:23,089 --> 00:05:25,858\nleading Republicans in the\nCongress, and that resulted\n\n117\n00:05:25,858 --> 00:05:30,029\nin the bipartisan bill that\nfor most of the last two\n\n118\n00:05:30,029 --> 00:05:33,466\nyears has allowed us\nto enjoy an end to the\n\n119\n00:05:33,466 --> 00:05:36,502\nbudgetary brinksmanship\nRepublicans seem to\n\n120\n00:05:36,502 --> 00:05:40,039\nsalivate over.\n\n121\n00:05:40,039 --> 00:05:42,642\nSo we'd like to see another\nagreement like that.\n\n122\n00:05:42,642 --> 00:05:45,178\nThat previous agreement\nwas reached based on\n\n123\n00:05:45,178 --> 00:05:47,180\nnegotiations between\nDemocrats and Republicans in\n\n124\n00:05:47,180 --> 00:05:49,849\nCongress, and we believe\nthat's how it should be\n\n125\n00:05:49,849 --> 00:05:51,551\nresolved this time.\n\n126\n00:05:51,551 --> 00:05:55,154\nThat said, I wouldn't rule\nout future conversations\n\n127\n00:05:55,154 --> 00:05:57,290\nbetween the President\nand some Republicans in\n\n128\n00:05:57,290 --> 00:06:01,728\nCongress, including the\nRepublican leaders.\n\n129\n00:06:01,728 --> 00:06:03,696\nBut at this point, the next\nconversation that needs to\n\n130\n00:06:03,696 --> 00:06:05,698\noccur is between Democrats\nand Republicans in the Congress.\n\n131\n00:06:05,698 --> 00:06:07,700\nDemocrats are ready for\nthat conversation, but\n\n132\n00:06:07,700 --> 00:06:09,969\nRepublicans have rebuffed\nthose overtures for months.\n\n133\n00:06:09,969 --> 00:06:15,675\nThe Press: Switching topics,\nthe House Energy Committee\n\n134\n00:06:15,675 --> 00:06:19,312\npassed a bill today to end\nthe ban on oil exports and\n\n135\n00:06:19,312 --> 00:06:21,481\nyou said the White House\ndoesn't support\n\n136\n00:06:21,481 --> 00:06:22,915\nthat legislation.\n\n137\n00:06:22,915 --> 00:06:24,884\nNow that it's starting to\nmove through the process,\n\n138\n00:06:24,884 --> 00:06:27,587\ncan you say whether that's\nsomething the President\n\n139\n00:06:27,587 --> 00:06:29,756\nwould veto if it ends\nup getting to his desk?\n\n140\n00:06:29,756 --> 00:06:31,124\nBecause there is a lot of\nsupport for it in both\n\n141\n00:06:31,124 --> 00:06:32,759\nhouses of Congress.\n\n142\n00:06:32,759 --> 00:06:34,594\nMr. Earnest: Well, I don't\nhave a specific veto threat\n\n143\n00:06:34,594 --> 00:06:35,695\nto offer at this point.\n\n144\n00:06:35,695 --> 00:06:39,565\nBut our position on this\nbill is crystal- clear.\n\n145\n00:06:39,565 --> 00:06:41,067\nThe Press: Thanks.\n\n146\n00:06:41,067 --> 00:06:42,668\nMr. Earnest: Julia.\n\n147\n00:06:42,668 --> 00:06:43,803\nThe Press: Thanks, Josh.\n\n148\n00:06:43,803 --> 00:06:47,306\nThe Syrian air force has\nlaunched an air campaign\n\n149\n00:06:47,306 --> 00:06:51,144\nagainst the Islamic\nState-held city of Raqqa.\n\n150\n00:06:51,144 --> 00:06:53,746\nAnd is there any kind of\ncoordination between the\n\n151\n00:06:53,746 --> 00:06:56,949\nU.S.-led coalition against\nthe Islamic State and the\n\n152\n00:06:56,949 --> 00:07:00,153\nAssad government when they\nhave a shared goal here?\n\n153\n00:07:00,153 --> 00:07:05,525\nMr. Earnest: Well, Julia,\nwe have made clear from the\n\n154\n00:07:05,525 --> 00:07:12,165\nbeginning of our actions\ninside of Syria that it was\n\n155\n00:07:12,165 --> 00:07:15,368\nthe responsibility of the\nSyrian government to not\n\n156\n00:07:15,368 --> 00:07:18,571\ninterfere in our activities.\n\n157\n00:07:18,571 --> 00:07:22,341\nThe fact is the United\nStates and our coalition\n\n158\n00:07:22,341 --> 00:07:27,046\npartners hold the Assad\nregime responsible for the\n\n159\n00:07:27,046 --> 00:07:30,349\ndramatic growth that we've\nseen in ISIL over the last\n\n160\n00:07:30,349 --> 00:07:31,551\nyear and a half or so.\n\n161\n00:07:31,551 --> 00:07:34,387\nIt's because of Bashar\nal-Assad's failed leadership\n\n162\n00:07:34,387 --> 00:07:38,858\ninside of Syria that that\nnation has ruptured and\n\n163\n00:07:38,858 --> 00:07:43,596\ncreated an opportunity for\nextremists of a variety of\n\n164\n00:07:43,596 --> 00:07:48,701\nflavors to establish\na foothold in Syria.\n\n165\n00:07:48,701 --> 00:07:52,438\nNo one has been able to as\nsuccessfully exploit that\n\n166\n00:07:52,438 --> 00:07:56,676\nopening as the\nextremists in ISIL.\n\n167\n00:07:56,676 --> 00:08:02,648\nSo we believe the thing that\nwould do the most to advance\n\n168\n00:08:07,153 --> 00:08:11,424\nour strategy to degrade and\nultimately destroy ISIL is\n\n169\n00:08:11,424 --> 00:08:15,094\nfor Assad to leave power so\nthat we can see the kind of\n\n170\n00:08:15,094 --> 00:08:18,764\npolitical leadership inside\nof Syria that would restore\n\n171\n00:08:18,764 --> 00:08:23,569\nat least some semblance of\nstability to that country,\n\n172\n00:08:23,569 --> 00:08:26,606\nthat would make it much\nmore difficult for ISIL to\n\n173\n00:08:26,606 --> 00:08:29,876\noperate and would enhance\nour efforts to degrade and\n\n174\n00:08:29,876 --> 00:08:30,743\nultimately destroy them.\n\n175\n00:08:30,743 --> 00:08:31,911\nThe Press: Right.\n\n176\n00:08:31,911 --> 00:08:33,880\nBut is there any kind of\ncommunication even through a\n\n177\n00:08:33,880 --> 00:08:35,114\nthird country?\n\n178\n00:08:35,114 --> 00:08:38,384\nWhen you have two different\nparties carrying out an air\n\n179\n00:08:38,384 --> 00:08:40,786\ncampaign on the same force\nin the same city -- is there\n\n180\n00:08:40,786 --> 00:08:44,457\nany kind of communication\nperhaps through another party?\n\n181\n00:08:44,457 --> 00:08:46,592\nMr. Earnest: Well, I\ndon't have any specific\n\n182\n00:08:46,592 --> 00:08:48,995\nconversations to tell you\nabout, other than the kinds\n\n183\n00:08:48,995 --> 00:08:52,098\nof conversations that date\nback to the very beginning\n\n184\n00:08:52,098 --> 00:08:57,303\nof our military airstrikes,\nthis military air campaign\n\n185\n00:08:57,303 --> 00:09:00,072\nthat began in Syria a\nlittle over a year ago now.\n\n186\n00:09:00,072 --> 00:09:03,009\nAt that point, the United\nStates and our coalition\n\n187\n00:09:03,009 --> 00:09:05,011\npartners made clear to the\nSyrians that they shouldn't\n\n188\n00:09:05,011 --> 00:09:07,013\ninterfere in those\nefforts, and they haven't.\n\n189\n00:09:07,013 --> 00:09:10,516\nThe Press: I know that you\nand the President have\n\n190\n00:09:10,516 --> 00:09:14,020\ndeclined to weigh in on last\nnight's debate, but I did\n\n191\n00:09:14,020 --> 00:09:17,990\nnotice that the White House\nput out three statements\n\n192\n00:09:17,990 --> 00:09:23,062\nright at the beginning\nof the second prime-time debate.\n\n193\n00:09:23,062 --> 00:09:27,833\nTwo were veto threats on\nPlanned Parenthood and a new\n\n194\n00:09:27,833 --> 00:09:30,002\nprocess for approving\nprojects -- in other words,\n\n195\n00:09:30,002 --> 00:09:32,371\nan opposition to Lawsuit\nAbuse Reduction Act.\n\n196\n00:09:32,371 --> 00:09:36,208\nWas that at all timed to\nhave the White House view\n\n197\n00:09:36,208 --> 00:09:39,245\nout there at the same\ntime as the debates?\n\n198\n00:09:39,245 --> 00:09:41,213\nSpecifically the one\nabout Planned Parenthood.\n\n199\n00:09:41,213 --> 00:09:42,214\nMr. Earnest: It was not.\n\n200\n00:09:42,214 --> 00:09:45,451\nI think those news releases\nwere part of the daily\n\n201\n00:09:45,451 --> 00:09:48,354\nrhythm of news coverage\nhere at the White House,\n\n202\n00:09:48,354 --> 00:09:50,856\nsomething that you're quite\nfamiliar with after being\n\n203\n00:09:50,856 --> 00:09:51,424\nhere for a while now.\n\n204\n00:09:51,424 --> 00:09:53,159\nJim.\n\n205\n00:09:53,159 --> 00:09:56,929\nThe Press: Josh, you said\nthat the President was not\n\n206\n00:09:56,929 --> 00:09:59,332\ngoing to watch the\ndebate last night.\n\n207\n00:09:59,332 --> 00:10:01,500\nDoes he have any general\nimpressions of what he saw\n\n208\n00:10:01,500 --> 00:10:04,971\nlast night in clips, in the\ncoverage, and what he\n\n209\n00:10:04,971 --> 00:10:05,771\nread online?\n\n210\n00:10:05,771 --> 00:10:07,206\nMr. Earnest: Presumably.\n\n211\n00:10:07,206 --> 00:10:09,275\nI haven't talked to him\nabout it, to be candid with you.\n\n212\n00:10:09,275 --> 00:10:12,945\nBut I did have an\nopportunity to watch the\n\n213\n00:10:12,945 --> 00:10:15,781\ndebate, and I have to admit\nthat sort of watching the\n\n214\n00:10:15,781 --> 00:10:17,783\ndebate reminded me a little\nbit of a tough day at\n\n215\n00:10:17,783 --> 00:10:18,284\nthe airport.\n\n216\n00:10:18,284 --> 00:10:19,618\n(laughter)\n\n217\n00:10:19,618 --> 00:10:21,887\nThe Press: Can\nyou tell us how?\n\n218\n00:10:21,887 --> 00:10:26,792\nMr. Earnest: Well, you saw\na dozen people in suits who\n\n219\n00:10:26,792 --> 00:10:29,695\nwere lined up in kiosks\nin front of a plane.\n\n220\n00:10:29,695 --> 00:10:31,964\nThey seemed angry, they\nseemed pessimistic, and\n\n221\n00:10:31,964 --> 00:10:34,367\nthey're looking for\nsomebody to threaten.\n\n222\n00:10:34,367 --> 00:10:36,836\nBut they also stood there\nfor three hours, so you\n\n223\n00:10:36,836 --> 00:10:39,638\ncould hardly blame them.\n\n224\n00:10:39,638 --> 00:10:41,640\nBut what we didn't see is\nwe didn't see a lot of the\n\n225\n00:10:41,640 --> 00:10:47,847\nsunny optimism that was\ntypical of the President\n\n226\n00:10:47,847 --> 00:10:49,582\nwhose library they stood in.\n\n227\n00:10:49,582 --> 00:10:53,452\nAnd we also didn't see a\nwhole lot of commitment to\n\n228\n00:10:53,452 --> 00:10:55,454\nthe policies that were\nadvanced by that\n\n229\n00:10:55,454 --> 00:10:56,455\nPresident either.\n\n230\n00:10:56,455 --> 00:10:59,258\nInstead, we saw what I might\ndescribe as an odd nostalgia\n\n231\n00:10:59,258 --> 00:11:01,694\nfor the George W. Bush era.\n\n232\n00:11:01,694 --> 00:11:04,163\nThis is an era that was\ncharacterized by a rush to\n\n233\n00:11:04,163 --> 00:11:07,867\nwar and economic policies\nthat nearly led us into a\n\n234\n00:11:07,867 --> 00:11:12,038\nfinancial abyss, only\nrivaling the scale of the\n\n235\n00:11:12,038 --> 00:11:14,540\nGreat Depression.\n\n236\n00:11:14,540 --> 00:11:19,979\nNow, the fact is, is that\nwhen then Senator Obama ran\n\n237\n00:11:19,979 --> 00:11:23,783\nin 2007 and 2008, you had a\nsituation where Osama bin\n\n238\n00:11:23,783 --> 00:11:26,919\nLaden was still threatening\nAmericans; that you had an\n\n239\n00:11:26,919 --> 00:11:28,921\neconomy that was plunging\ntoward a second Great\n\n240\n00:11:28,921 --> 00:11:34,160\nDepression; and despite\nall those reasons to be\n\n241\n00:11:34,160 --> 00:11:38,431\nconcerned, this was a\ncandidate that plastered\n\n242\n00:11:38,431 --> 00:11:41,300\n\"Hope\" on his yard signs.\n\n243\n00:11:41,300 --> 00:11:45,371\nAnd he ended up winning\nthat election and he won\n\n244\n00:11:45,371 --> 00:11:50,676\nreelection, and he's led our\ncountry back to have the\n\n245\n00:11:50,676 --> 00:11:54,180\nsafest, strongest\neconomy in the world.\n\n246\n00:11:54,180 --> 00:11:58,317\nSo I think that's a\ntestament to the idea that\n\n247\n00:11:58,317 --> 00:12:02,755\nhaving an optimistic,\nforward-looking, positive\n\n248\n00:12:02,755 --> 00:12:06,192\nvision for the country\nisn't just a good political\n\n249\n00:12:06,192 --> 00:12:09,562\nstrategy, it turns out to be\na good governing one, too.\n\n250\n00:12:09,562 --> 00:12:11,697\nApparently all the\nRepublican candidates for\n\n251\n00:12:11,697 --> 00:12:14,433\nPresident at this point have\na different strategy in mind.\n\n252\n00:12:14,433 --> 00:12:17,703\nThe Press: And speaking of\none of those candidates,\n\n253\n00:12:17,703 --> 00:12:21,240\nCarly Fiorina came away with\na lot of positive reviews\n\n254\n00:12:21,240 --> 00:12:22,775\nfor her performance.\n\n255\n00:12:22,775 --> 00:12:25,244\nBut one thing that she said\nduring the debate is that\n\n256\n00:12:25,244 --> 00:12:27,313\nshe would not talk\nto Vladimir Putin.\n\n257\n00:12:27,313 --> 00:12:29,748\nThe President has spoken to\nPresident Putin on\n\n258\n00:12:29,748 --> 00:12:31,217\nnumerous occasions.\n\n259\n00:12:31,217 --> 00:12:33,986\nDoes that sound like a good\nstrategy to the White House?\n\n260\n00:12:33,986 --> 00:12:35,788\nMr. Earnest: Well, I don't\nwant to turn the White House\n\n261\n00:12:35,788 --> 00:12:38,324\nbriefing room into the\npost-debate spin room.\n\n262\n00:12:38,324 --> 00:12:42,862\nBut I will just say in\ngeneral that the President\n\n263\n00:12:42,862 --> 00:12:46,265\nhas made the case repeatedly\nthat the interests of the\n\n264\n00:12:46,265 --> 00:12:48,467\nUnited States are more\neffectively advanced around\n\n265\n00:12:48,467 --> 00:12:52,138\nthe world through\nengagement.\n\n266\n00:12:52,138 --> 00:12:54,773\nAnd we tried a policy of\nisolation against Cuba for\n\n267\n00:12:54,773 --> 00:12:57,877\nmore than five decades that\ndidn't yield very much.\n\n268\n00:12:57,877 --> 00:12:59,879\nSo the President is\nadvocating a different\n\n269\n00:12:59,879 --> 00:13:01,881\nstrategy there and has\nimplemented some policy\n\n270\n00:13:01,881 --> 00:13:03,716\nchanges according\nto that philosophy.\n\n271\n00:13:03,716 --> 00:13:07,486\nWe've seen a similar effort\nto try to advance our\n\n272\n00:13:07,486 --> 00:13:10,022\ninterests in preventing Iran\nfrom obtaining a nuclear weapon.\n\n273\n00:13:10,022 --> 00:13:14,693\nWe believe that that\ndiplomatic agreement is the\n\n274\n00:13:14,693 --> 00:13:16,729\nmost effective way to\nprevent Iran from obtaining\n\n275\n00:13:16,729 --> 00:13:17,730\na nuclear weapon.\n\n276\n00:13:17,730 --> 00:13:20,966\nMany of our military leaders\nshare that assessment.\n\n277\n00:13:20,966 --> 00:13:22,968\nAnd that was a diplomatic\nagreement that was only\n\n278\n00:13:22,968 --> 00:13:27,439\npossible by the United\nStates and the President\n\n279\n00:13:27,439 --> 00:13:30,109\nleading a strategy\nof engagement.\n\n280\n00:13:30,109 --> 00:13:33,612\nSo it is clear that this\nis an area of disagreement\n\n281\n00:13:33,612 --> 00:13:37,016\nbetween President Obama and\nmany of the Republicans on\n\n282\n00:13:37,016 --> 00:13:38,017\nthe stage last night.\n\n283\n00:13:38,017 --> 00:13:42,321\nAnd I will say that this is\na worthy debate for us to\n\n284\n00:13:42,321 --> 00:13:46,659\nhave, and I'm confident that\nover the course of the next\n\n285\n00:13:46,659 --> 00:13:48,661\nyear or so, in advance of\nthe general election, that\n\n286\n00:13:48,661 --> 00:13:50,663\nthere will be ample\nopportunity to sort of\n\n287\n00:13:50,663 --> 00:13:53,098\nconsider the merits of these\narguments, and the American\n\n288\n00:13:53,098 --> 00:13:56,368\npeople should do that as\nthey contemplate who the\n\n289\n00:13:56,368 --> 00:13:58,370\nnext President of the\nUnited States should be.\n\n290\n00:13:58,370 --> 00:14:00,372\nThe Press: You may have\nspotted a segue, but has the\n\n291\n00:14:00,372 --> 00:14:01,340\nPresident called\nVladimir Putin yet?\n\n292\n00:14:01,340 --> 00:14:02,775\nMr. Earnest: No, he has not.\n\n293\n00:14:02,775 --> 00:14:03,576\nThe Press: He has not.\n\n294\n00:14:03,576 --> 00:14:04,710\nMr. Earnest: Not\nrecently, at least.\n\n295\n00:14:04,710 --> 00:14:07,179\nThe Press: Is there any -- I\nmean, is that something that\n\n296\n00:14:07,179 --> 00:14:08,614\nyou would like\nto see happen?\n\n297\n00:14:08,614 --> 00:14:11,450\nIs that something that\nmight be forthcoming?\n\n298\n00:14:11,450 --> 00:14:13,152\nSometimes you like to\nsay, \"Well, I wouldn't be\n\n299\n00:14:13,152 --> 00:14:14,253\nsurprised if...\"\n\n300\n00:14:14,253 --> 00:14:15,888\nMr. Earnest: I think at this\npoint what I would say is\n\n301\n00:14:15,888 --> 00:14:19,458\nPresident Putin has made\nit clear that he's very\n\n302\n00:14:19,458 --> 00:14:21,927\ninterested in trying to sit\ndown with the President, but\n\n303\n00:14:21,927 --> 00:14:25,931\nI don't have additional\nmeetings to tell you about\n\n304\n00:14:25,931 --> 00:14:27,099\nat this point.\n\n305\n00:14:27,099 --> 00:14:29,335\nThe Press: And finally, on\nthe situation in Syria with\n\n306\n00:14:29,335 --> 00:14:34,773\nRussia and the overall\ndifficulty that you talked\n\n307\n00:14:34,773 --> 00:14:37,543\nabout yesterday with respect\nto the President's strategy\n\n308\n00:14:37,543 --> 00:14:40,679\nfor dealing with ISIS in\nSyria, the four to five\n\n309\n00:14:40,679 --> 00:14:43,983\nSyrian fighters that have\nbeen trained so far as part\n\n310\n00:14:43,983 --> 00:14:46,585\nof that policy -- does\nthe President still have\n\n311\n00:14:46,585 --> 00:14:50,089\nconfidence in\nGeneral Austin?\n\n312\n00:14:50,089 --> 00:14:52,491\nMr. Earnest: Of\ncourse, he does.\n\n313\n00:14:52,491 --> 00:14:55,527\nAnd I think it's important\nto note -- and I made a\n\n314\n00:14:55,527 --> 00:14:57,930\nreference to this yesterday\n-- General Austin, to his\n\n315\n00:14:57,930 --> 00:15:01,834\ncredit, sat before that\ncongressional committee,\n\n316\n00:15:01,834 --> 00:15:07,406\ntook the oath, faced the\ncameras and delivered some\n\n317\n00:15:07,406 --> 00:15:11,710\nhard news about the status\nof one aspect of our strategy.\n\n318\n00:15:11,710 --> 00:15:18,150\nAnd that is not the kind of\ncourageous stand that we've\n\n319\n00:15:18,150 --> 00:15:21,353\nseen from those who have\nlong advocated this kind of\n\n320\n00:15:21,353 --> 00:15:23,956\ntrain-and-equip operation\nas essentially the silver\n\n321\n00:15:23,956 --> 00:15:25,591\nbullet inside of Syria.\n\n322\n00:15:25,591 --> 00:15:30,562\nThe President has long been\nskeptical of relying solely\n\n323\n00:15:30,562 --> 00:15:31,864\non this strategy.\n\n324\n00:15:31,864 --> 00:15:35,668\nThat's why he isn't, and our\ncountry isn't relying solely\n\n325\n00:15:35,668 --> 00:15:38,704\non that specific\ntrain-and-equip operation to\n\n326\n00:15:38,704 --> 00:15:40,706\nlead our efforts\ninside of Syria.\n\n327\n00:15:40,706 --> 00:15:42,708\nThe fact of the matter\nis the United States has\n\n328\n00:15:42,708 --> 00:15:47,413\nprovided important material\nsupport to Syrian opposition\n\n329\n00:15:47,413 --> 00:15:50,716\nfighters, particularly those\nSyrian Kurds and Syrian\n\n330\n00:15:50,716 --> 00:15:53,185\nArabs that are operating in\nnorthern and\n\n331\n00:15:53,185 --> 00:15:55,220\nnortheastern Syria.\n\n332\n00:15:55,220 --> 00:15:57,489\nThey've made tremendous\nprogress in driving ISIL out\n\n333\n00:15:57,489 --> 00:16:01,293\nof thousands of square\nkilometers in northern Syria.\n\n334\n00:16:01,293 --> 00:16:03,696\nThere's a range of other\nsupport that the United\n\n335\n00:16:03,696 --> 00:16:06,265\nStates has provided --\nnonlethal support -- things\n\n336\n00:16:06,265 --> 00:16:09,635\nlike MREs and medical\nsupplies that are critical\n\n337\n00:16:09,635 --> 00:16:13,105\nto the ability of many of\nthese fighting forces to\n\n338\n00:16:13,105 --> 00:16:15,674\nsustaining their efforts.\n\n339\n00:16:15,674 --> 00:16:20,412\nThat is on top of the\nongoing military airstrike\n\n340\n00:16:20,412 --> 00:16:22,715\ncampaign that has advanced\nthe efforts of many of those\n\n341\n00:16:22,715 --> 00:16:24,216\nfighting forces\non the ground.\n\n342\n00:16:24,216 --> 00:16:27,052\nThat is on top of the\nstrategy that we've\n\n343\n00:16:27,052 --> 00:16:29,722\nimplemented to shut down\nfinancing for many of\n\n344\n00:16:29,722 --> 00:16:31,457\nISIL's operations.\n\n345\n00:16:31,457 --> 00:16:33,459\nThat's on top of the\nstrategy that the\n\n346\n00:16:33,459 --> 00:16:35,527\nadministration has put\nforward to target senior\n\n347\n00:16:35,527 --> 00:16:37,062\nleaders in ISIL.\n\n348\n00:16:37,062 --> 00:16:40,065\nWe've got a couple of\nhigh-profile members of ISIL\n\n349\n00:16:40,065 --> 00:16:42,668\nthat just in the last couple\nof months have been taken\n\n350\n00:16:42,668 --> 00:16:44,169\noff the battlefield.\n\n351\n00:16:44,169 --> 00:16:46,705\nThat strategy is\nyielding some results.\n\n352\n00:16:46,705 --> 00:16:49,141\nThere is a coordinated --\nThe Press: The President\n\n353\n00:16:49,141 --> 00:16:52,244\ncan't be satisfied with $500\nmillion for four or five\n\n354\n00:16:52,244 --> 00:16:53,412\nISIS fighters.\n\n355\n00:16:53,412 --> 00:16:54,713\nMr. Earnest: Of course not.\n\n356\n00:16:54,713 --> 00:16:55,714\nI don't think anybody is.\n\n357\n00:16:55,714 --> 00:16:56,281\nAnd that's exactly why\nGeneral Austin indicated\n\n358\n00:16:56,281 --> 00:16:57,216\nthat -- The Press: Has he\ncommunicated that to\n\n359\n00:16:57,216 --> 00:17:00,285\nGeneral Austin?\n\n360\n00:17:00,285 --> 00:17:01,253\nHave they had any\nconversations where he said\n\n361\n00:17:01,253 --> 00:17:01,920\nthat's not acceptable?\n\n362\n00:17:01,920 --> 00:17:03,589\nMr. Earnest: I'm not going\nto get into any of the\n\n363\n00:17:03,589 --> 00:17:07,025\nconversations between the\nPresident and the Commander\n\n364\n00:17:07,025 --> 00:17:09,094\nof Central Command.\n\n365\n00:17:09,094 --> 00:17:12,331\nBut I will say that General\nAustin testified -- again,\n\n366\n00:17:12,331 --> 00:17:15,467\nto his credit -- before the\ncameras, in front of an open\n\n367\n00:17:15,467 --> 00:17:18,303\ncommittee, indicating that\nsome changes to that program\n\n368\n00:17:18,303 --> 00:17:21,340\nwere needed and that he\nwas going to make some\n\n369\n00:17:21,340 --> 00:17:24,643\nrecommendations\nfor doing that.\n\n370\n00:17:24,643 --> 00:17:27,045\nBut again, that is not\nwhat we have seen from our\n\n371\n00:17:27,045 --> 00:17:30,349\ncritics, who, for years,\ncriticized the President for\n\n372\n00:17:30,349 --> 00:17:33,619\nnot pursuing this kind of\napproach and suggested that\n\n373\n00:17:33,619 --> 00:17:35,721\nthat is actually the only\nthing we need to do in order\n\n374\n00:17:35,721 --> 00:17:38,891\nto solve all of our\nproblems inside of Syria.\n\n375\n00:17:38,891 --> 00:17:41,059\nSo, still waiting to hear\nfrom those individuals about\n\n376\n00:17:41,059 --> 00:17:44,329\nwhat they believe\nwe should do now.\n\n377\n00:17:44,329 --> 00:17:44,830\nApril.\n\n378\n00:17:44,830 --> 00:17:49,401\nThe Press: I want to go back\nto your equating the GOP\n\n379\n00:17:49,401 --> 00:17:51,270\ndebate to a bad experience\nat an airport\n\n380\n00:17:51,270 --> 00:17:52,571\nMr. Earnest: Yes.\n\n381\n00:17:52,571 --> 00:17:54,573\nIt looked like they had\ntheir flight cancelled,\n\n382\n00:17:54,573 --> 00:17:55,174\ndidn't they?\n\n383\n00:17:55,174 --> 00:17:56,575\n(laughter)\n\n384\n00:17:56,575 --> 00:17:58,377\nStanding there in line,\nwaiting for their\n\n385\n00:17:58,377 --> 00:17:59,578\ntickets, angry.\n\n386\n00:17:59,578 --> 00:18:00,512\n(laughter)\n\n387\n00:18:00,512 --> 00:18:02,047\nThe Press: Well, wouldn't\nthe FAA oversee that, though?\n\n388\n00:18:02,047 --> 00:18:06,318\nMr. Earnest: Some big\nmultinational company was\n\n389\n00:18:06,318 --> 00:18:08,854\nmaking them wait three hours\nbefore they could get their\n\n390\n00:18:08,854 --> 00:18:09,788\nsituation resolved.\n\n391\n00:18:09,788 --> 00:18:12,024\nThe Press: So what did you\nthink about the attacks on\n\n392\n00:18:12,024 --> 00:18:15,594\nthe Obama administration\nwhen it came to not keeping\n\n393\n00:18:15,594 --> 00:18:19,331\nthis country safe, when they\nwere talking about security\n\n394\n00:18:19,331 --> 00:18:21,633\nand foreign policy?\n\n395\n00:18:21,633 --> 00:18:23,402\nMr. Earnest: Well, you know,\na lot of those kinds of\n\n396\n00:18:23,402 --> 00:18:25,904\nattacks and charges didn't\nreally hold up to a lot\n\n397\n00:18:25,904 --> 00:18:27,039\nof scrutiny.\n\n398\n00:18:27,039 --> 00:18:29,174\nSo I don't want to get into\na situation, as I told Jim,\n\n399\n00:18:29,174 --> 00:18:31,276\nand sort of get into a\nback-and-forth with\n\n400\n00:18:31,276 --> 00:18:32,277\nthose candidates.\n\n401\n00:18:32,277 --> 00:18:37,282\nThey'll have an opportunity\nto have that debate.\n\n402\n00:18:37,282 --> 00:18:40,385\nSo they certainly have\nclaims that they're entitled\n\n403\n00:18:40,385 --> 00:18:42,688\nto make, but many of those\nclaims are not backed up by\n\n404\n00:18:42,688 --> 00:18:43,689\nthe actual facts.\n\n405\n00:18:43,689 --> 00:18:46,492\nThe Press: Moving on to\nanother subject, this is a\n\n406\n00:18:46,492 --> 00:18:50,062\nbig week in Washington for\nthe Congressional Black\n\n407\n00:18:50,062 --> 00:18:50,863\nCaucus members.\n\n408\n00:18:50,863 --> 00:18:53,999\nMany of the administration\npersonnel are going over\n\n409\n00:18:53,999 --> 00:18:57,469\nthere to speak for\nvarious events.\n\n410\n00:18:57,469 --> 00:18:59,505\nAnd I understand that Vice\nPresident Joe Biden is going\n\n411\n00:18:59,505 --> 00:19:03,408\nSaturday night to the\nPhoenix Awards, as well as\n\n412\n00:19:03,408 --> 00:19:04,376\nHillary Clinton.\n\n413\n00:19:04,376 --> 00:19:06,144\nIs there something that we\nshould be reading into this\n\n414\n00:19:06,144 --> 00:19:09,448\nthat Vice President Biden\nis going to the event and\n\n415\n00:19:09,448 --> 00:19:11,717\nnormally he does\nnot go every year?\n\n416\n00:19:11,717 --> 00:19:14,353\nHe's normally home on the\nweekends in Delaware.\n\n417\n00:19:14,353 --> 00:19:18,290\nMr. Earnest: I'm not aware\nof the specific plans for\n\n418\n00:19:18,290 --> 00:19:20,292\nthe Vice President's\nschedule over the weekend.\n\n419\n00:19:20,292 --> 00:19:21,293\nYou can check\nwith his office.\n\n420\n00:19:21,293 --> 00:19:23,896\nI wouldn't be surprised to\nhear that he is attending\n\n421\n00:19:23,896 --> 00:19:25,030\nthe dinner.\n\n422\n00:19:25,030 --> 00:19:27,366\nI don't know if he\nattends regularly.\n\n423\n00:19:27,366 --> 00:19:30,068\nI'm sure it's not the first\ntime that he has attended,\n\n424\n00:19:30,068 --> 00:19:31,537\nif that's what\nhis plans are.\n\n425\n00:19:31,537 --> 00:19:33,539\nThe President is certainly\nlooking forward to the\n\n426\n00:19:33,539 --> 00:19:35,541\nopportunity that he'll have\nto address the gathering on\n\n427\n00:19:35,541 --> 00:19:36,542\nSaturday evening.\n\n428\n00:19:36,542 --> 00:19:39,711\nThis is an event that the\nPresident has spoken at\n\n429\n00:19:39,711 --> 00:19:41,713\nfrequently, particularly\nsince he's been in office,\n\n430\n00:19:41,713 --> 00:19:43,882\nand he regularly looks\nforward to this opportunity.\n\n431\n00:19:43,882 --> 00:19:45,417\nThe Press: And he\nwas once a member.\n\n432\n00:19:45,417 --> 00:19:47,119\nAnd also, so as the\nPresident speaking about\n\n433\n00:19:47,119 --> 00:19:50,489\ncriminal justice Saturday,\nthere was somewhat of a\n\n434\n00:19:50,489 --> 00:19:52,858\ncriminal justice type\nmeeting, I understand, here\n\n435\n00:19:52,858 --> 00:19:55,460\nyesterday with grassroots\nleaders from Ferguson and\n\n436\n00:19:55,460 --> 00:19:58,130\nBaltimore -- meeting\nwith Valerie Jarrett.\n\n437\n00:19:58,130 --> 00:20:00,732\nCan you talk about that\nmeeting, and why now?\n\n438\n00:20:00,732 --> 00:20:03,101\nMr. Earnest: Well, April,\nthis has been part of our\n\n439\n00:20:03,101 --> 00:20:07,072\nongoing efforts to meet with\nthose activists who share\n\n440\n00:20:07,072 --> 00:20:13,445\nthe priority that this\nadministration has placed on\n\n441\n00:20:13,445 --> 00:20:17,316\ntrying to improve trust\nbetween law enforcement\n\n442\n00:20:17,316 --> 00:20:19,318\nofficers and the communities\nthey're sworn to serve\n\n443\n00:20:19,318 --> 00:20:20,319\nand protect.\n\n444\n00:20:20,319 --> 00:20:23,355\nIn many cases, these\nwere advocates for those\n\n445\n00:20:23,355 --> 00:20:31,296\nindividuals who have been\nvictims of police violence,\n\n446\n00:20:31,296 --> 00:20:33,332\nand many of these are\nindividuals who are\n\n447\n00:20:33,332 --> 00:20:36,401\ninterested in trying to find\na constructive solution.\n\n448\n00:20:36,401 --> 00:20:40,639\nI would also note that as is\ntypical of our efforts, the\n\n449\n00:20:40,639 --> 00:20:42,774\nadministration has also made\na concerted effort to reach\n\n450\n00:20:42,774 --> 00:20:45,344\nout to law enforcement and\nengage them in these kinds\n\n451\n00:20:45,344 --> 00:20:46,345\nof conversation.\n\n452\n00:20:46,345 --> 00:20:49,581\nI would note that the Police\nChief of Philadelphia\n\n453\n00:20:49,581 --> 00:20:51,650\nactually was the chair\nof the -- or one of the\n\n454\n00:20:51,650 --> 00:20:54,586\nco-chairs of the President's\nTask Force on 21st\n\n455\n00:20:54,586 --> 00:20:56,288\nCentury Policing.\n\n456\n00:20:56,288 --> 00:21:00,492\nAnd today, senior White\nHouse officials, including\n\n457\n00:21:00,492 --> 00:21:02,494\nMs. Jarrett, will be meeting\nwith law enforcement\n\n458\n00:21:02,494 --> 00:21:04,963\nofficials to talk about\nthis issue as well.\n\n459\n00:21:04,963 --> 00:21:08,266\nAnd I would describe this as\npart of our ongoing efforts\n\n460\n00:21:08,266 --> 00:21:11,103\nto continue to consult with\nthose who are interested in\n\n461\n00:21:11,103 --> 00:21:16,375\nthis issue as we try to\nleverage as much federal\n\n462\n00:21:16,375 --> 00:21:19,778\ninfluence as we can to try\nto address this problem.\n\n463\n00:21:19,778 --> 00:21:21,713\nThe Press: So should\nwe expect out of these\n\n464\n00:21:21,713 --> 00:21:27,452\ncontinuing meetings some\ntype of paperwork or\n\n465\n00:21:27,452 --> 00:21:30,522\nsomething to come out saying\nthis is what we gathered and\n\n466\n00:21:30,522 --> 00:21:33,091\nthis is what we need\nto implement further?\n\n467\n00:21:33,091 --> 00:21:34,860\nShould we expect\nsomething like that?\n\n468\n00:21:34,860 --> 00:21:36,895\nMr. Earnest: Well, there was\na task force report that was\n\n469\n00:21:36,895 --> 00:21:38,463\nissued earlier this year --\n\n470\n00:21:38,463 --> 00:21:39,464\nThe Press: But beyond the\n\n471\n00:21:39,464 --> 00:21:41,166\ntask force report, is this\nsomething -- because they're\n\n472\n00:21:41,166 --> 00:21:43,702\nalso listening to what I\nunderstand -- they were\n\n473\n00:21:43,702 --> 00:21:47,272\ngoing back telling Valerie\nJarrett things that they're\n\n474\n00:21:47,272 --> 00:21:49,474\nstill hearing on the ground,\nso this is beyond the\n\n475\n00:21:49,474 --> 00:21:51,543\ntask force.\n\n476\n00:21:51,543 --> 00:21:54,946\nIs there something that\ncould result or stem from\n\n477\n00:21:54,946 --> 00:21:56,415\nthese meetings?\n\n478\n00:21:56,415 --> 00:21:58,850\nMr. Earnest: Well, I\ncertainly wouldn't rule out\n\n479\n00:21:58,850 --> 00:22:02,220\nthe idea that there could\nbe some additional best\n\n480\n00:22:02,220 --> 00:22:06,024\npractices or additional\nfindings that could be\n\n481\n00:22:06,024 --> 00:22:07,025\nshared here.\n\n482\n00:22:07,025 --> 00:22:10,829\nBut the President long\nenvisioned the creation of\n\n483\n00:22:10,829 --> 00:22:14,866\nthis task force to work\nquickly to incorporate a\n\n484\n00:22:14,866 --> 00:22:17,836\nvariety of points of view\nand put forward some\n\n485\n00:22:17,836 --> 00:22:21,173\nconsensus recommendations\nabout what can be done to\n\n486\n00:22:21,173 --> 00:22:24,076\ntry to improve the\nsituation, or at least\n\n487\n00:22:24,076 --> 00:22:25,477\naddress the situation.\n\n488\n00:22:25,477 --> 00:22:27,479\nAnd one of the most\nimportant things that they\n\n489\n00:22:27,479 --> 00:22:31,083\ndid was to put forward a\ngood list of best practices\n\n490\n00:22:31,083 --> 00:22:33,785\nthat draw upon the\nexperience of local law\n\n491\n00:22:33,785 --> 00:22:35,787\nenforcement officials in\ncommunities all across\n\n492\n00:22:35,787 --> 00:22:36,788\nthe country.\n\n493\n00:22:36,788 --> 00:22:39,324\nBy sharing these best\npractices it can give law\n\n494\n00:22:39,324 --> 00:22:41,626\nenforcement leaders in other\ncommunities some additional\n\n495\n00:22:41,626 --> 00:22:46,331\ntools for addressing\nsome of these challenges.\n\n496\n00:22:46,331 --> 00:22:50,035\nAnd if additional\ndiscussions yield more\n\n497\n00:22:50,035 --> 00:22:52,037\ncommon ground and more\nconsensus about what\n\n498\n00:22:52,037 --> 00:22:54,673\nadditional best practices\nwould look like, we will not\n\n499\n00:22:54,673 --> 00:22:55,574\nhesitate to share that.\n\n500\n00:22:55,574 --> 00:22:56,374\nThe Press: Thank you.\n\n501\n00:22:56,374 --> 00:22:57,242\nMr. Earnest: Julie.\n\n502\n00:22:57,242 --> 00:22:58,744\nThe Press: Just following up\non that, can you give us a\n\n503\n00:22:58,744 --> 00:23:01,446\nlittle bit of an update on\nwhere things stand with the\n\n504\n00:23:01,446 --> 00:23:04,783\ncriminal justice reform\nlegislation on the Hill and\n\n505\n00:23:04,783 --> 00:23:07,886\nthe push to get that going\nand to get a bipartisan deal\n\n506\n00:23:07,886 --> 00:23:10,956\non that, and whether any of\nthe rhetoric from Republican\n\n507\n00:23:10,956 --> 00:23:14,292\npresidential candidates\nlinking crime to either\n\n508\n00:23:14,292 --> 00:23:17,395\nPresident Obama's rhetoric\nor to the \"Black Lives\n\n509\n00:23:17,395 --> 00:23:19,998\nMatter\" movement have in\nany way undermined the\n\n510\n00:23:19,998 --> 00:23:23,702\nbipartisan sort of movement\nthat was coalescing behind\n\n511\n00:23:23,702 --> 00:23:26,037\ndoing something on\nthat in the short term?\n\n512\n00:23:26,037 --> 00:23:28,807\nIs that still on track, or\nhas that gotten derailed by\n\n513\n00:23:28,807 --> 00:23:34,279\nsome of the presidential\ncampaign --\n\n514\n00:23:34,279 --> 00:23:36,014\nMr. Earnest: That's a good question.\n\n515\n00:23:36,014 --> 00:23:38,016\nLet me answer it\nin a couple ways.\n\n516\n00:23:38,016 --> 00:23:40,018\nI mean, the first thing that\nI would point out is that\n\n517\n00:23:40,018 --> 00:23:44,856\nthere were some candidates\non the stage last night,\n\n518\n00:23:44,856 --> 00:23:47,592\neven in the context of\nRepublican primary, who\n\n519\n00:23:47,592 --> 00:23:50,929\nindicated their support for\nsome criminal justice\n\n520\n00:23:50,929 --> 00:23:52,364\nreform measures.\n\n521\n00:23:52,364 --> 00:23:57,035\nAnd I think that probably is\na pretty powerful way for us\n\n522\n00:23:57,035 --> 00:24:00,972\nto evaluate the continuing\nsupport on the Republican\n\n523\n00:24:00,972 --> 00:24:04,142\nside of the aisle for some\ncriminal justice\n\n524\n00:24:04,142 --> 00:24:05,811\nreform measures.\n\n525\n00:24:05,811 --> 00:24:08,480\nThere has long been deep\nsupport on the Democratic\n\n526\n00:24:08,480 --> 00:24:09,648\nside of the aisle for\nconfronting some of\n\n527\n00:24:09,648 --> 00:24:11,249\nthese issues.\n\n528\n00:24:11,249 --> 00:24:13,618\nAnd we welcome and even have\nbeen complimentary of some\n\n529\n00:24:13,618 --> 00:24:16,421\nRepublicans with whom we\ndon't often agree about\n\n530\n00:24:16,421 --> 00:24:18,423\ntheir support for\nsome of these issues.\n\n531\n00:24:18,423 --> 00:24:20,725\nI mean, I'll be blunt.\n\n532\n00:24:20,725 --> 00:24:22,727\nI don't think that there's\nbeen a lot of legislative\n\n533\n00:24:22,727 --> 00:24:24,996\nwork that's been done on\nthis over the last couple of\n\n534\n00:24:24,996 --> 00:24:29,067\nmonths, primarily because\nCongress has been out of\n\n535\n00:24:29,067 --> 00:24:31,603\ntown for most of the last\ncouple of months, and since\n\n536\n00:24:31,603 --> 00:24:33,605\nthey've gotten back they've\nbeen bogged down in some of\n\n537\n00:24:33,605 --> 00:24:35,607\nthese issues related\nto funding for\n\n538\n00:24:35,607 --> 00:24:36,608\nPlanned Parenthood.\n\n539\n00:24:36,608 --> 00:24:38,610\nBut I think that would be\nanother reason that we're\n\n540\n00:24:38,610 --> 00:24:42,247\neager to see this budget\nsituation resolved, because\n\n541\n00:24:42,247 --> 00:24:49,588\nthis is, I think, a rich\nopportunity for bipartisan\n\n542\n00:24:49,588 --> 00:24:53,058\nagreement around a set of\nissues the President has\n\n543\n00:24:53,058 --> 00:24:55,493\nlong prioritized and were\neager to get to work on.\n\n544\n00:24:55,493 --> 00:24:59,798\nNow, there have been some\nconversations, but the real\n\n545\n00:24:59,798 --> 00:25:03,635\nlegislative hard work and\nlegislative negotiations\n\n546\n00:25:03,635 --> 00:25:07,472\nthat need to take place are\nstill a little bit down\n\n547\n00:25:07,472 --> 00:25:08,406\nthe line.\n\n548\n00:25:08,406 --> 00:25:10,275\nThe Press: Down\nthe line, how far?\n\n549\n00:25:10,275 --> 00:25:11,443\nIs it something that\ncould get done this year?\n\n550\n00:25:11,443 --> 00:25:14,246\nOr does the President now\nsee this as -- given the\n\n551\n00:25:14,246 --> 00:25:17,082\ndivide that's happened on\nthe Iran deal, given the\n\n552\n00:25:17,082 --> 00:25:20,252\ndivide now over the budget\nand all the other items that\n\n553\n00:25:20,252 --> 00:25:22,220\nthey have to fight over this\nfall, then it's not going to\n\n554\n00:25:22,220 --> 00:25:23,288\nget done till October?\n\n555\n00:25:23,288 --> 00:25:24,589\nMr. Earnest: Well, I\nwouldn't set a timeline on\n\n556\n00:25:24,589 --> 00:25:27,492\nit, but I don't think\nthere's any -- look, the\n\n557\n00:25:27,492 --> 00:25:30,028\nPresident recognizes that\nhe's got another 15 months\n\n558\n00:25:30,028 --> 00:25:31,496\nor so in office.\n\n559\n00:25:31,496 --> 00:25:35,467\nSo there's a particular\nsense of urgency around many\n\n560\n00:25:35,467 --> 00:25:38,203\nof these priorities,\nparticularly this one.\n\n561\n00:25:38,203 --> 00:25:42,207\nSo we're hopeful that we'll\nhave an opportunity sooner\n\n562\n00:25:42,207 --> 00:25:45,677\nrather than later to try\nto start advancing this.\n\n563\n00:25:45,677 --> 00:25:47,012\nDevon.\n\n564\n00:25:47,012 --> 00:25:49,247\nThe Press: Speaking of\nurgency and priorities, I\n\n565\n00:25:49,247 --> 00:25:51,283\nwanted to ask\nyou about Gitmo.\n\n566\n00:25:51,283 --> 00:25:52,817\nThe Pentagon today announced\nthey have transferred\n\n567\n00:25:52,817 --> 00:25:56,054\nanother detainee, their\nfirst in three months.\n\n568\n00:25:56,054 --> 00:26:00,025\nAs you know, there's 115\nleft there; 56 of them have\n\n569\n00:26:00,025 --> 00:26:02,827\nbeen cleared for release,\nbut you just can't find a\n\n570\n00:26:02,827 --> 00:26:03,762\nplace to put them.\n\n571\n00:26:03,762 --> 00:26:06,731\nAnd I remember when the\nPresident tapped Ash Carter,\n\n572\n00:26:06,731 --> 00:26:09,567\none of the -- the buzz\naround him was that he was\n\n573\n00:26:09,567 --> 00:26:13,505\ngoing to sort of expedite\nthis and clear those 56.\n\n574\n00:26:13,505 --> 00:26:16,975\nWhy is it still taking so\nlong for those 56 that have\n\n575\n00:26:16,975 --> 00:26:22,647\nalready been cleared to get\nout of there and be placed?\n\n576\n00:26:22,647 --> 00:26:25,383\nMr. Earnest: Well, Devon,\nthe numbers that you have\n\n577\n00:26:25,383 --> 00:26:26,418\nmatch with what I have here.\n\n578\n00:26:26,418 --> 00:26:29,621\nRight now there are 115\ndetainees who remain\n\n579\n00:26:29,621 --> 00:26:31,256\nat Guantanamo.\n\n580\n00:26:31,256 --> 00:26:35,126\nIt's not insignificant that\nsince President Obama took\n\n581\n00:26:35,126 --> 00:26:40,198\noffice we've transferred\n123 detainees out of Gitmo.\n\n582\n00:26:40,198 --> 00:26:42,200\nSo that's an indication\nthat we have made a lot of\n\n583\n00:26:42,200 --> 00:26:44,202\nimportant progress; more\nthan half of the detainees\n\n584\n00:26:44,202 --> 00:26:46,204\nwho were at Gitmo when the\nPresident took office have\n\n585\n00:26:46,204 --> 00:26:47,238\nbeen transferred.\n\n586\n00:26:47,238 --> 00:26:49,741\nSo that's an indication of\nthe President's commitment\n\n587\n00:26:49,741 --> 00:26:50,742\nto this.\n\n588\n00:26:50,742 --> 00:26:52,744\nI think there are a variety\nof things that make this\n\n589\n00:26:52,744 --> 00:26:53,745\nquite challenging.\n\n590\n00:26:53,745 --> 00:26:55,747\nThe first is we've seen a\nnumber of obstacles erected\n\n591\n00:26:55,747 --> 00:26:59,517\nby Congress intentionally to\nmake this more difficult.\n\n592\n00:26:59,517 --> 00:27:01,519\nAnd Republicans and\nDemocrats -- and some\n\n593\n00:27:01,519 --> 00:27:03,788\nDemocrats on Capitol Hill\nhave been pretty candid\n\n594\n00:27:03,788 --> 00:27:05,156\nabout that.\n\n595\n00:27:05,156 --> 00:27:07,892\nSo one of the things that\nmakes this difficult\n\n596\n00:27:07,892 --> 00:27:10,895\nchallenge much harder is\nthe kind of congressional\n\n597\n00:27:10,895 --> 00:27:12,764\ninterference\nthat we've seen.\n\n598\n00:27:12,764 --> 00:27:17,602\nThe second thing is that the\nPresident himself has set a\n\n599\n00:27:17,602 --> 00:27:20,005\nhigh standard for ensuring\nthat our national security\n\n600\n00:27:20,005 --> 00:27:21,940\ninterests are served\nby these transfers.\n\n601\n00:27:21,940 --> 00:27:25,343\nThe Secretary of Defense is\nresponsible for certifying\n\n602\n00:27:25,343 --> 00:27:27,679\nthat appropriate measures\nhave been taken to mitigate\n\n603\n00:27:27,679 --> 00:27:29,714\nthe risk to national\nsecurity when any of these\n\n604\n00:27:29,714 --> 00:27:32,117\nindividuals is transferred.\n\n605\n00:27:32,117 --> 00:27:34,119\nAnd I know that Secretary\nCarter takes that\n\n606\n00:27:34,119 --> 00:27:36,021\nresponsibility\nquite seriously.\n\n607\n00:27:36,021 --> 00:27:38,423\nThere's also been a\nconcerted diplomatic effort\n\n608\n00:27:38,423 --> 00:27:41,359\non the part of State\nDepartment officials to work\n\n609\n00:27:41,359 --> 00:27:44,863\nwith our partners and allies\naround the world to find an\n\n610\n00:27:44,863 --> 00:27:49,200\nappropriate way to transfer\nthese individuals.\n\n611\n00:27:49,200 --> 00:27:50,568\nAnd so that work is ongoing.\n\n612\n00:27:50,568 --> 00:27:52,570\nThe Press: -- not\nbeen more fruitful?\n\n613\n00:27:52,570 --> 00:27:54,139\nIs that -- is it a\nfailure of diplomacy?\n\n614\n00:27:54,139 --> 00:27:56,608\nIs it a difficulty in\nworking with some of our\n\n615\n00:27:56,608 --> 00:28:01,946\npartners to take those 56\nthat have been cleared but not\n\n616\n00:28:01,946 --> 00:28:04,616\nMr. Earnest: Well,\nDevon, I think for a lot of\n\n617\n00:28:04,616 --> 00:28:06,584\nthese other countries\nthere's not a lot of upside\n\n618\n00:28:06,584 --> 00:28:08,586\nto taking a Gitmo\ndetainee, right?\n\n619\n00:28:08,586 --> 00:28:11,356\nIn fact, that's why the Bush\nadministration tried to\n\n620\n00:28:11,356 --> 00:28:13,792\nsidestep this issue from the\nvery beginning and open up\n\n621\n00:28:13,792 --> 00:28:16,294\nthis prison several years\nago because they didn't know\n\n622\n00:28:16,294 --> 00:28:16,928\nwhere to put them.\n\n623\n00:28:16,928 --> 00:28:21,132\nAnd I think that is further\nexplained by Congress\n\n624\n00:28:21,132 --> 00:28:23,835\npassing legislation that\neffectively prevents any of\n\n625\n00:28:23,835 --> 00:28:25,837\ntheir transfers to\nthe United States.\n\n626\n00:28:25,837 --> 00:28:29,240\nSo it's not surprising that\nit takes -- it requires more\n\n627\n00:28:29,240 --> 00:28:36,081\nthan one conversation to\nconvince another country to\n\n628\n00:28:36,081 --> 00:28:38,216\naccept custody of\nthese individuals.\n\n629\n00:28:38,216 --> 00:28:40,585\nThat said, the reason -- so\nthen you're asking yourself,\n\n630\n00:28:40,585 --> 00:28:45,590\nwhy does any country accept\nthese individuals, and the\n\n631\n00:28:45,590 --> 00:28:47,592\nreason for that is that\nthey share the goal of the\n\n632\n00:28:47,592 --> 00:28:49,761\nadministration of\nclosing the prison.\n\n633\n00:28:49,761 --> 00:28:51,529\nAnd these are countries\n-- the leaders of these\n\n634\n00:28:51,529 --> 00:28:56,167\ncountries understand that\nthe prison in Guantanamo Bay\n\n635\n00:28:56,167 --> 00:28:58,803\nand its continued operation\ndoes serve to effectively\n\n636\n00:28:58,803 --> 00:29:04,476\nbenefit extremists\nrecruiters; that they hold\n\n637\n00:29:04,476 --> 00:29:07,112\nup the prison at Guantanamo\nBay as a reason that people\n\n638\n00:29:07,112 --> 00:29:10,381\nshould radicalize\nand join their cause.\n\n639\n00:29:10,381 --> 00:29:11,983\nThe Press: And just one\nmore, one the domestic\n\n640\n00:29:11,983 --> 00:29:12,717\npolitical side.\n\n641\n00:29:12,717 --> 00:29:14,619\nFrom this podium three\nmonths ago you said that you\n\n642\n00:29:14,619 --> 00:29:17,789\nwere in the final stages of\ndrafting this plan that was\n\n643\n00:29:17,789 --> 00:29:19,624\ngoing to -- again,\nyour words -- going to\n\n644\n00:29:19,624 --> 00:29:23,161\nshort-circuit some of the\nGOP opposition on this.\n\n645\n00:29:23,161 --> 00:29:26,531\nIs there any update on where\nthat plan is or what it\n\n646\n00:29:26,531 --> 00:29:27,699\nwould be?\n\n647\n00:29:27,699 --> 00:29:28,800\nMr. Earnest: This is the\nplan that continues to be\n\n648\n00:29:28,800 --> 00:29:29,834\nunder development.\n\n649\n00:29:29,834 --> 00:29:34,272\nSince we last talked about\nthis, the officials at the\n\n650\n00:29:34,272 --> 00:29:38,643\nDepartment of Defense have\nmade site visits to a couple\n\n651\n00:29:38,643 --> 00:29:41,813\nof facilities inside the\nUnited States to evaluate\n\n652\n00:29:41,813 --> 00:29:45,550\nhow those facilities may\nfit into our broader plans.\n\n653\n00:29:45,550 --> 00:29:48,553\nSo there is work that is\nactively being done on this.\n\n654\n00:29:48,553 --> 00:29:53,725\nAnd we are hopeful that\nwe can finally see some\n\n655\n00:29:53,725 --> 00:29:56,961\nconstructive engagement\nfrom members of Congress to\n\n656\n00:29:56,961 --> 00:30:00,565\naccomplish a goal the\nPresident set out to achieve\n\n657\n00:30:00,565 --> 00:30:03,034\nmore than six years ago and\nthat's to finally close the\n\n658\n00:30:03,034 --> 00:30:05,270\nprison at Guantanamo.\n\n659\n00:30:05,270 --> 00:30:06,271\nMargaret.\n\n660\n00:30:06,271 --> 00:30:08,506\nThe Press: On that same\nnote, is the President still\n\n661\n00:30:08,506 --> 00:30:10,375\nconfident that he can close\nGuantanamo Bay before he\n\n662\n00:30:10,375 --> 00:30:11,743\nleaves office?\n\n663\n00:30:11,743 --> 00:30:13,811\nMr. Earnest: He's\nsure going to try.\n\n664\n00:30:13,811 --> 00:30:15,813\nAnd I think that today's\nannouncement is an\n\n665\n00:30:15,813 --> 00:30:18,783\nindication that while a lot\nof this difficult diplomatic\n\n666\n00:30:18,783 --> 00:30:21,286\nand national security work\ntakes place behind the\n\n667\n00:30:21,286 --> 00:30:24,088\nscenes, that this is\nsomething that the President\n\n668\n00:30:24,088 --> 00:30:27,158\nhas made clear to his team\nthey need to remain focused on.\n\n669\n00:30:27,158 --> 00:30:29,994\nAnd again, the fact that\nwe've transferred 123\n\n670\n00:30:29,994 --> 00:30:34,465\ndetainees -- and that's more\nthan half of the detainees\n\n671\n00:30:34,465 --> 00:30:37,168\nwho were in custody when the\nPresident took office -- is\n\n672\n00:30:37,168 --> 00:30:39,971\nan indication of the dogged\neffort that's taking place,\n\n673\n00:30:39,971 --> 00:30:43,775\nagain, mostly behind the\nscenes to try to accomplish\n\n674\n00:30:43,775 --> 00:30:45,877\nwhat the President has\nlaid out as a significant\n\n675\n00:30:45,877 --> 00:30:47,879\nnational security goal,\nwhich is closing the prison\n\n676\n00:30:47,879 --> 00:30:48,947\nat Guantanamo Bay.\n\n677\n00:30:48,947 --> 00:30:49,914\nThe Press: I want to follow\nup on one of the answers\n\n678\n00:30:49,914 --> 00:30:51,616\nyou gave.\n\n679\n00:30:51,616 --> 00:30:54,552\nCan you just clarify -- do\nyou see the bottleneck here\n\n680\n00:30:54,552 --> 00:30:57,088\nas the problem being with\ndiplomacy or with the\n\n681\n00:30:57,088 --> 00:30:58,456\ncertification process?\n\n682\n00:30:58,456 --> 00:31:00,158\nBecause there have been\ncountries lined up to take\n\n683\n00:31:00,158 --> 00:31:03,461\nsome of these detainees, but\nthe Sec Def hasn't signed\n\n684\n00:31:03,461 --> 00:31:04,295\noff on all of them.\n\n685\n00:31:04,295 --> 00:31:06,431\nMr. Earnest: Well, I think\nthe chief bottleneck\n\n686\n00:31:06,431 --> 00:31:07,432\nis Congress.\n\n687\n00:31:07,432 --> 00:31:09,267\nThat's true in a lot of\nareas; it's true in this one\n\n688\n00:31:09,267 --> 00:31:10,635\nas well.\n\n689\n00:31:10,635 --> 00:31:15,340\nWe have seen Congress pass\nlegislation that they put in\n\n690\n00:31:15,340 --> 00:31:20,044\nplace intentionally and to\nspecifically make closing\n\n691\n00:31:20,044 --> 00:31:23,715\nthe prison at Guantanamo\nBay much more difficult.\n\n692\n00:31:23,715 --> 00:31:27,885\nThat's unfortunate, but it's\nthe situation that we're\n\n693\n00:31:27,885 --> 00:31:28,886\ndealing with.\n\n694\n00:31:28,886 --> 00:31:31,155\nThat is the chief\nbottleneck.\n\n695\n00:31:31,155 --> 00:31:34,692\nBut again, I think I was\npretty direct in answering\n\n696\n00:31:34,692 --> 00:31:38,229\nDevin's question that there\nare significant national\n\n697\n00:31:38,229 --> 00:31:41,032\nsecurity considerations to\nmake when considering\n\n698\n00:31:41,032 --> 00:31:42,333\nthese transfers.\n\n699\n00:31:42,333 --> 00:31:45,503\nThe President holds those as\nhigh priorities, and it's\n\n700\n00:31:45,503 --> 00:31:47,505\nthe responsibility of the\nSecretary of Defense to dig\n\n701\n00:31:47,505 --> 00:31:51,276\ninto the details of the\narrangements that we reach\n\n702\n00:31:51,276 --> 00:31:56,948\nwith other countries to\nadequately mitigate any\n\n703\n00:31:56,948 --> 00:31:59,517\nthreat to our national\nsecurity that these transfer\n\n704\n00:31:59,517 --> 00:32:02,353\ndetainees may pose.\n\n705\n00:32:02,353 --> 00:32:05,156\nAnd, yes, it's a difficult\ndiplomatic conversation to\n\n706\n00:32:05,156 --> 00:32:10,295\nmake the case to another\ncountry that they should\n\n707\n00:32:10,295 --> 00:32:12,497\nbring these individuals\ninside their borders.\n\n708\n00:32:12,497 --> 00:32:15,333\nSo that's difficult\ndiplomatic work, too.\n\n709\n00:32:15,333 --> 00:32:21,706\nBut none of that is enhanced\nby what has been an\n\n710\n00:32:21,706 --> 00:32:24,609\nobstructionist policy that's\nbeen pursued by Congress.\n\n711\n00:32:24,609 --> 00:32:26,944\nThe Press: And do you have a\ntimeline on when a plan is\n\n712\n00:32:26,944 --> 00:32:29,280\ngoing to be submitted\nto Congress?\n\n713\n00:32:29,280 --> 00:32:31,282\nMr. Earnest: I don't have\na timeline at this point.\n\n714\n00:32:31,282 --> 00:32:33,284\nThis is something that we've\nbeen working on for a few\n\n715\n00:32:33,284 --> 00:32:40,425\nmonths now, and I would\nanticipate that once we've\n\n716\n00:32:40,425 --> 00:32:43,361\ngotten that plan maybe not\nfinalized but at least in a\n\n717\n00:32:43,361 --> 00:32:45,763\ncondition where it can be\nshared with members of\n\n718\n00:32:45,763 --> 00:32:49,033\nCongress, we'll be in a\nposition to at least talk\n\n719\n00:32:49,033 --> 00:32:51,035\nabout a little bit\nmore with all of you.\n\n720\n00:32:51,035 --> 00:32:53,037\nThe Press: Quick\nquestion on Russia.\n\n721\n00:32:53,037 --> 00:32:55,940\nApart from the Putin-POTUS\npossible meeting there, this\n\n722\n00:32:55,940 --> 00:32:57,675\nproposal from the\nRussians to have a\n\n723\n00:32:57,675 --> 00:33:00,578\nmilitary-to-military\nconversation -- where is the\n\n724\n00:33:00,578 --> 00:33:02,580\nWhite House on that?\n\n725\n00:33:02,580 --> 00:33:05,616\nAnd is there concern that\nhaving military chiefs,\n\n726\n00:33:05,616 --> 00:33:09,721\ndefense chiefs sit down\ntogether would at least give\n\n727\n00:33:09,721 --> 00:33:11,923\nthe appearance of\ncollusion between the U.S.\n\n728\n00:33:11,923 --> 00:33:13,358\nand Russia?\n\n729\n00:33:13,358 --> 00:33:15,960\nMr. Earnest: Well, first,\nMargaret, the fact is -- and\n\n730\n00:33:15,960 --> 00:33:18,396\nwe have said this many\ntimes, but in the context of\n\n731\n00:33:18,396 --> 00:33:20,531\nthis question I think it\nbears repeating -- there's\n\n732\n00:33:20,531 --> 00:33:23,434\nno military solution to the\nturmoil that plagues Syria\n\n733\n00:33:23,434 --> 00:33:24,602\nright now.\n\n734\n00:33:24,602 --> 00:33:29,073\nThe solution to this lies\nin advancing the kind of\n\n735\n00:33:29,073 --> 00:33:33,778\npolitical agreement that\nwould transfer Assad out of\n\n736\n00:33:33,778 --> 00:33:36,981\npower and put in power a\ngovernment inside of Syria\n\n737\n00:33:36,981 --> 00:33:41,252\nthat has the confidence and\nreflects the will of the\n\n738\n00:33:41,252 --> 00:33:42,019\nSyrian people.\n\n739\n00:33:42,019 --> 00:33:46,557\nThat's the root of this.\n\n740\n00:33:46,557 --> 00:33:50,628\nAs you know, and as you've\nclosely covered, the\n\n741\n00:33:50,628 --> 00:33:52,630\nsignificant\nmilitary-to-military\n\n742\n00:33:52,630 --> 00:33:55,566\ncooperation between the\nUnited States and Russia was\n\n743\n00:33:58,536 --> 00:34:02,640\ndeeply affected by Russia's\ndecisions to try to annex\n\n744\n00:34:02,640 --> 00:34:05,910\nCrimea and engage in a\nvariety of destabilizing\n\n745\n00:34:05,910 --> 00:34:09,180\nactions using their military\nin eastern Ukraine.\n\n746\n00:34:11,215 --> 00:34:16,120\nSo we've made clear that\nRussia's military actions\n\n747\n00:34:16,120 --> 00:34:20,525\ninside of Syria, if they are\nused to prop up the Assad\n\n748\n00:34:20,525 --> 00:34:24,529\nregime, would be\ndestabilizing and\n\n749\n00:34:24,529 --> 00:34:29,801\ncounterproductive; that\npropping up a regime that's\n\n750\n00:34:29,801 --> 00:34:34,038\nlosing its grip on power\nin many cases only has the\n\n751\n00:34:34,038 --> 00:34:38,776\neffect of driving more\nSyrian citizens into the\n\n752\n00:34:38,776 --> 00:34:41,045\narms of extremists.\n\n753\n00:34:41,045 --> 00:34:44,682\nNow, that all being said, we\nhave long indicated -- and\n\n754\n00:34:44,682 --> 00:34:46,751\nI've been saying this for\nquite a bit over the last\n\n755\n00:34:46,751 --> 00:34:48,920\ncouple of days -- we would\nwelcome constructive\n\n756\n00:34:51,055 --> 00:34:52,523\ncontributions from the\nRussians to the\n\n757\n00:34:52,523 --> 00:34:55,626\nanti-ISIL coalition.\n\n758\n00:34:55,626 --> 00:34:56,093\nSo that's why we'll remain\nopen to tactical, practical\n\n759\n00:34:56,093 --> 00:35:02,834\ndiscussions with the\nRussians in order to further\n\n760\n00:35:02,834 --> 00:35:05,436\nthe goals of the\ncounter-ISIL coalition and\n\n761\n00:35:05,436 --> 00:35:08,940\nto ensure the safe conduct\nof coalition operations.\n\n762\n00:35:08,940 --> 00:35:11,509\nThe Press: The proposal\nfrom the Russians, the word\n\n763\n00:35:11,509 --> 00:35:16,214\n\"de-conflict\" was used\nthere, sort of suggesting\n\n764\n00:35:16,214 --> 00:35:17,849\nthat if the U.S.\n\n765\n00:35:17,849 --> 00:35:19,984\ncoalition forces and\nRussians are acting in the\n\n766\n00:35:19,984 --> 00:35:21,986\nsame space, Syria, that\nthere could be concern of\n\n767\n00:35:21,986 --> 00:35:24,956\nbeing in conflict with\neach other --\n\n768\n00:35:24,956 --> 00:35:25,823\nMr. Earnest: Surely.\n\n769\n00:35:25,823 --> 00:35:27,091\nThe Press: -- even\ninadvertently.\n\n770\n00:35:27,091 --> 00:35:27,758\nMr. Earnest: That's right.\n\n771\n00:35:27,758 --> 00:35:29,327\nThe Press: So when you say\nyou're open to tactical,\n\n772\n00:35:29,327 --> 00:35:31,863\npractical conversations,\ndoes that include this\n\n773\n00:35:31,863 --> 00:35:34,298\nproposal from the Russians\nto sit down and say, let's\n\n774\n00:35:34,298 --> 00:35:37,368\nnot be at odds here, even if\nwe don't have the same ends\n\n775\n00:35:37,368 --> 00:35:39,637\nin our intervention?\n\n776\n00:35:39,637 --> 00:35:42,173\nMr. Earnest: Well, again, I\nthink we would use any venue\n\n777\n00:35:42,173 --> 00:35:45,042\nthat we had to reiterate to\nthe Russians the things that\n\n778\n00:35:45,042 --> 00:35:46,511\nI started out here --\nthat there's no military\n\n779\n00:35:46,511 --> 00:35:49,180\nsolution, that we continue\nto have significant concerns\n\n780\n00:35:49,180 --> 00:35:54,285\nwith the conduct of their\nmilitary in Ukraine, and we\n\n781\n00:35:54,285 --> 00:35:57,455\nwould warn them against\ndoubling down on their\n\n782\n00:35:57,455 --> 00:35:58,623\nsupport for the\nAssad regime.\n\n783\n00:35:58,623 --> 00:35:59,624\nThat's a losing bet.\n\n784\n00:35:59,624 --> 00:36:01,626\nIt's a losing bet for\nRussia, it's a losing bet\n\n785\n00:36:01,626 --> 00:36:03,961\nfor Syria, and it's a losing\nbet for our efforts to\n\n786\n00:36:03,961 --> 00:36:06,931\ndegrade and ultimately\ndestroy ISIL.\n\n787\n00:36:06,931 --> 00:36:08,933\nBut we do have some of the\nconcerns that you just\n\n788\n00:36:08,933 --> 00:36:15,206\ndescribed, and that's why\nwe'll remain open to what I\n\n789\n00:36:15,206 --> 00:36:18,042\nwould describe as tactical,\npractical discussions with\n\n790\n00:36:18,042 --> 00:36:19,577\nthe Russians.\n\n791\n00:36:19,577 --> 00:36:21,812\nAnd those discussions would\nbe focused on furthering the\n\n792\n00:36:21,812 --> 00:36:26,083\ngoals of our counter-ISIL\ncoalition and ensuring the\n\n793\n00:36:26,083 --> 00:36:29,720\nsafe conduct of anti-ISIL\ncoalition operations.\n\n794\n00:36:29,720 --> 00:36:31,355\nKevin.\n\n795\n00:36:31,355 --> 00:36:32,557\nThe Press: Josh, thanks.\n\n796\n00:36:32,557 --> 00:36:33,824\nI just want to sort of\nfollow up very quickly on\n\n797\n00:36:33,824 --> 00:36:35,226\nMargaret's question.\n\n798\n00:36:35,226 --> 00:36:38,829\nYou said earlier that you\nmentioned that Syria has a\n\n799\n00:36:38,829 --> 00:36:42,333\nresponsibility not to\ninterfere with U.S.\n\n800\n00:36:42,333 --> 00:36:44,435\noperations in Syria.\n\n801\n00:36:44,435 --> 00:36:47,605\nDoes that also apply\nto the Russians have a\n\n802\n00:36:47,605 --> 00:36:50,841\nresponsibility to not\ninterfere with U.S.\n\n803\n00:36:50,841 --> 00:36:52,143\noperations in Syria?\n\n804\n00:36:52,143 --> 00:36:54,145\nMr. Earnest: Well, Kevin, I\nthink what it is, is that\n\n805\n00:36:54,145 --> 00:36:56,147\nwe've made clear to the\nSyrians that they shouldn't\n\n806\n00:36:56,147 --> 00:36:59,250\ninterfere with our military\nactivities inside of Syria.\n\n807\n00:36:59,250 --> 00:37:02,987\nAnd when I say \"our,\" I mean\nour coalition's anti-ISIL\n\n808\n00:37:02,987 --> 00:37:04,989\nefforts that are focused on\ndegrading and ultimately\n\n809\n00:37:04,989 --> 00:37:06,490\ndestroying ISIL.\n\n810\n00:37:06,490 --> 00:37:08,826\nWhen it comes to the\nRussians, we obviously would\n\n811\n00:37:08,826 --> 00:37:12,663\nwelcome their constructive\ncontribution to that\n\n812\n00:37:12,663 --> 00:37:20,471\nefforts, and we'll be open\nto the kind of tactical,\n\n813\n00:37:20,471 --> 00:37:24,041\npractical discussions that\nmay be needed to try to\n\n814\n00:37:24,041 --> 00:37:28,245\nadvance our anti-ISIL goals\nand to ensure the safe\n\n815\n00:37:28,245 --> 00:37:31,015\nconduct of anti-ISIL\ncoalition operations.\n\n816\n00:37:31,015 --> 00:37:33,084\nThe Press: Does the White\nHouse view Russia's\n\n817\n00:37:33,084 --> 00:37:35,086\nactivities in Syria\nas a provocation?\n\n818\n00:37:35,086 --> 00:37:37,855\nMr. Earnest: Well, we\ncertainly would view Russian\n\n819\n00:37:37,855 --> 00:37:40,491\nactivities in support\nof the Assad regime as\n\n820\n00:37:40,491 --> 00:37:42,493\ndestabilizing and\ncounterproductive.\n\n821\n00:37:42,493 --> 00:37:45,830\nWe've made that clear in\nprivate in the midst of\n\n822\n00:37:45,830 --> 00:37:49,400\nconversations between\nSecretary Kerry and Foreign\n\n823\n00:37:49,400 --> 00:37:50,401\nMinister Lavrov.\n\n824\n00:37:50,401 --> 00:37:53,037\nI think they've spoken now\nthree times in the last week\n\n825\n00:37:53,037 --> 00:37:54,038\nor so.\n\n826\n00:37:54,038 --> 00:37:57,241\nIn each conversation,\nSecretary Kerry has made\n\n827\n00:37:57,241 --> 00:37:58,576\nclear our view on that.\n\n828\n00:37:58,576 --> 00:38:00,845\nAnd obviously that's\nsomething that we've\n\n829\n00:38:00,845 --> 00:38:03,714\ndiscussed at some length\npublicly as well.\n\n830\n00:38:03,714 --> 00:38:11,422\nBut ultimately -- well, let\nme explain the reason for that.\n\n831\n00:38:11,422 --> 00:38:15,126\nWe believe that further\npropping up the Assad regime\n\n832\n00:38:15,126 --> 00:38:22,233\nonly serves to double\ndown on a losing bet.\n\n833\n00:38:22,233 --> 00:38:28,372\nThe Assad regime has lost\nsignificant territory in the\n\n834\n00:38:28,372 --> 00:38:30,374\nlast several years.\n\n835\n00:38:30,374 --> 00:38:33,277\nThey are isolated, or\nlargely isolated from the\n\n836\n00:38:33,277 --> 00:38:35,946\nbroader international\ncommunity.\n\n837\n00:38:35,946 --> 00:38:42,787\nAnd efforts to prop them up\nonly makes the priorities of\n\n838\n00:38:42,787 --> 00:38:46,157\nour counter-ISIL campaign\nmore difficult to achieve.\n\n839\n00:38:46,157 --> 00:38:49,994\nThe Press: Is it difficult,\nthough, to sort of suspend\n\n840\n00:38:49,994 --> 00:38:51,262\nwhat you're seeing?\n\n841\n00:38:51,262 --> 00:38:55,599\nIt seems like Russia is\npropping up the Assad regime.\n\n842\n00:38:55,599 --> 00:38:57,568\nDoes the White House not see\nthat, or do you not view it\n\n843\n00:38:57,568 --> 00:38:58,536\nthat way?\n\n844\n00:38:58,536 --> 00:39:01,138\nMr. Earnest: Well, I think\nat this point it's -- and\n\n845\n00:39:01,138 --> 00:39:03,007\nI've been pretty candid\nabout this in the past, too\n\n846\n00:39:03,007 --> 00:39:05,443\n-- it's difficult to discern\nexactly what their most\n\n847\n00:39:05,443 --> 00:39:10,548\nimportant priority is.\n\n848\n00:39:10,548 --> 00:39:13,484\nThe Russians have even said\nsome conflicting things in\n\n849\n00:39:13,484 --> 00:39:16,153\npublic about what their\nexact intentions are.\n\n850\n00:39:16,153 --> 00:39:20,224\nSo that's why we're trying\nto be as clear and direct as\n\n851\n00:39:20,224 --> 00:39:22,560\nwe can about what our\nintentions are and what our\n\n852\n00:39:22,560 --> 00:39:23,961\npriorities are.\n\n853\n00:39:23,961 --> 00:39:28,365\nAnd again, we've made those\nintentions known both in\n\n854\n00:39:28,365 --> 00:39:33,838\npublic and in private, and\nthere's no misunderstanding\n\n855\n00:39:33,838 --> 00:39:35,473\nthem in Moscow.\n\n856\n00:39:35,473 --> 00:39:37,074\nChris.\n\n857\n00:39:37,074 --> 00:39:38,642\nThe Press: Just a couple of\nthings about the debate last\n\n858\n00:39:38,642 --> 00:39:40,111\nnight, since you\ndid watch it.\n\n859\n00:39:40,111 --> 00:39:44,482\nThe numbers just came out on\nthe viewership; it was early\n\n860\n00:39:44,482 --> 00:39:46,917\nnumbers -- 22.9 million,\njust below what the Fox\n\n861\n00:39:46,917 --> 00:39:47,918\ndebate was.\n\n862\n00:39:47,918 --> 00:39:52,923\nObviously a tremendous\namount of interest, and most\n\n863\n00:39:52,923 --> 00:39:55,426\npeople would have a similar\ntake on why that is.\n\n864\n00:39:55,426 --> 00:39:57,428\nBut are you surprised that\nthere's that much interest\n\n865\n00:39:57,428 --> 00:39:59,396\nthis early in the campaign?\n\n866\n00:39:59,396 --> 00:40:04,802\nAnd does it argue -- for\nthose who have been trying\n\n867\n00:40:04,802 --> 00:40:07,271\nto tell Debbie Wasserman\nSchultz and the Democrats\n\n868\n00:40:07,271 --> 00:40:09,440\nthat maybe they should\nconsider more debates --\n\n869\n00:40:09,440 --> 00:40:12,977\nthat more eyeballs, more\nchances to get their message\n\n870\n00:40:12,977 --> 00:40:14,612\nout there might\nbe a good idea?\n\n871\n00:40:14,612 --> 00:40:17,481\nMr. Earnest: Well, again,\nI'm not sure that the\n\n872\n00:40:17,481 --> 00:40:21,318\nRepublican prospects in the\ngeneral election in 2016\n\n873\n00:40:21,318 --> 00:40:24,455\nwere enhanced by a large\nviewing audience last night.\n\n874\n00:40:24,455 --> 00:40:28,125\nI think they saw a lot\nof angry, pessimistic,\n\n875\n00:40:28,125 --> 00:40:30,094\nthreatening people on\ntheir screen yesterday.\n\n876\n00:40:30,094 --> 00:40:32,263\nNow, again, these were\nindividuals who were\n\n877\n00:40:32,263 --> 00:40:34,398\nstanding in line for three\nhours, so you can understand\n\n878\n00:40:34,398 --> 00:40:38,302\nwhy that -- to borrow a word\n-- that their persona might\n\n879\n00:40:38,302 --> 00:40:39,970\nlook like that.\n\n880\n00:40:39,970 --> 00:40:43,374\nBut the fact is there will\nbe an opportunity for us to\n\n881\n00:40:43,374 --> 00:40:46,210\nhave a very robust\ndiscussion in this country\n\n882\n00:40:46,210 --> 00:40:50,147\nabout the best way for us\nto capitalize on the really\n\n883\n00:40:50,147 --> 00:40:53,384\nimportant progress that our\ncountry has made over the\n\n884\n00:40:53,384 --> 00:40:58,222\nlast six or seven years.\n\n885\n00:40:58,222 --> 00:40:59,623\nThere's a tremendous\nopportunity awaiting the\n\n886\n00:40:59,623 --> 00:41:01,625\nnext President of\nthe United States.\n\n887\n00:41:01,625 --> 00:41:05,095\nThe United States and our\ninfluence around the world\n\n888\n00:41:05,095 --> 00:41:07,698\nis quite strong, and there\nare a variety of ways to\n\n889\n00:41:07,698 --> 00:41:09,700\nmeasure that -- whether it's\nthe success that President\n\n890\n00:41:09,700 --> 00:41:13,070\nObama had in building a\ncoalition of more than 60\n\n891\n00:41:13,070 --> 00:41:15,806\nnations to degrade\nand ultimately ISIL.\n\n892\n00:41:15,806 --> 00:41:18,409\nThere was a lot of\nskepticism in this room --\n\n893\n00:41:18,409 --> 00:41:21,045\nunderstandably so -- about\nhow broad that coalition\n\n894\n00:41:21,045 --> 00:41:22,046\nwould be.\n\n895\n00:41:22,046 --> 00:41:24,849\nBut there's no arguing\nabout the success of those\n\n896\n00:41:24,849 --> 00:41:26,851\ndiplomatic efforts.\n\n897\n00:41:28,118 --> 00:41:30,321\nWe've talked quite a bit\nabout how the international\n\n898\n00:41:30,321 --> 00:41:32,323\ncommunity when it came to\nconfronting Iran over their\n\n899\n00:41:32,323 --> 00:41:36,126\nnuclear program was going\nin a thousand different\n\n900\n00:41:36,126 --> 00:41:38,896\ndirections, struggling to\nknow exactly what should be\n\n901\n00:41:38,896 --> 00:41:41,565\ndone in the face of a\nquickly advancing nuclear\n\n902\n00:41:41,565 --> 00:41:43,334\nprogram inside of Iran.\n\n903\n00:41:43,334 --> 00:41:45,336\nThe President demonstrated\nsome leadership on the\n\n904\n00:41:45,336 --> 00:41:49,874\ninternational scale and\nbuilt -- essentially led\n\n905\n00:41:49,874 --> 00:41:56,580\ninternational unity around a\nstrategy that applied tough\n\n906\n00:41:56,580 --> 00:41:58,582\nsanctions on Iran,\nconfronted them over their\n\n907\n00:41:58,582 --> 00:42:00,584\nnuclear program, received\nsignificant concessions from\n\n908\n00:42:00,584 --> 00:42:02,753\nIran in terms of the\nconstraints that they would\n\n909\n00:42:02,753 --> 00:42:04,855\napply to their nuclear\nprogram and the kind of\n\n910\n00:42:04,855 --> 00:42:08,559\ninspections that they would\nsubmit to verify their\n\n911\n00:42:08,559 --> 00:42:11,662\ncompliance with\nthe agreement.\n\n912\n00:42:11,662 --> 00:42:15,199\nThat has strengthened the\nhand of the United States in\n\n913\n00:42:15,199 --> 00:42:16,800\nthe international community.\n\n914\n00:42:16,800 --> 00:42:18,936\nTo say nothing of the long\nlist of statistics I could\n\n915\n00:42:18,936 --> 00:42:21,839\nrecite about the inherent\nstrength of our economy.\n\n916\n00:42:21,839 --> 00:42:24,008\nOur economy right now is\nthe envy of the world.\n\n917\n00:42:24,008 --> 00:42:28,479\nAnd again, I think the way\nthat our economy has bounced\n\n918\n00:42:28,479 --> 00:42:31,248\nback is primarily a\ntestament to the grit and\n\n919\n00:42:31,248 --> 00:42:33,651\ndetermination and\ninventiveness of American\n\n920\n00:42:33,651 --> 00:42:35,653\nworkers and American\nentrepreneurs.\n\n921\n00:42:35,653 --> 00:42:39,690\nBut those efforts were\nsignificantly enhanced by\n\n922\n00:42:39,690 --> 00:42:42,326\ndifficult policy decisions\nthat this President made in\n\n923\n00:42:42,326 --> 00:42:44,328\nthe earliest days\nof his presidency.\n\n924\n00:42:44,328 --> 00:42:46,363\nAnd whether that's the\nRecovery Act, or rescuing\n\n925\n00:42:46,363 --> 00:42:49,033\nthe auto industry, we've got\na heck of a lot to show for it.\n\n926\n00:42:49,033 --> 00:42:51,035\nAnd what that means is\nit means that the next\n\n927\n00:42:51,035 --> 00:42:53,003\nPresident of the United\nStates will be very\n\n928\n00:42:53,003 --> 00:42:56,674\nwell-positioned to lead the\ncountry into the future.\n\n929\n00:42:56,674 --> 00:43:01,312\nAnd the risk associated with\nthat, however, is that by\n\n930\n00:43:01,312 --> 00:43:03,314\nreverting back to the\npolicies that were\n\n931\n00:43:03,314 --> 00:43:08,352\nchampioned by the previous\nadministration, those gains\n\n932\n00:43:08,352 --> 00:43:14,658\nare tenuous, and we could be\nin a situation where we pay\n\n933\n00:43:14,658 --> 00:43:17,227\nan economic price for going\nback and pursuing those\n\n934\n00:43:17,227 --> 00:43:20,764\nfailed economic policies,\nparticularly the middle class.\n\n935\n00:43:20,764 --> 00:43:22,766\nAnd so that's why the\nPresident feels like he's\n\n936\n00:43:22,766 --> 00:43:24,768\ngot such a big stake\nin this election.\n\n937\n00:43:24,768 --> 00:43:27,371\nAnd that's why he would\nwelcome every opportunity to\n\n938\n00:43:27,371 --> 00:43:30,607\nhave a robust public debate\nabout the future of the country.\n\n939\n00:43:30,607 --> 00:43:31,709\nThe Press: Well, then to\ngo back to my original\n\n940\n00:43:31,709 --> 00:43:34,878\nquestion, the arguments\nthat you just made, that\n\n941\n00:43:34,878 --> 00:43:37,982\npresumably some Democratic\ncandidates might make given\n\n942\n00:43:37,982 --> 00:43:41,051\nthe opportunity, does it\nmake sense for them to\n\n943\n00:43:41,051 --> 00:43:43,253\nconsider more debates, more\nopportunities to get the\n\n944\n00:43:43,253 --> 00:43:48,525\nmessage you just articulated\nout to an audience of millions?\n\n945\n00:43:48,525 --> 00:43:52,629\nMr. Earnest: Well, the view\nof the President is that\n\n946\n00:43:52,629 --> 00:43:55,466\ndebates are important and\nthey certainly do\n\n947\n00:43:55,466 --> 00:43:56,500\nattract attention.\n\n948\n00:43:56,500 --> 00:44:01,572\nAnd I know that the DNC has\nannounced that they would\n\n949\n00:44:01,572 --> 00:44:04,375\nhave six debates among\nall the candidates.\n\n950\n00:44:04,375 --> 00:44:06,944\nThe President has not\ntaken a position about the\n\n951\n00:44:06,944 --> 00:44:09,246\nappropriate number of\ndebates, other than his view\n\n952\n00:44:09,246 --> 00:44:12,116\nthat he believes that\nthey should have them.\n\n953\n00:44:12,116 --> 00:44:14,251\nAnd he's pleased to see\nthat they'll do that.\n\n954\n00:44:14,251 --> 00:44:18,122\nAnd that will be -- in\ncontrast to the Republicans\n\n955\n00:44:18,122 --> 00:44:20,124\nthat I don't think will be\nwell served, or have been\n\n956\n00:44:20,124 --> 00:44:23,694\nwell served by the debates\nthat have drawn a large\n\n957\n00:44:23,694 --> 00:44:26,363\nviewing audience -- I do\nthink that the opportunity\n\n958\n00:44:26,363 --> 00:44:28,999\nthat Democratic candidates\nwill have as early as next\n\n959\n00:44:28,999 --> 00:44:31,969\nmonth to engage in the\ndebate about the priorities\n\n960\n00:44:31,969 --> 00:44:34,938\nand values of this party I\nthink will be quite good for\n\n961\n00:44:34,938 --> 00:44:36,940\nour prospects in the\ngeneral election next year.\n\n962\n00:44:36,940 --> 00:44:38,942\nThe Press: Since you saw the\ndebate, you know that your\n\n963\n00:44:38,942 --> 00:44:40,944\nboss was mentioned\nmore than a few times.\n\n964\n00:44:40,944 --> 00:44:43,447\nLet me just ask you about\none particular instance\n\n965\n00:44:43,447 --> 00:44:48,185\nsince it has been cited I\nthink both by more liberal\n\n966\n00:44:48,185 --> 00:44:51,088\nand more conservative\npundits as one of the big\n\n967\n00:44:51,088 --> 00:44:53,457\nmoments of the night, and\nthat was Carly Fiorina who\n\n968\n00:44:53,457 --> 00:44:55,959\ndared Hillary Clinton and\nthe President to watch the\n\n969\n00:44:55,959 --> 00:44:59,696\nPlanned Parenthood tape\n-- obviously, the extra\n\n970\n00:44:59,696 --> 00:45:02,900\nsignificance given\nthe budget battle.\n\n971\n00:45:02,900 --> 00:45:06,403\nAnd she said they should\nsend a message because this\n\n972\n00:45:06,403 --> 00:45:08,972\nis about \"the character\nof our nation.\"\n\n973\n00:45:08,972 --> 00:45:11,375\nAnd I wonder if you have\nany reaction to that.\n\n974\n00:45:11,375 --> 00:45:14,344\nMr. Earnest: I don't have\na specific reaction to\n\n975\n00:45:14,344 --> 00:45:15,345\nher comments.\n\n976\n00:45:15,345 --> 00:45:17,681\nI think we've been quite\nclear about the fact that\n\n977\n00:45:17,681 --> 00:45:20,184\nPlanned Parenthood did\noffer an apology about the\n\n978\n00:45:20,184 --> 00:45:22,519\ncomments that were made in\nthe context of those videos.\n\n979\n00:45:22,519 --> 00:45:24,755\nThat certainly was\nappropriate for them to do so.\n\n980\n00:45:24,755 --> 00:45:26,723\nThe comments that were\nmade in those videos\n\n981\n00:45:26,723 --> 00:45:28,792\nwere shocking.\n\n982\n00:45:28,792 --> 00:45:32,763\nPresumably that's why those\nvideos were released.\n\n983\n00:45:32,763 --> 00:45:34,765\nSo the President believes\nthat was an appropriate\n\n984\n00:45:34,765 --> 00:45:36,767\nthing for Planned\nParenthood to do.\n\n985\n00:45:36,767 --> 00:45:38,769\nBut he does not believe it\nwould be appropriate for\n\n986\n00:45:38,769 --> 00:45:40,771\nRepublicans to follow\nthrough on the promise that\n\n987\n00:45:40,771 --> 00:45:43,440\nthey have made to shut down\nthe government over funding\n\n988\n00:45:43,440 --> 00:45:45,642\nfor Planned Parenthood.\n\n989\n00:45:45,642 --> 00:45:47,044\nThe fact of the matter is\n-- everybody in this room I\n\n990\n00:45:47,044 --> 00:45:49,046\nthink knows this, but it\nbears repeating -- the fact\n\n991\n00:45:49,046 --> 00:45:51,915\nof the matter is federal\nfunding is not allowed to be\n\n992\n00:45:51,915 --> 00:45:53,016\nused for abortions.\n\n993\n00:45:53,016 --> 00:45:54,017\nThat's the federal law.\n\n994\n00:45:54,017 --> 00:45:57,521\nThat's the law that this\nadministration has enforced.\n\n995\n00:45:57,521 --> 00:46:03,127\nAnd that's why when\nRepublicans suggest they\n\n996\n00:46:03,127 --> 00:46:05,529\nshould shut off funding for\nPlanned Parenthood, the only\n\n997\n00:46:05,529 --> 00:46:08,365\nthing that they're doing is\nproposing to cut access to\n\n998\n00:46:08,365 --> 00:46:11,268\nhealth care that millions\nof Americans rely on.\n\n999\n00:46:11,268 --> 00:46:12,769\nThe Press: So let me ask\nyou, do you think that the\n\n1000\n00:46:12,769 --> 00:46:14,938\nconversations that were had\nlast night, the reaction in\n\n1001\n00:46:14,938 --> 00:46:18,175\nthat room and some of the\nreaction that we've heard\n\n1002\n00:46:18,175 --> 00:46:20,677\nsince then to that argument,\nand others who made similar\n\n1003\n00:46:20,677 --> 00:46:23,680\narguments about Planned\nParenthood and about\n\n1004\n00:46:23,680 --> 00:46:27,184\ndefunding, will have an\nimpact on the budget process?\n\n1005\n00:46:27,184 --> 00:46:29,786\nDo you think it's brought\nthe conversation more broadly?\n\n1006\n00:46:29,786 --> 00:46:31,989\nDid you listen to it last\nnight and say this could\n\n1007\n00:46:31,989 --> 00:46:34,691\nmake it harder for there\nto be a budget deal?\n\n1008\n00:46:34,691 --> 00:46:36,627\nMr. Earnest: Well, look,\nI think that -- are you\n\n1009\n00:46:36,627 --> 00:46:38,595\nreferring specifically to\nthis question of Planned\n\n1010\n00:46:38,595 --> 00:46:40,697\nParenthood, or the active\ndebate in the Republican\n\n1011\n00:46:40,697 --> 00:46:42,499\npresidential primary on it?\n\n1012\n00:46:42,499 --> 00:46:43,400\nThe Press: Well, I'm just\nsaying there's an active\n\n1013\n00:46:43,400 --> 00:46:45,802\ndebate, but this certainly\nhas shone a spotlight on it\n\n1014\n00:46:45,802 --> 00:46:48,305\nin a very huge\nway last night.\n\n1015\n00:46:48,305 --> 00:46:51,074\nMr. Earnest: Well, again, I\ntook note of the fact that\n\n1016\n00:46:51,074 --> 00:46:54,178\nthe preponderance of\ncandidates on that stage\n\n1017\n00:46:54,178 --> 00:46:57,681\nlast night advocated for\nshutting down the federal\n\n1018\n00:46:57,681 --> 00:47:01,618\ngovernment just to prevent\nmillions of families in this\n\n1019\n00:47:01,618 --> 00:47:03,620\ncountry from getting\naccess to health care.\n\n1020\n00:47:03,620 --> 00:47:06,290\nThat is the effective impact\nof the policy that\n\n1021\n00:47:06,290 --> 00:47:07,524\nthey're advocating.\n\n1022\n00:47:07,524 --> 00:47:09,526\nAnd people should\nunderstand that.\n\n1023\n00:47:09,526 --> 00:47:13,997\nAnd 22.9 million viewers who\nwatched CNN now I think do.\n\n1024\n00:47:13,997 --> 00:47:20,404\nAnd that is certainly not an\napproach that the President\n\n1025\n00:47:20,404 --> 00:47:22,406\nsupports, and for a variety\nof reasons -- what's that?\n\n1026\n00:47:22,406 --> 00:47:23,073\nYou're welcome for the plug.\n\n1027\n00:47:23,073 --> 00:47:24,374\n(laughter)\n\n1028\n00:47:24,374 --> 00:47:27,644\nBut that certainly is not a\npolicy or an approach the\n\n1029\n00:47:27,644 --> 00:47:28,645\nPresident supports.\n\n1030\n00:47:28,645 --> 00:47:30,914\nAnd the way that\nRepublicans, including some\n\n1031\n00:47:30,914 --> 00:47:33,617\nRepublican candidates, have\ninjected this ideological\n\n1032\n00:47:33,617 --> 00:47:37,120\nissue into the midst of the\nbudget debate has made it\n\n1033\n00:47:37,120 --> 00:47:39,756\nmore difficult to reach a\nbipartisan budget agreement\n\n1034\n00:47:39,756 --> 00:47:42,226\nand does have consequences\nfor the ability of the\n\n1035\n00:47:42,226 --> 00:47:47,431\nCongress to reach a budget\nagreement, which also has\n\n1036\n00:47:47,431 --> 00:47:49,933\nsignificant consequences\nfor our economy.\n\n1037\n00:47:49,933 --> 00:47:52,369\nYou heard the President\nyesterday, particularly in\n\n1038\n00:47:52,369 --> 00:47:56,506\nthe context of volatile\neconomic markets around the\n\n1039\n00:47:56,506 --> 00:47:59,543\nworld -- volatile financial\nmarkets around the world --\n\n1040\n00:47:59,543 --> 00:48:04,081\nit doesn't make sense for\nCongress to be adding this\n\n1041\n00:48:04,081 --> 00:48:08,285\nvolatility into the\neconomy so unnecessarily.\n\n1042\n00:48:08,285 --> 00:48:13,890\nAnd that President is\nhopeful that this will be\n\n1043\n00:48:13,890 --> 00:48:16,293\none of those rare instances\nin which common sense will\n\n1044\n00:48:16,293 --> 00:48:18,195\nactually prevail\non Capitol Hill.\n\n1045\n00:48:18,195 --> 00:48:19,196\nCheryl.\n\n1046\n00:48:19,196 --> 00:48:20,264\nThe Press: Thanks.\n\n1047\n00:48:20,264 --> 00:48:23,066\nTo sort of follow up on a\ngovernment shutdown, it\n\n1048\n00:48:23,066 --> 00:48:25,769\nseems we're talking about\nthis every year now.\n\n1049\n00:48:25,769 --> 00:48:30,140\nDoes the President now see\nthe threat of a government\n\n1050\n00:48:30,140 --> 00:48:31,775\nshutdown as routine?\n\n1051\n00:48:31,775 --> 00:48:34,711\nAnd what kind of effect does\nthis have, particularly on\n\n1052\n00:48:34,711 --> 00:48:37,047\nthe federal workforce?\n\n1053\n00:48:37,047 --> 00:48:41,184\nMr. Earnest: Well, Cheryl,\nlet me start by saying that\n\n1054\n00:48:41,184 --> 00:48:45,789\nwe didn't have this\nbrinksmanship last year,\n\n1055\n00:48:45,789 --> 00:48:49,226\nprimarily because in the\naftermath of the last\n\n1056\n00:48:49,226 --> 00:48:52,896\ngovernment shutdown that was\nengineered by Republicans,\n\n1057\n00:48:52,896 --> 00:48:55,032\nDemocrats and Republicans on\nCapitol Hill sat down and\n\n1058\n00:48:55,032 --> 00:48:57,834\nhammered out a two-year\nbudget agreement.\n\n1059\n00:48:57,834 --> 00:49:00,070\nThat ended up being\ngood for our economy.\n\n1060\n00:49:00,070 --> 00:49:03,573\nThat was an important way\nthat Congress could support\n\n1061\n00:49:03,573 --> 00:49:04,574\nthe U.S.\n\n1062\n00:49:04,574 --> 00:49:06,610\neconomy and the\nprivate sector.\n\n1063\n00:49:06,610 --> 00:49:09,146\nAnd we encourage them\nto do that again.\n\n1064\n00:49:09,146 --> 00:49:12,516\nIt doesn't mean that they\nyielded a perfect product or\n\n1065\n00:49:12,516 --> 00:49:16,653\na piece of legislation that\nwas beloved by anybody in\n\n1066\n00:49:16,653 --> 00:49:17,888\neither party.\n\n1067\n00:49:17,888 --> 00:49:22,426\nIt's not the kind of\nlegislation for which they\n\n1068\n00:49:22,426 --> 00:49:25,762\nwill erect a specific\nwing of the Barack Obama\n\n1069\n00:49:25,762 --> 00:49:29,733\npresidential library, but it\nis a notable achievement in\n\n1070\n00:49:29,733 --> 00:49:34,104\nthat it reflected bipartisan\ncompromise and it adequately\n\n1071\n00:49:34,104 --> 00:49:36,106\nfunded our economic\nand national security\n\n1072\n00:49:36,106 --> 00:49:41,311\npriorities, and it prevented\nthis damaging debate and\n\n1073\n00:49:41,311 --> 00:49:43,680\navoided the unnecessary risk\nof a potential\n\n1074\n00:49:43,680 --> 00:49:44,681\ngovernment shutdown.\n\n1075\n00:49:44,681 --> 00:49:47,918\nBut two years after the\nlast Republican-engineered\n\n1076\n00:49:47,918 --> 00:49:51,321\ngovernment shutdown,\nunfortunately we seem to be\n\n1077\n00:49:51,321 --> 00:49:53,523\ncareening toward another\none, also engineered\n\n1078\n00:49:53,523 --> 00:49:55,225\nby Republicans.\n\n1079\n00:49:55,225 --> 00:49:58,662\nSo that's bad for the\neconomy, and I do think it\n\n1080\n00:49:58,662 --> 00:50:00,731\ndoes have an impact on the\nmindset of the\n\n1081\n00:50:00,731 --> 00:50:02,299\nfederal workforce.\n\n1082\n00:50:02,299 --> 00:50:06,436\nAnd that's one of the many,\nmany consequences of this\n\n1083\n00:50:06,436 --> 00:50:11,808\nkind of irresponsible\ngamesmanship that we've seen\n\n1084\n00:50:11,808 --> 00:50:15,245\nfrom Republicans on Capitol\nHill and needs to stop.\n\n1085\n00:50:15,245 --> 00:50:18,115\nThe Press: Just to follow\nup, though, on the impact.\n\n1086\n00:50:18,115 --> 00:50:22,953\nDoes the continued threat\nof government shutdown\n\n1087\n00:50:22,953 --> 00:50:26,590\nundermine the public\nconfidence in government?\n\n1088\n00:50:26,590 --> 00:50:29,326\nDoes it hurt\nproductivity and morale?\n\n1089\n00:50:29,326 --> 00:50:32,729\nDoes it undermine our\nstanding on the global stage?\n\n1090\n00:50:32,729 --> 00:50:36,032\nI just heard you talk about\nhow strong the United States\n\n1091\n00:50:36,032 --> 00:50:39,436\nis now on the global stage,\nbut yet it's like another\n\n1092\n00:50:39,436 --> 00:50:40,437\ngovernment shutdown.\n\n1093\n00:50:40,437 --> 00:50:43,073\nMr. Earnest: It surely\ndoesn't help any of that.\n\n1094\n00:50:43,073 --> 00:50:46,877\nAnd again, if we're in a\nsituation where Congress\n\n1095\n00:50:46,877 --> 00:50:49,146\nwants to try to find a way\nto play a constructive role\n\n1096\n00:50:49,146 --> 00:50:52,582\nfor a change, simply doing\n-- fulfilling their most\n\n1097\n00:50:52,582 --> 00:50:56,586\nbasic responsibility in some\nways is an important way for\n\n1098\n00:50:56,586 --> 00:50:58,121\nthem to do that.\n\n1099\n00:50:58,121 --> 00:51:00,524\nCongress was entrusted by\nour Founding Fathers with\n\n1100\n00:51:00,524 --> 00:51:03,794\nsignificant power, and the\nmost significant of those\n\n1101\n00:51:03,794 --> 00:51:06,897\npowers was the power of the\npurse and the ability to\n\n1102\n00:51:06,897 --> 00:51:09,065\npass the budget -- and\nessentially, their\n\n1103\n00:51:09,065 --> 00:51:11,435\nrequirement to pass a\nbudget to allow the federal\n\n1104\n00:51:11,435 --> 00:51:13,336\ngovernment to function.\n\n1105\n00:51:13,336 --> 00:51:15,639\nSo we're hopeful that\nthey'll live up to\n\n1106\n00:51:15,639 --> 00:51:16,640\nthat responsibility.\n\n1107\n00:51:16,640 --> 00:51:19,743\nAnd certainly the last\nthing that the U.S.\n\n1108\n00:51:19,743 --> 00:51:24,481\neconomy needs is the\nunnecessary injection of\n\n1109\n00:51:24,481 --> 00:51:28,985\neven more volatility\ninto the U.S. economy.\n\n1110\n00:51:28,985 --> 00:51:29,419\nToluse.\n\n1111\n00:51:29,419 --> 00:51:32,022\nThe Press: There was\napparently a military coup\n\n1112\n00:51:32,022 --> 00:51:33,723\nin Burkina Faso.\n\n1113\n00:51:33,723 --> 00:51:35,826\nI'm wondering if the White\nHouse has a response to that.\n\n1114\n00:51:35,826 --> 00:51:38,462\nMr. Earnest: I do have a\nlittle something on this.\n\n1115\n00:51:38,462 --> 00:51:40,597\nThe United States is\ndeeply concerned about the\n\n1116\n00:51:40,597 --> 00:51:42,933\nunfolding events\nin Burkina Faso.\n\n1117\n00:51:42,933 --> 00:51:45,836\nWe call for the immediate\nrelease of all officials\n\n1118\n00:51:45,836 --> 00:51:47,337\nthat are being held there.\n\n1119\n00:51:47,337 --> 00:51:49,973\nThe United States strongly\ncondemns any attempt to\n\n1120\n00:51:49,973 --> 00:51:53,777\nseize power through\nextra-constitutional means,\n\n1121\n00:51:53,777 --> 00:51:56,680\nor resolve internal\npolitical disagreements\n\n1122\n00:51:56,680 --> 00:51:57,681\nusing force.\n\n1123\n00:51:57,681 --> 00:52:01,084\nThe United States calls\nfor an immediate end to\n\n1124\n00:52:01,084 --> 00:52:05,522\nviolence, urges the military\npersonnel involved to return\n\n1125\n00:52:05,522 --> 00:52:10,527\nto their barracks, and\nreaffirms our steadfast\n\n1126\n00:52:10,527 --> 00:52:13,096\nsupport for the civilian\ntransitional government to\n\n1127\n00:52:13,096 --> 00:52:15,565\ncontinue its work of\npreparing for free, fair and\n\n1128\n00:52:15,565 --> 00:52:19,035\ncredible elections that are\nscheduled for October 11.\n\n1129\n00:52:19,035 --> 00:52:21,538\nThe Press: I also wanted to\nask about the video that the\n\n1130\n00:52:21,538 --> 00:52:25,275\nPresident starred in or did\na voiceover for earlier\n\n1131\n00:52:25,275 --> 00:52:26,977\ntoday about citizenship.\n\n1132\n00:52:26,977 --> 00:52:32,148\nI'm wondering if that video,\nsort of timed the morning\n\n1133\n00:52:32,148 --> 00:52:35,051\nafter the debate and the\nearlier comments by the\n\n1134\n00:52:35,051 --> 00:52:38,088\nPresident saying\nanti-immigrant rhetoric is\n\n1135\n00:52:38,088 --> 00:52:41,124\nUnited Nations-American, and\nwhat we heard from Joe Biden\n\n1136\n00:52:41,124 --> 00:52:43,660\nsaying that Trump's comments\nwere \"sick\" -- I'm wondering\n\n1137\n00:52:43,660 --> 00:52:45,462\nif there is sort of a\nconcerted effort by the\n\n1138\n00:52:45,462 --> 00:52:48,698\nWhite House to promote\ncitizenship and\n\n1139\n00:52:48,698 --> 00:52:52,402\npro-immigrant language at\na time when we're seeing\n\n1140\n00:52:52,402 --> 00:52:56,606\nDonald Trump and sort of\nsome Republicans who have\n\n1141\n00:52:56,606 --> 00:53:00,777\nexpressed different thoughts\nget a lot of support from\n\n1142\n00:53:00,777 --> 00:53:03,380\nthe voters on the\nRepublican side.\n\n1143\n00:53:03,380 --> 00:53:06,283\nMr. Earnest: Toluse, the\nvideo is released today to\n\n1144\n00:53:06,283 --> 00:53:07,551\nmark \"Citizenship Day.\"\n\n1145\n00:53:07,551 --> 00:53:11,154\nAnd it's an opportunity for\nthe White House to unveil\n\n1146\n00:53:11,154 --> 00:53:12,389\nthe \"Stand Stronger\"\nCitizenship Awareness\n\n1147\n00:53:12,389 --> 00:53:15,125\nCampaign, which is a project\nthat we've engaged in with a\n\n1148\n00:53:15,125 --> 00:53:17,227\nnonprofit called\nCivic Nation.\n\n1149\n00:53:17,227 --> 00:53:19,930\nAnd the goal is to encourage\neligible immigrants to take\n\n1150\n00:53:19,930 --> 00:53:22,299\nan important step in their\nAmerican journey and commit\n\n1151\n00:53:22,299 --> 00:53:23,833\nto American citizenship.\n\n1152\n00:53:23,833 --> 00:53:26,036\nTo launch this effort, the\nPresident released a video\n\n1153\n00:53:26,036 --> 00:53:40,116\nmessage that can be found\non CommitToCitizenship.org.\n\n1154\n00:53:40,116 --> 00:53:42,118\nOverall, the initiative is\nfocused on encouraging the\n\n1155\n00:53:42,118 --> 00:53:44,120\n8.8 million legal immigrants\n--legal permanent residents\n\n1156\n00:53:44,120 --> 00:53:46,122\nto the United States that\nqualify for citizenship to\n\n1157\n00:53:46,122 --> 00:53:48,124\nlearn more about the\nnaturalization process so\n\n1158\n00:53:48,124 --> 00:53:50,093\nthey can solidify their\nroots here in the United\n\n1159\n00:53:50,093 --> 00:53:52,095\nStates and tap into the\nincredible opportunities\n\n1160\n00:53:52,095 --> 00:53:54,097\nthat await new\nAmerican citizens.\n\n1161\n00:53:54,097 --> 00:53:56,099\nIt also bears mentioning at\nthis point that the United\n\n1162\n00:53:56,099 --> 00:53:58,101\nStates also has a path to\ncitizenship for refugees.\n\n1163\n00:53:58,101 --> 00:54:00,103\nAnd we've talked a lot about\nthe status of refugees over\n\n1164\n00:54:00,103 --> 00:54:02,505\nthe last several weeks.\n\n1165\n00:54:02,505 --> 00:54:08,478\nI believe that the number is\n370,000 refugees that have\n\n1166\n00:54:10,714 --> 00:54:15,685\ngotten citizenship since\n2009, when the President\n\n1167\n00:54:15,685 --> 00:54:16,686\ntook office.\n\n1168\n00:54:16,686 --> 00:54:19,656\nAnd again, these refugees\nare individuals who are\n\n1169\n00:54:19,656 --> 00:54:21,791\nclassified as refugees by\nthe United Nations -- they\n\n1170\n00:54:21,791 --> 00:54:23,126\nhave a very specific status.\n\n1171\n00:54:23,126 --> 00:54:27,964\nAnd the United States takes\nin more of these individuals\n\n1172\n00:54:27,964 --> 00:54:29,966\nwith the specific\nU.N.-designated refugee\n\n1173\n00:54:29,966 --> 00:54:33,103\nstatus than every other\nnation in the world combined.\n\n1174\n00:54:33,103 --> 00:54:35,105\nAnd those refugees are\nafforded some important\n\n1175\n00:54:35,105 --> 00:54:37,140\nbenefits, including\nthe opportunity to get\n\n1176\n00:54:37,140 --> 00:54:39,142\ncitizenship here in\nthe United States.\n\n1177\n00:54:39,142 --> 00:54:41,311\nSo it's a very particular\npath, it's a very specific\n\n1178\n00:54:41,311 --> 00:54:45,915\none, but it does reflect the\nkind of opportunity that\n\n1179\n00:54:45,915 --> 00:54:48,985\nawaits refugees, and it\nreflects the kind of\n\n1180\n00:54:48,985 --> 00:54:51,488\nopportunities that the\nUnited States is willing to\n\n1181\n00:54:51,488 --> 00:54:56,426\ngive to those who go through\nthis legal process of\n\n1182\n00:54:56,426 --> 00:54:59,362\nbecoming either a legal\npermanent resident or going\n\n1183\n00:54:59,362 --> 00:55:00,697\nthrough this\nU.N.-administered\n\n1184\n00:55:00,697 --> 00:55:01,531\nrefugee process.\n\n1185\n00:55:01,531 --> 00:55:03,800\nThe Press: If I can just\nfollow up on an earlier\n\n1186\n00:55:03,800 --> 00:55:06,036\nquestion about the\noil export ban.\n\n1187\n00:55:06,036 --> 00:55:08,405\nYou mentioned that the\nWhite House position is\n\n1188\n00:55:08,405 --> 00:55:09,439\ncrystal-clear.\n\n1189\n00:55:09,439 --> 00:55:11,841\nBut in the past, you sort of\nsaid that this is a decision\n\n1190\n00:55:11,841 --> 00:55:14,878\nthat's housed at the\nCommerce Department.\n\n1191\n00:55:14,878 --> 00:55:20,483\nI'm wondering if you can go\na little bit beyond that to\n\n1192\n00:55:20,483 --> 00:55:22,152\ntalk about whether or not\nthe White House is actually\n\n1193\n00:55:22,152 --> 00:55:25,622\nstudying this issue,\nwhether or not the Commerce\n\n1194\n00:55:25,622 --> 00:55:27,390\nDepartment, which is under\nthe White House, is in\n\n1195\n00:55:27,390 --> 00:55:29,959\nconversations with you.\n\n1196\n00:55:29,959 --> 00:55:32,796\nDo you have a broader\nphilosophical position on\n\n1197\n00:55:32,796 --> 00:55:36,933\nthe crude export ban itself,\nmore than just sort of\n\n1198\n00:55:36,933 --> 00:55:38,468\nsaying this is something\nthat the Commerce Department\n\n1199\n00:55:38,468 --> 00:55:42,272\nis in charge of?\n\n1200\n00:55:42,272 --> 00:55:43,473\nMr. Earnest: Well, it's\na clever way to ask\n\n1201\n00:55:43,473 --> 00:55:44,474\nthe question.\n\n1202\n00:55:44,474 --> 00:55:48,945\nOur crystal-clear position\nis in opposition to the\n\n1203\n00:55:48,945 --> 00:55:51,548\nlegislation that's currently\nbeing contemplated by\n\n1204\n00:55:51,548 --> 00:55:52,549\nCongress right now.\n\n1205\n00:55:52,549 --> 00:55:55,485\nThe fact is, this is a\npolicy decision that's made\n\n1206\n00:55:55,485 --> 00:55:56,753\nat the Commerce Department.\n\n1207\n00:55:56,753 --> 00:56:01,825\nI would allow that there is\na view at the White House,\n\n1208\n00:56:01,825 --> 00:56:06,563\nbut I'm not prepared to\nengage in that philosophical\n\n1209\n00:56:06,563 --> 00:56:10,533\nconversation from\nthe podium today.\n\n1210\n00:56:10,533 --> 00:56:10,834\nI'm sorry?\n\n1211\n00:56:10,834 --> 00:56:11,835\nThe Press: Why not?\n\n1212\n00:56:11,835 --> 00:56:14,571\nMr. Earnest: Well, I know\nthat particularly readers of\n\n1213\n00:56:14,571 --> 00:56:17,607\nBloomberg are well aware of\nthe market sensitivities\n\n1214\n00:56:17,607 --> 00:56:19,209\nassociated with these kinds\nof deliberations, or the\n\n1215\n00:56:19,209 --> 00:56:22,679\nfact that these\ndeliberations may even be\n\n1216\n00:56:22,679 --> 00:56:24,681\ntaking place -- which I'm\nnot in a position to confirm\n\n1217\n00:56:24,681 --> 00:56:26,416\nfrom here.\n\n1218\n00:56:26,416 --> 00:56:29,786\nSo that's why I've been\nquite circumspect, maybe\n\n1219\n00:56:29,786 --> 00:56:32,322\nuncharacteristically\ncircumspect in discussing\n\n1220\n00:56:32,322 --> 00:56:33,323\nthis particular issue.\n\n1221\n00:56:33,323 --> 00:56:35,091\nGo ahead, Scott.\n\n1222\n00:56:35,091 --> 00:56:37,961\nThe Press: Is it fair to say\nthat you're crystal-clear\n\n1223\n00:56:37,961 --> 00:56:39,295\nagainst this particular\nbill --\n\n1224\n00:56:39,295 --> 00:56:40,296\nMr. Earnest: That's correct.\n\n1225\n00:56:40,296 --> 00:56:42,398\nThe Press: -- but you're not\nnecessarily crystal-clear\n\n1226\n00:56:42,398 --> 00:56:46,436\nagainst another bill that\nwould lift the ban on oil?\n\n1227\n00:56:46,436 --> 00:56:48,138\nI mean, is it something\nabout this bill in\n\n1228\n00:56:48,138 --> 00:56:55,278\nparticular, beyond the basic\nfact of lifting the ban on oil?\n\n1229\n00:56:55,278 --> 00:56:58,615\nMr. Earnest: Well, we are\nopposed to this bill, and\n\n1230\n00:56:58,615 --> 00:57:00,617\nthe reason that we oppose\nthe bill is because this is\n\n1231\n00:57:00,617 --> 00:57:03,586\na decision that actually can\nbe made and should be made,\n\n1232\n00:57:03,586 --> 00:57:05,588\nin our view, by the\nCommerce Department.\n\n1233\n00:57:05,588 --> 00:57:06,790\nThe Press: So it's\njurisdictional.\n\n1234\n00:57:06,790 --> 00:57:08,558\nMr. Earnest: It doesn't\nrequire an act of Congress\n\n1235\n00:57:08,558 --> 00:57:11,327\nto make this\npolicy decision.\n\n1236\n00:57:11,327 --> 00:57:13,329\nSo we believe that the\nCommerce Department has\n\n1237\n00:57:13,329 --> 00:57:14,397\naccess to all the expertise\nand information that they\n\n1238\n00:57:14,397 --> 00:57:17,600\nneed to set this policy.\n\n1239\n00:57:17,600 --> 00:57:20,336\nFrancesca.\n\n1240\n00:57:20,336 --> 00:57:21,938\nThe Press: Hey, Josh.\n\n1241\n00:57:21,938 --> 00:57:26,509\nI'm being made aware that\nthe list of attendees for\n\n1242\n00:57:26,509 --> 00:57:29,979\nthe Pope's visit, the\nreception that's being had\n\n1243\n00:57:29,979 --> 00:57:31,581\nhasn't been released yet.\n\n1244\n00:57:31,581 --> 00:57:35,652\nBut a news organization\ntoday reported that among\n\n1245\n00:57:35,652 --> 00:57:38,922\nthe list of guests there\nwould be a pro-choice, a\n\n1246\n00:57:38,922 --> 00:57:42,892\ntransgender woman, and an\nopenly gay episcopal bishop.\n\n1247\n00:57:42,892 --> 00:57:45,461\nAnd I was wondering if the\nWhite House is trying to\n\n1248\n00:57:45,461 --> 00:57:49,299\nsend a message or make a\nstatement with the invitees\n\n1249\n00:57:49,299 --> 00:57:50,900\nat that reception.\n\n1250\n00:57:50,900 --> 00:57:52,936\nMr. Earnest: Francesca,\nI have not seen the news\n\n1251\n00:57:52,936 --> 00:57:54,938\nreport that you're\nreferring to.\n\n1252\n00:57:54,938 --> 00:57:59,175\nI think it's important\nfor all of you to, as you\n\n1253\n00:57:59,175 --> 00:58:02,245\nconsider chasing that\nreport, to know that there\n\n1254\n00:58:02,245 --> 00:58:05,014\nwill be -- I believe the\nnumber is about 15,000\n\n1255\n00:58:05,014 --> 00:58:07,016\npeople who will be on the\nSouth Lawn of the White\n\n1256\n00:58:07,016 --> 00:58:12,889\nHouse, or in the vicinity\nof the White House to\n\n1257\n00:58:12,889 --> 00:58:15,425\nparticipate in those\nceremonies welcoming the\n\n1258\n00:58:15,425 --> 00:58:18,628\nPope to Washington.\n\n1259\n00:58:18,628 --> 00:58:20,697\nSo we'll have more\ninformation on the guest\n\n1260\n00:58:20,697 --> 00:58:24,267\nlist once I can actually\nconfirm for myself who's on it.\n\n1261\n00:58:24,267 --> 00:58:27,203\nBut I think that's why I\nwould warn you against\n\n1262\n00:58:27,203 --> 00:58:31,708\ndrawing a lot of conclusions\nabout one or two or maybe\n\n1263\n00:58:31,708 --> 00:58:34,944\neven three people who may be\non the guest list, because\n\n1264\n00:58:34,944 --> 00:58:38,615\nthere will be 15,000\nother people there too.\n\n1265\n00:58:38,615 --> 00:58:39,616\nThe Press: Sure.\n\n1266\n00:58:39,616 --> 00:58:41,584\nI'm just making sure that\nthere's also not some sort\n\n1267\n00:58:41,584 --> 00:58:43,753\nof other reception that's\ntaking place, like a private\n\n1268\n00:58:43,753 --> 00:58:45,722\nreception maybe they would\nbe not necessarily on the\n\n1269\n00:58:45,722 --> 00:58:48,958\nopen lawn thing that you're\ntalking about where 15,000\n\n1270\n00:58:48,958 --> 00:58:50,360\npeople would be at.\n\n1271\n00:58:50,360 --> 00:58:52,061\nMr. Earnest: We'll have more\ninformation about the exact\n\n1272\n00:58:52,061 --> 00:58:55,365\nitinerary for the\nPope early next week.\n\n1273\n00:58:55,365 --> 00:58:58,401\nThe Press: 15,000 here?\n\n1274\n00:58:58,401 --> 00:59:00,937\nMr. Earnest: Yes, on the\nSouth Lawn and on the\n\n1275\n00:59:00,937 --> 00:59:03,339\nEllipse and things.\n\n1276\n00:59:03,339 --> 00:59:05,441\nIt's why you may have\nnoticed that the Officer of\n\n1277\n00:59:05,441 --> 00:59:08,344\nPersonnel Management has\nencouraged federal workers,\n\n1278\n00:59:08,344 --> 00:59:11,114\nat least on that day,\nto take advantage of\n\n1279\n00:59:11,114 --> 00:59:13,549\ntelecommuting policies that\nmay be in place at\n\n1280\n00:59:13,549 --> 00:59:14,350\ntheir agency.\n\n1281\n00:59:14,350 --> 00:59:16,352\nTraffic is going\nto be a mess.\n\n1282\n00:59:16,352 --> 00:59:17,353\nSteve.\n\n1283\n00:59:17,353 --> 00:59:20,023\nThe Press: Back to\nPlanned Parenthood.\n\n1284\n00:59:20,023 --> 00:59:24,994\nI'm wondering, would the\nWhite House be interested or\n\n1285\n00:59:24,994 --> 00:59:28,731\nwilling to consider a\npotential compromise that\n\n1286\n00:59:28,731 --> 00:59:31,501\nwould fall short of\ndefunding Planned\n\n1287\n00:59:31,501 --> 00:59:34,003\nParenthood, which you've\nmade absolutely clear is on\n\n1288\n00:59:34,003 --> 00:59:36,039\nthe table but be vetoed?\n\n1289\n00:59:36,039 --> 00:59:39,208\nThere are proposals that\nwould address the specific\n\n1290\n00:59:39,208 --> 00:59:43,179\nissue in these tapes, which\nis money changing hands for\n\n1291\n00:59:43,179 --> 00:59:46,482\nfetal body parts from\naborted fetuses.\n\n1292\n00:59:46,482 --> 00:59:50,386\nAnd there's a proposal in\nthe House by Kevin Yoder\n\n1293\n00:59:50,386 --> 00:59:55,224\nthat would say you couldn't\nget any expenses paid for --\n\n1294\n00:59:55,224 --> 00:59:58,061\nyou couldn't get a check\nin your account if you're\n\n1295\n00:59:58,061 --> 01:00:00,296\nPlanned Parenthood --\nwork at another clinic.\n\n1296\n01:00:00,296 --> 01:00:03,366\nIs that the sort of thing\nthat maybe this could\n\n1297\n01:00:03,366 --> 01:00:06,703\nresolve this fight short of\na shutdown, that the White\n\n1298\n01:00:06,703 --> 01:00:09,238\nHouse would be interested\nin potentially trying\n\n1299\n01:00:09,238 --> 01:00:10,239\nto negotiate?\n\n1300\n01:00:10,239 --> 01:00:13,509\nMr. Earnest: Well, Steve, I\nhaven't seen any other those\n\n1301\n01:00:13,509 --> 01:00:15,511\n-- or at least that one\nproposal that you've\n\n1302\n01:00:15,511 --> 01:00:16,512\nnoted there.\n\n1303\n01:00:16,512 --> 01:00:19,482\nSo I'm reluctant to weigh in\non it one way or the other,\n\n1304\n01:00:19,482 --> 01:00:22,151\nor even indicate our\nwillingness to consider it.\n\n1305\n01:00:22,151 --> 01:00:24,153\nI think we've been pretty\ndirect about what our\n\n1306\n01:00:24,153 --> 01:00:28,624\nconcerns are, and those\nconcerns center on the fact\n\n1307\n01:00:28,624 --> 01:00:31,060\nthat there is already\nfederal law in place that's\n\n1308\n01:00:31,060 --> 01:00:33,696\nenforced by this\nadministration that prevents\n\n1309\n01:00:33,696 --> 01:00:37,133\nany organization from using\nfederal funds to\n\n1310\n01:00:37,133 --> 01:00:38,134\nperform abortions.\n\n1311\n01:00:38,134 --> 01:00:40,536\nIt's against the law,\nand it's a law that this\n\n1312\n01:00:40,536 --> 01:00:41,804\nadministration enforces.\n\n1313\n01:00:41,804 --> 01:00:45,475\nThat's why the effect of the\npolicy that's being advanced\n\n1314\n01:00:45,475 --> 01:00:48,711\nby Republicans does nothing\nmore than take away health\n\n1315\n01:00:48,711 --> 01:00:51,214\ncare access for millions\nof families all across\n\n1316\n01:00:51,214 --> 01:00:52,215\nthe country.\n\n1317\n01:00:52,215 --> 01:00:56,052\nAnd that's why the President\nis vehemently opposed to it.\n\n1318\n01:00:56,052 --> 01:00:59,389\nThat's why -- I guess I'll\nalso point out this is not\n\n1319\n01:00:59,389 --> 01:01:01,758\nthe first time that the\nPresident has opposed a\n\n1320\n01:01:01,758 --> 01:01:05,928\nRepublican effort to take\nhealth care away from people.\n\n1321\n01:01:05,928 --> 01:01:09,065\nI'm not really sure what the\nRepublican fascination is\n\n1322\n01:01:09,065 --> 01:01:11,367\nwith taking health care away\nfrom millions of American\n\n1323\n01:01:11,367 --> 01:01:13,069\nfamilies, but it's not\nsomething the President is\n\n1324\n01:01:13,069 --> 01:01:14,137\ngoing to go along with.\n\n1325\n01:01:14,137 --> 01:01:16,039\nThe Press: And you don't\nhave a position at this\n\n1326\n01:01:16,039 --> 01:01:19,075\npoint on whether the\nPresident would veto an\n\n1327\n01:01:19,075 --> 01:01:21,978\neffort to prohibit anybody\nfrom getting a check in\n\n1328\n01:01:21,978 --> 01:01:24,280\nreturn for a body part?\n\n1329\n01:01:24,280 --> 01:01:26,249\nMr. Earnest: I just don't\nknow that that -- what I'm\n\n1330\n01:01:26,249 --> 01:01:28,251\nsaying is I don't know that\nthe administration has\n\n1331\n01:01:28,251 --> 01:01:30,520\nconsidered that specific\nproposal from Mr. Yoder.\n\n1332\n01:01:30,520 --> 01:01:34,023\nThe Press: Back\nto Guantanamo.\n\n1333\n01:01:34,023 --> 01:01:36,225\nSenator McCain -- who I know\nthe President called this\n\n1334\n01:01:36,225 --> 01:01:40,963\nspring to try to set the\nstage for a compromise on\n\n1335\n01:01:40,963 --> 01:01:44,267\nthis -- Senator McCain is\ntelling reporters today that\n\n1336\n01:01:44,267 --> 01:01:47,904\nhe needs to see a specific\nplan from the White House, a\n\n1337\n01:01:47,904 --> 01:01:51,174\nplan for where these\ndetainees are going to go,\n\n1338\n01:01:51,174 --> 01:01:54,977\nan actual specific site if\nthey're going to be brought\n\n1339\n01:01:54,977 --> 01:01:58,114\nto the United States, and\nnot just sort of a range, a\n\n1340\n01:01:58,114 --> 01:01:59,749\nmenu of options.\n\n1341\n01:01:59,749 --> 01:02:02,318\nIn addition to -- you\nhaven't had a timeline yet,\n\n1342\n01:02:02,318 --> 01:02:04,787\nbut you're facing a\ndeadline with the defense\n\n1343\n01:02:04,787 --> 01:02:06,689\nauthorization bill that the\nPresident has threatened to\n\n1344\n01:02:06,689 --> 01:02:07,924\nveto over this issue.\n\n1345\n01:02:07,924 --> 01:02:10,526\nAnd McCain says he can't go\nto his colleagues and get\n\n1346\n01:02:10,526 --> 01:02:15,098\nthem to vote for something\nthat you want until he has that.\n\n1347\n01:02:15,098 --> 01:02:17,567\nIs that sense of urgency\nknown in the White House?\n\n1348\n01:02:17,567 --> 01:02:22,305\nDo they understand where\nMcCain is at here?\n\n1349\n01:02:22,305 --> 01:02:25,575\nMr. Earnest: Well, Senator\nMcCain is one of those in\n\n1350\n01:02:25,575 --> 01:02:28,644\nCongress that, depending on\nthe day you ask him, does\n\n1351\n01:02:28,644 --> 01:02:31,380\nindicate a willingness to\nwork with us constructively\n\n1352\n01:02:31,380 --> 01:02:33,382\nto close the prison\nat Guantanamo Bay.\n\n1353\n01:02:33,382 --> 01:02:36,452\nAnd so it appears that today\nmight have been one those days.\n\n1354\n01:02:36,452 --> 01:02:42,758\nSo I think what you would\nsee from the administration\n\n1355\n01:02:42,758 --> 01:02:46,963\nis a desire to engage him.\n\n1356\n01:02:46,963 --> 01:02:49,999\nAnd I would just point out\nthat, as I mentioned in\n\n1357\n01:02:49,999 --> 01:02:53,536\nanswering an earlier\nquestion, that the\n\n1358\n01:02:53,536 --> 01:02:56,172\nadministration has been\ndoing site surveys of\n\n1359\n01:02:56,172 --> 01:02:57,373\nspecific locations.\n\n1360\n01:02:57,373 --> 01:03:00,543\nAnd I think that should give\nyou an indication that the\n\n1361\n01:03:00,543 --> 01:03:03,980\nadministration is taking the\nformulation of this plan\n\n1362\n01:03:03,980 --> 01:03:07,250\nquite seriously and is\ninterested in how the\n\n1363\n01:03:07,250 --> 01:03:09,785\ndetails of that\nplan would work.\n\n1364\n01:03:09,785 --> 01:03:12,788\nI don't want to prejudge at\nthis point exactly what form\n\n1365\n01:03:12,788 --> 01:03:15,291\na presentation like\nthat would take.\n\n1366\n01:03:15,291 --> 01:03:18,628\nI don't want to get ahead of\nany proposals that they may\n\n1367\n01:03:18,628 --> 01:03:20,630\nhave to offer in terms of\nwhat those details look like.\n\n1368\n01:03:20,630 --> 01:03:25,334\nBut the interest that\nSenator McCain is showing\n\n1369\n01:03:25,334 --> 01:03:29,839\ntoday in cooperating with\nthe administration on this\n\n1370\n01:03:29,839 --> 01:03:32,341\nnational security priority\nis one that we\n\n1371\n01:03:32,341 --> 01:03:33,876\ntake seriously.\n\n1372\n01:03:33,876 --> 01:03:37,046\nAnd I think that's why you\nhave seen us seek to engage\n\n1373\n01:03:37,046 --> 01:03:39,549\nhim in a spirit of\ncooperation and respect to\n\n1374\n01:03:39,549 --> 01:03:42,485\ntry to advance that measure.\n\n1375\n01:03:42,485 --> 01:03:44,954\nSo there is hard work\nbeing done on this.\n\n1376\n01:03:44,954 --> 01:03:48,624\nAnd I think, quite frankly,\nI'll be in a position to\n\n1377\n01:03:48,624 --> 01:03:52,295\nspeak a little bit more\nabout the details of this\n\n1378\n01:03:52,295 --> 01:03:55,131\nplan once something has been\nsent up to Capitol Hill.\n\n1379\n01:03:55,131 --> 01:03:56,966\nThe Press: Well, he's\nalso threatened -- if the\n\n1380\n01:03:56,966 --> 01:04:02,371\nPresident and his veto\nthreats stand, he's also\n\n1381\n01:04:02,371 --> 01:04:05,575\nthreatened to start blocking\ncivilian nominees for\n\n1382\n01:04:05,575 --> 01:04:06,576\nthe Senate.\n\n1383\n01:04:06,576 --> 01:04:08,644\nMr. Earnest: Because they're\njust speeding through right\n\n1384\n01:04:08,644 --> 01:04:11,914\nnow, I mean just\nsailing through.\n\n1385\n01:04:11,914 --> 01:04:13,916\nIt's hard to keep track\nof all of them, isn't it?\n\n1386\n01:04:13,916 --> 01:04:15,918\nThe Press: Well, I'm just\nsaying that this is starting\n\n1387\n01:04:15,918 --> 01:04:16,986\nto escalate.\n\n1388\n01:04:16,986 --> 01:04:18,120\nYou're coming up near\nthe end of the year.\n\n1389\n01:04:18,120 --> 01:04:19,021\nMr. Earnest: I'm not too\nconcerned about it, though.\n\n1390\n01:04:19,021 --> 01:04:20,790\nWe saw all kinds of\nroadblocks with our nominees\n\n1391\n01:04:20,790 --> 01:04:22,191\nall the time.\n\n1392\n01:04:22,191 --> 01:04:25,061\nSo that's not something that\nwe'd be particular\n\n1393\n01:04:25,061 --> 01:04:26,295\nconcerned about.\n\n1394\n01:04:26,295 --> 01:04:27,496\nDave, I'll give\nyou the last one.\n\n1395\n01:04:27,496 --> 01:04:28,297\nThe Press: Thanks, Josh.\n\n1396\n01:04:28,297 --> 01:04:29,365\nBack on Syria.\n\n1397\n01:04:29,365 --> 01:04:32,401\nA year ago the President\nsaid he wanted to train and\n\n1398\n01:04:32,401 --> 01:04:37,139\nequip 15,000 opposition\nfighters to defeat ISIL.\n\n1399\n01:04:37,139 --> 01:04:41,043\nI quote him saying, \"We must\nstrengthen the opposition as\n\n1400\n01:04:41,043 --> 01:04:43,412\nthe best counterweight\nto extremists.\"\n\n1401\n01:04:43,412 --> 01:04:45,848\nDoes the President\nstill believe that?\n\n1402\n01:04:45,848 --> 01:04:52,321\nMr. Earnest: Well, I think,\nDave, I mean obviously the\n\n1403\n01:04:52,321 --> 01:04:54,323\nspecific train-and-equip\nprogram that the Department\n\n1404\n01:04:54,323 --> 01:04:57,260\nof Defense has been working\nto implement over the last\n\n1405\n01:04:57,260 --> 01:05:02,465\nyear or so has fallen\nfar short of that goal.\n\n1406\n01:05:02,465 --> 01:05:04,467\nWe knew at the beginning and\nthe President knew when he\n\n1407\n01:05:04,467 --> 01:05:07,536\nuttered those words how\ndifficult of a challenge\n\n1408\n01:05:07,536 --> 01:05:10,706\nstanding up this proposal\nand implementing this\n\n1409\n01:05:10,706 --> 01:05:12,074\nproposal would be.\n\n1410\n01:05:12,074 --> 01:05:14,944\nI think in fairness to the\nPresident, I don't think he\n\n1411\n01:05:14,944 --> 01:05:19,615\ncontemplated those 15,000\nSyrian opposition fighters\n\n1412\n01:05:19,615 --> 01:05:22,852\nbeing trained and equipped\nand fighting all within the\n\n1413\n01:05:22,852 --> 01:05:23,853\nspace of one year.\n\n1414\n01:05:23,853 --> 01:05:30,526\nBut what I will say is that\nthere is -- that General\n\n1415\n01:05:30,526 --> 01:05:33,696\nAustin has made clear that\nhe's going to consider\n\n1416\n01:05:33,696 --> 01:05:37,400\nchanges to the program and\ntry to determine what kinds\n\n1417\n01:05:37,400 --> 01:05:41,904\nof changes can be made to\nyield much better results.\n\n1418\n01:05:41,904 --> 01:05:46,008\nThe other thing that the\nadministration has sought to\n\n1419\n01:05:46,008 --> 01:05:52,682\ndo is to offer greater\nsupport to those Syrian\n\n1420\n01:05:52,682 --> 01:05:55,484\nopposition fighters that\nare already fighting.\n\n1421\n01:05:55,484 --> 01:06:00,723\nAnd there is significant\nsupport that the United\n\n1422\n01:06:00,723 --> 01:06:03,659\nStates and our coalition\npartners have offered to\n\n1423\n01:06:03,659 --> 01:06:07,697\nSyrian Kurds, in particular\nwho have been effective in\n\n1424\n01:06:07,697 --> 01:06:10,633\ndriving ISIL out of some\nareas of northern and\n\n1425\n01:06:10,633 --> 01:06:13,102\nnortheastern Syria.\n\n1426\n01:06:13,102 --> 01:06:18,174\nWe are in a place where we\nhave nearly shut off ISIL's\n\n1427\n01:06:18,174 --> 01:06:21,177\naccess to the\nborder with Turkey.\n\n1428\n01:06:21,177 --> 01:06:24,413\nThis is a border that's\nnearly 600 miles long.\n\n1429\n01:06:24,413 --> 01:06:26,449\nAnd they only have a narrow\ncorridor now in which to\n\n1430\n01:06:26,449 --> 01:06:28,584\noperate, and we're\nseeking to close that.\n\n1431\n01:06:28,584 --> 01:06:32,388\nThat is thanks primarily to\nthe efforts of those Syrian\n\n1432\n01:06:32,388 --> 01:06:35,257\nopposition fighters that are\nbeing backed by coalition\n\n1433\n01:06:35,257 --> 01:06:37,026\nmilitary airstrikes.\n\n1434\n01:06:37,026 --> 01:06:40,463\nAnd those fighters have also\nbenefited from material\n\n1435\n01:06:40,463 --> 01:06:42,798\nsupport by the United States\nand our coalition partners,\n\n1436\n01:06:42,798 --> 01:06:43,799\nas well.\n\n1437\n01:06:43,799 --> 01:06:45,801\nSo that's just one example\nof how we have been able to\n\n1438\n01:06:45,801 --> 01:06:49,205\ndeepen our cooperation with\nfighters on the ground in\n\n1439\n01:06:49,205 --> 01:06:52,274\nSyria in a way that has\nadvanced our goal to degrade\n\n1440\n01:06:52,274 --> 01:06:53,409\nand ultimately destroy ISIL.\n\n1441\n01:06:53,409 --> 01:06:56,045\nThe Press: And in July\nSecretary Carter said, to\n\n1442\n01:06:56,045 --> 01:06:59,081\nthat point, we had trained\nand equipped about 60\n\n1443\n01:06:59,081 --> 01:07:01,050\nSyrian fighters.\n\n1444\n01:07:01,050 --> 01:07:03,152\nAnd now we have\nfour or five.\n\n1445\n01:07:03,152 --> 01:07:04,920\nIs it fair to say the\nPresident is discouraged by\n\n1446\n01:07:04,920 --> 01:07:05,888\nthat direction?\n\n1447\n01:07:05,888 --> 01:07:07,957\nMr. Earnest: I think it's\nfair for you to say that the\n\n1448\n01:07:07,957 --> 01:07:14,530\nPresident believes that the\nprogram needs to operate at\n\n1449\n01:07:14,530 --> 01:07:17,700\na higher -- a\nmuch higher level.\n\n1450\n01:07:17,700 --> 01:07:19,702\nAnd that's why General\nAustin is considering a\n\n1451\n01:07:19,702 --> 01:07:21,704\nrange of changes\nto the program.\n\n1452\n01:07:21,704 --> 01:07:23,706\nFor the kinds of changes\nthey're considering I'd\n\n1453\n01:07:23,706 --> 01:07:25,674\nrefer you to the\nDepartment of Defense.\n\n1454\n01:07:25,674 --> 01:07:27,676\nThey may or may not be able\nto tell you about some of\n\n1455\n01:07:27,676 --> 01:07:28,677\nthose plans.\n\n1456\n01:07:28,677 --> 01:07:30,880\nBut the President certainly\nhas much higher expectations\n\n1457\n01:07:30,880 --> 01:07:31,881\nfor the program.\n\n1458\n01:07:31,881 --> 01:07:32,848\nThanks a lot, everybody.\n\n1459\n01:07:32,848 --> 01:07:33,682\nWe'll see you tomorrow.\n\n1460\n01:07:33,682 --> 01:07:34,650\nThe Press: Josh, did\nyou see the Fed news?\n\n1461\n01:07:34,650 --> 01:07:35,918\nYou probably didn't.\n\n1462\n01:07:35,918 --> 01:07:36,452\nMr. Earnest: I didn't.\n\n1463\n01:07:36,452 --> 01:07:37,353\nThe Press: They're leaving\nthe rates unchanged.\n\n1464\n01:07:37,353 --> 01:07:38,821\nIs the White House going\nto have a comment on that?\n\n1465\n01:07:38,821 --> 01:07:40,322\nMr. Earnest: I doubt it.\n\n1466\n01:07:40,322 --> 01:07:40,756\nThe Press: Doubt it.\n\n1467\n01:07:40,756 --> 01:07:41,457\nOkay.\n\n1468\n01:07:41,457 --> 01:07:42,792\nMr. Earnest: Thanks, guys.\n\n","markerStore":{"nextMarkerId":47,"markersById":{"0":{"range":{"start":{"row":0,"column":0},"end":{"row":0,"column":0}